{"title_page": "Flame robin", "text_new": "{{short description|A small passerine bird native to southeastern Australia}}\n{{speciesbox\n | name                = Flame robin\n | status              = NT\n | status_system       = IUCN3.1\n | status_ref          = <ref name=IUCN>{{cite iucn|url=https://www.iucnredlist.org/details/22704819/0 |title=''Petroica phoenicea'' |author=BirdLife International |author-link=BirdLife International |year=2012 |access-date=26 November 2013|ref=harv}}</ref>\n | image               = Flame Robin, Eaglehawk Neck..jpg\n | genus               = Petroica\n | species             = phoenicea\n | authority           = [[John Gould|Gould]], 1837\n | range_map           = Flamerobin dist gnangarra.png\n}}\n\nThe '''flame robin''' (''Petroica phoenicea'') is a small [[passerine]] bird native to [[Australia]]. It is a moderately common resident of the coolest parts of south-eastern Australia, including [[Tasmania]]. Like the other two red-breasted ''Petroica'' robins&mdash;the [[scarlet robin]] and the [[red-capped robin]]&mdash;it is often simply called the ''robin redbreast''. Like many brightly coloured robins of the [[Petroicidae]], it is [[Sexual dimorphism|sexually dimorphic]]. Measuring {{convert|12|\u2013|14|cm|in|abbr=on}} long, the flame robin has dark brown eyes and a small thin black bill. The male has a brilliant orange-red chest and throat, and a white patch on the forehead above the bill. Its upper parts are iron-grey with white bars, and its tail black with white tips. The female is a nondescript grey-brown. Its song has been described as the most musical of its genus.\n\nThe position of the flame robin and its Australian relatives on the passerine family tree is unclear; the Petroicidae are not closely related to either the [[European robin|European]] or [[American robin]]s, but appear to be an early offshoot of the [[Passerida]] group of [[songbird]]s. The flame robin is predominantly [[insectivore|insectivorous]], pouncing on prey from a perch in a tree, or foraging on the ground. A [[territory (animal)|territorial]] bird, the flame robin employs song and plumage displays to mark out and defend its territory. Classified by [[BirdLife International]] as ''[[Near Threatened]]'', the species has suffered a marked decline in the past 25 years.\n\n==Taxonomy==\nThe flame robin was first [[Species description|described]] by the French [[natural history|naturalist]]s, [[Jean Ren\u00e9 Constant Quoy]] and [[Joseph Paul Gaimard]], in 1830 as ''Muscicapa chrysoptera''.<ref>Quoy, Jean Ren\u00e9 Constant; Gaimard, Joseph Paul in Dumont-d'Urville, J. (1830). ''Voyage de d\u00e9couvertes de l'Astrolabe ex\u00e9cut\u00e9 par ordre du Roi, pendant les anne\u00e9s 1826\u20131827\u20131828\u20131829, sous le commandement de M.J. Dumont-d'Urville''. Zoologie. Paris: J. Tastu Vol. '''1'''</ref> The [[specific name (zoology)|specific epithet]], ''chrysoptera'', is derived from the [[Ancient Greek]] words ''chrysos'' 'golden', and ''pteron'' 'feather'.<ref name=Liddell1980>{{cite book | author = Liddell, Henry George | author-link = Henry Liddell | author2 = Scott, Robert | author2-link = Robert Scott (philologist) | year = 1980 | title = [[A Greek\u2013English Lexicon]] (Abridged Edition) | publisher = [[Oxford University Press]] | location = Oxford, United Kingdom | isbn = 0-19-910207-4 | pages = [https://archive.org/details/lexicon00lidd/page/615 615, 791] }}</ref>\n\n[[John Gould]] placed the flame robin in its current genus as ''Petroica phoenicea'' in his 1837 description, and it was this latter binomial name that has been used since that time. Given this, Quoy and Gaimard's name was declared a ''[[nomen oblitum]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Species ''Petroica (Littlera) phoenicea'' Gould, 1837|url=http://www.environment.gov.au/biodiversity/abrs/online-resources/fauna/afd/taxa/234a4598-0331-4881-aaa9-9f635d1890d9|accessdate=26 August 2010|author=((Department of the Environment, Water, Heritage and the Arts))|date=October 9, 2008|publisher=Australian Government|work=Australian Biological Resources Study: Australian Faunal Directory|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121012084338/http://www.environment.gov.au/biodiversity/abrs/online-resources/fauna/afd/taxa/234a4598-0331-4881-aaa9-9f635d1890d9|archivedate=12 October 2012}}</ref> The generic name is derived from the Ancient Greek words ''petros'' 'rock' and ''oikos'' 'home', from the birds' habit of sitting on rocks.<ref>Boles, p. 66.</ref> The [[specific name (zoology)|specific epithet]] is also derived from Ancient Greek, from the adjective ''phoinikes'' 'red'. It is one of five red- or pink-breasted species [[common name|colloquially]] known as \"red robins\", as distinct from the \"yellow robins\" of the genus ''[[Eopsaltria]]''. Although named after the [[European robin]], the flame robin is not closely related to either it or the [[American robin]].<ref name=\"Boles, p. xv\"/> The Australian robins were placed in the [[Old World flycatcher]] family [[Muscicapidae]],<ref name=\"Boles, p. xv\">Boles, p. xv.</ref> and the whistler family [[Pachycephalidae]],<ref name=Boles35>Boles, p. 35.</ref> before being [[Biological classification|classified]] in their own family [[Petroicidae]].<ref name=Boles35/><ref>Gill, F. and D. Donsker, eds. (2020). IOC World Bird List (v 10.1). Doi 10.14344/IOC.ML.10.1.  http://www.worldbirdnames.org/</ref> [[Charles Sibley|Sibley]] and [[Jon Edward Ahlquist|Ahlquist]]'s [[DNA-DNA hybridisation]] studies placed the robins in a [[Corvida]] [[parvorder]] comprising many tropical and Australian passerines, including [[Pardalotidae|pardalotes]], [[Maluridae|fairy-wrens]] and [[Meliphagidae|honeyeaters]], as well as crows.<ref name=\"SibAhl\">{{cite book|author1=Sibley, Charles G. |author2=Ahlquist, Jon E. |title=Phylogeny and Classification of Birds: A Study in Molecular Evolution |publisher=Yale University Press|location=New Haven, Connecticut|year=1990|pages=603, 610\u201327|isbn=0-300-04085-7}}</ref> However, subsequent [[molecular phylogenetics|molecular]] research (and current consensus) places the robins as a very early offshoot of the [[Passerida]], or \"advanced\" songbirds, within the [[songbird]] lineage.<ref>{{cite journal |author1=Barker, F. Keith |author2=Cibois, Alice |author3=Schikler, Peter A. |author4=Feinstein, Julie |author5=Cracraft, Joel |year=2004 |title=Phylogeny and diversification of the largest avian radiation. |journal=[[Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences]] |volume=101 |issue=30 |pages=11040\u201345 |doi=10.1073/pnas.0401892101 |url=http://www.pnas.org/cgi/reprint/0401892101v1.pdf |format=pdf |accessdate=14 August 2008 |pmid=15263073 |pmc=503738 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080309053127/http://www.pnas.org/cgi/reprint/0401892101v1.pdf |archive-date=2008-03-09 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nNo [[subspecies]] are recognised,<ref name=Higgins666>Higgins ''et al.'', p. 666.</ref> and the degree of geographic variation is unclear. Adult male birds which breed on the mainland have been reported as having lighter upperparts and underparts than their Tasmanian relatives, and females are said to be browner, but these differences may also result from worn plumage. Furthermore, migration across the [[Bass Strait]] by some birds obfuscates the issue. Mainland and Tasmanian birds are the same size.<ref name=Higgins681>Higgins ''et al.'', p. 681.</ref> Ornithologists, [[Richard Schodde]] and Ian Mason, argued that the poor quality of museum collections and partially migratory habits meant that discrete subspecies could not be distinguished on the basis of the observed variation within the species.<ref name=schodde99>{{cite book|author1=Schodde, Richard |author-link=Richard Schodde |author2=Mason, Ian J.|year=1999|title=The Directory of Australian Birds: Passerines. A taxonomic and zoogeographic atlas of the biodiversity of birds of Australia and its territories|pages=273\u201375|publisher=CSIRO Publishing|location=Melbourne|isbn=0-643-06456-7}}</ref>\n\n''Flame-breasted robin'' was the [[common name]] formerly used for the species, and it was gradually abbreviated to ''flame robin''.<ref name=Boles88>Boles, p. 68.</ref> Other names recorded include ''bank robin'', ''redhead'', and (inaccurately) ''robin redbreast''.<ref name=Higgins666/>  \"Flame Robin\" is the preferred vernacular name of the [[International Ornithological Congress]].<ref>Frank Gill and Minturn Wright, ''Birds of the World: Recommended English Names'', Princeton University Press, 2006.</ref>\n\n==Description==\n[[File:Flame robin.jpg|thumb|right|The flame robin, ''Petroica phoenicea'', 1931 by [[E. E. Gostelow]].]]\nThe largest of the red robins, the flame robin is {{convert|12|\u2013|14|cm|in|abbr=on}} long. It has a more slender build than other members of the genus ''Petroica'', with relatively long wings and neck and small head.<ref name=Higgins666/> The male is easily distinguished by the bright orange-red [[Feather|plumage]] of the throat, breast, and abdomen. The crown, [[nape]], ear [[covert feather|coverts]], hindneck, and sides of neck are dark grey, and [[Bird anatomy#Head|lores]] and chin are a grey-black. The grey feathers of the sides of the [[crown (anatomy)|crown]] may be suffused with dull orange.<ref name=Higgins678>Higgins ''et al.'', p. 678.</ref> The rest of the upperparts, comprising the wings, back and tail, are dark grey. There is a small, white frontal spot above the bill, and the wing bar and outer tail shafts are white. The feathers of the posterior belly, flanks, and vent are white with grey-black bases. The female is plainly coloured\u2014pale brown overall, and a lighter [[buff (colour)|buff]] underneath. The posterior belly, flanks, and vent are off-white. As in the male, feathers on the side of the crown may be suffused with a dull orange, and this may also occur with breast feathers. There are small, off-white marks on the wings and above the bill.<ref name=Higgins679>Higgins ''et al.'', p. 679.</ref> The bill, legs, feet, and claws are black, and the eyes dark brown.<ref name=Higgins680>Higgins ''et al.'', p. 680.</ref> A flame robin with an all lemon-yellow breast and otherwise female plumage was observed in a small flock of flame robins near [[Swansea, Tasmania|Swansea]], in eastern Tasmania, in September 1950.<ref>{{cite journal|title=Xanthochroism in scarlet robin, ''Petroica multicolor'', and flame robin, ''P. phoenicea''|author=Wall, L. E.|journal=Emu| volume=66|issue=3|page=297|year=1967|doi=10.1071/mu966295d}}</ref>\n\nNestlings have dark grey or brown [[down feather|down]],<ref name=Higgins679/> cream to grey bills, cream [[gape]]s and orange throats.<ref name=Higgins680/> The plumage of juvenile birds in their first moult resembles that of the adult female, but the head and upperparts are streaked and slightly darker.<ref name=Higgins679/> Soon after [[fledge|fledging]], juveniles moult into their first immature plumage, and more closely resemble the adult female. The breasts of male juveniles may have some orange feathers. Birds in their second year moult into a second immature phase, some males of which may resemble adult males, while others retain a more immature brown plumage.<ref name=Higgins680/> Determining the age and sex of birds in brown plumage can be very difficult.<ref name=\"Higgins681\"/> Information on exact timing of moulting is lacking, but the replacement of [[primary feather]]s takes place over the summer months between December and February.<ref name=Higgins680/>\n\nThe colour alone is not a reliable guide to determine the species, as some [[scarlet robin]]s (''P.&nbsp;boodang'') take on an orange hue, but while male scarlet and [[red-capped robin]]s (''P.&nbsp;goodenovii'') have red breasts and black throats, the flame robin's breast plumage extends right up to the base of the bill. It is also a little slimmer and has a smaller head than the scarlet robin, and is clearly larger than the red-capped robin.<ref name = \"Simpsday\">{{cite book |author1=Simpson, Ken |author2=Day, Nicolas |author3=Trusler, Peter | title = Field Guide to the Birds of Australia | publisher = Viking O'Neil | year = 1993 | location = Ringwood, Victoria | page = 174 | isbn = 0-670-90478-3}}</ref> Females of the respective species are harder to tell apart. Those of red-capped, [[rose robin|rose]], and [[pink robin]]s are all smaller, with wing lengths less than {{convert|7|cm|in|abbr=on}}, smaller than the smallest flame robin. The female scarlet robin has a more pronounced red flush to the breast and the spot on the forehead above the bill is more prominent and white rather than off-white.<ref name=Higgins681/>\n\nThe flame robin's [[Bird vocalization|calls]] are grouped into louder and quieter calls; the former can be heard from {{convert|150|m|ft|abbr=on}} away, while the latter, which are often briefer, from {{convert|30|m|ft|abbr=on}}. Loud songs make up almost 90% of calls in spring, summer, and autumn, but less than 50% of calls from May to July. Males sing rarely during this time, although they do so to defend their territories.<ref name=Higgins675>Higgins ''et al.'', p. 675.</ref> Their song is more varied and complex than that of the scarlet robin,<ref name=\"North03\">{{cite book|last = North|first = Alfred J.|title = Nests and eggs of birds found breeding in Australia and Tasmania|url = https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/31727#198|accessdate = 19 August 2010|edition = 2nd|year = 1903|publisher = Australian Museum/F.W. White|location = Sydney|pages = 165\u201367|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20120923190135/http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/31727#198|archive-date = 2012-09-23|url-status = live}}</ref> and has been described as the most musical of the red robins. A series of descending notes in groups of three, the musical song has been likened to the phrases, \"''you-may-come, if-you-will, to-the-sea''\"<ref>Slater, Peter (1974) ''A Field Guide to Australian Birds: Passerines''. Adelaide: Rigby. ISBN 085179813-6</ref> or \"''you-are-not a-pretty-little-bird like-me''\". Both males and females sing this song, often perched from a vantage point, such as a stump or fence.<ref name=North03/> This loud song is used to attract the attention of a potential mate, and to announce the bringing of food to its mate or young. The softer call has been described as a ''tlip'', ''terp'' or ''pip'', and is used as a contact call in the vicinity of the nest.<ref name=Higgins676>Higgins ''et al.'', p. 676.</ref><!-- cites both previous sentences --> The female makes a hissing sound, if approached while on the nest,<ref name=North03/> and the male has been recorded making a wheezing call when displaying around the nest.<ref name=\"robinson90\">{{cite journal|doi=10.1071/MU9900040|last=Robinson|first=Doug|year=1990|title=The Nesting Ecology of Sympatric Scarlet Robin Petroica multicolor and Flame Robin ''Petroica phoenicea'' Populations in Open Eucalypt Forest|journal=Emu|volume=90|issue=1|pages=40\u201352}}</ref>\n\n==Distribution and habitat==\nThe flame robin is found in temperate regions of southeastern Australia and all over Tasmania, although it is less common in the southwest and west. In [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]], it is more common in uplands than lower altitudes.<ref name=Higgins667>Higgins ''et al.'', p. 667.</ref> It ranges from the [[Adelaide Plains|Adelaide]] and Murray Plains around the mouth of the [[Murray River]] in southeastern South Australia, across Victoria, and into the [[South West Slopes]] and southern regions of New South Wales. Further north, it is found along the [[Great Dividing Range]] and its western slopes, with a few records from southeast Queensland.<ref name=Higgins668>Higgins ''et al.'', p. 668.</ref> Within its range, it is generally migratory, moving from alpine and subalpine regions to lowlands in winter, although the breeding and non-breeding ranges overlap. There is some evidence that male birds migrate several days before the females. It is unclear what proportion of Tasmanian birds cross [[Bass Strait]] to winter in Victoria.<ref name=Higgins669>Higgins ''et al.'', p. 669.</ref> Birds which remain in Tasmania move away from breeding areas, and are found in paddocks in loose flocks of up to fourteen birds. They have left these areas by August, and immature birds appear to disperse earlier.<ref>{{cite journal|\ndoi=10.1071/MU969235d|\ntitle=Composition of Flame Robin Flocks Wintering in Tasmania |author=Thomas, D. G.|journal=Emu| volume=69|issue= 4| pages=240\u201341| year=1969}}</ref> A [[field study]] in the outer Melbourne suburb of [[Langwarrin, Victoria|Langwarrin]] showed that climate did not influence peak abundance of Flame Robins there.<ref>{{cite journal|\ndoi = 10.1071/MU09023|\ntitle = Altered timing of avian movements in a peri-urban environment and its relationship to climate |author = Chambers, Lynda E.|journal = Emu| volume = 110|issue = 1| pages = 48\u201353| year = 2010}}</ref> The international organization [[BirdLife International]] has regraded it from ''[[Least Concern]]'' to ''[[Near Threatened]]'' in 2004, due to its population decline over the previous 25 years.<ref name=IUCN/> The Australian Government had classified it as ''Least Concern'', but noted evidence of decline at the edges of its non-breeding range;<ref name=\"Garnett00\">{{cite web|publisher = Department of the Environment, Water, Heritage and the Arts, Australian Government|url = http://www.environment.gov.au/biodiversity/threatened/publications/action/birds2000/pubs/flame-robin.pdf|title = Taxon summary: Flame Robin|work = Environment Australia|year = 2000|author = Garnett, Stephen T.|accessdate = 9 August 2010|url-status = dead|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20110328003052/http://environment.gov.au/biodiversity/threatened/publications/action/birds2000/pubs/flame-robin.pdf|archivedate = 28 March 2011}}</ref> it has become rare in South Australia,<ref>{{cite journal|author1=Paton, D. C. |author2=Carpenter, G. |author3=Sinclair, R. G. |year=1994|title=A second bird atlas of the Adelaide region. Part 1: changes in the distribution of birds: 1974&ndash;75 vs 1984&ndash;85|journal= South Australian Ornithologist|volume= 31|pages=151\u201393}}</ref> and uncommon in the lowlands of Victoria.<ref name=Garnett00/> Flame robins are not rare in the Victorian high country. They are frequently encountered at high elevations on the Great Dividing Range, especially in sparser snow gum woodland and similar habitat, and during the summer breeding season are one of the most reliably observed species around the summit of Mount Macedon, NW of Melbourne.\n\nIn spring and summer, the flame robin is more often found in wet eucalypt forest in hilly or mountainous areas, particularly the tops and slopes, to an elevation of {{convert|1800|m|ft|abbr=on}}. It generally prefers areas with more clearings and less [[understory]]. In particular, it prefers tall forests dominated by such trees as snow gum (''[[Eucalyptus pauciflora]]''), mountain ash ( ''[[Eucalyptus regnans|E.&nbsp;regnans]]''), alpine ash (''[[Eucalyptus delegatensis|E.&nbsp;delegatensis]]''), manna gum (''[[Eucalyptus viminalis|E.&nbsp;viminalis]]''), messmate stringybark (''[[Eucalyptus obliqua|E.&nbsp;obliqua]]''), black gum (''[[Eucalyptus aggregata|E.&nbsp;aggregata]]''), white mountain gum (''[[Eucalyptus dalrympleana|E.&nbsp;dalrympleana]]''), brown barrel (''[[Eucalyptus fastigata|E.&nbsp;fastigata]]''), narrow-leaved peppermint (''[[Eucalyptus radiata|E.&nbsp;radiata]]''), and black peppermint (''[[Eucalyptus amygdalina|E.&nbsp;amygdalina]]''). It is occasionally encountered in [[temperate rainforest]]. In the autumn and winter, birds move to more open areas, such as grasslands and open woodlands, particularly those containing river red gum (''[[Eucalyptus camaldulensis|E.&nbsp;camaldulensis]]''), Blakely's red gum (''[[Eucalyptus blakelyi|E.&nbsp;blakelyi]]''), yellow box (''[[Eucalyptus melliodora|E.&nbsp;melliodora]]''), grey box (''[[Eucalyptus microcarpa|E.&nbsp;microcarpa]]''), and mugga ironbark  (''[[Eucalyptus sideroxylon|E.&nbsp;sideroxylon]]''), at lower altitude.<ref name=Higgins667/><!-- cites para -->\n\nFlame robins often become more abundant in areas recently burnt by [[bushfire]]s, but move away once the undergrowth regrows.<ref name=Higgins667/> They may also move into logged or cleared areas in forests.<ref name=Higgins668/> However, a field study in the Boola Boola State Forest in central [[Gippsland]] revealed they are not found in areas where the regrowth after logging is dense.<ref name=\"Loyn80\">{{cite journal|last=Loyn|first=Richard H.|year=1980|title=Bird populations in a mixed Eucalypt forest used for production of wood in Gippsland, Victoria|journal=Emu|volume=80|issue=3|pages=146\u201356|doi=10.1071/mu9800145}}</ref>\n\n==Behaviour==\n[[File:Petroica phoenicea 2 - Goat's Beach.jpg|thumb]]\nThe flame robin mostly breeds in and around the [[Great Dividing Range]], the Tasmanian highlands and islands in Bass Strait.<ref name=Ber03/> With the coming of cooler autumn weather, most birds disperse to lower and warmer areas, some travelling as far as eastern [[South Australia]], southern Queensland, or (in the case of some Tasmanian birds) across Bass Strait to Victoria. Birds breeding in the warmer climates north of the [[Blue Mountains (New South Wales)|Blue Mountains]] in [[New South Wales]] tend to retain their highland territories all year round. Outside the breeding season, birds may congregate in loose flocks, but they are most usually encountered throughout the year singly or in pairs, the latter more commonly in breeding season.<ref name=Higgins672>Higgins ''et al.'', p. 672.</ref>\n\nWhen perched or between bouts of foraging on the ground, the flame robin holds itself in a relatively upright pose, with its body angled at 45\u00b0 or less from the vertical, and its wings held low below its tail. It impresses as nervous and twitchy, flicking its wings alternately when still. The flame robin's flight is fast, with a markedly undulating character.<ref name=Higgins667/><!-- cites previous three sentences-->\n\nThe flame robin is [[territory (animal)|territorial]], defending its territory against other members of its species and also scarlet robins where they co-occur. In [[Nimmitabel, New South Wales|Nimmitabel]] in southern New South Wales, migratory flame robins invaded and eked out their territories from amid existing scarlet robin territories. Once settled, however, no species dominated over the other and stable boundaries emerged.<ref name=\"robinson89\">{{cite journal|doi = 10.1071/MU9890093|last = Robinson|first = Doug|year = 1989|title = Interspecific Aggression and Territorial Behavior Between Scarlet Robin ''Petroica multicolor'' and Flame Robin ''P. phoenicea''|journal = Emu|volume = 89|issue = 2|pages = 93\u2013101}}</ref> The flame robin deploys a number of [[Agonistic behaviour|agonistic]] displays, including a breast-puffing display where it puffs its breast feathers and a white spot display where it puffs its feathers to accentuate its frontal white crown, white wing markings or white outer tail feathers. They may also fly at intruders or sing to defend their territory.<ref name=\"robinson89\"/>\n\n===Courtship and breeding===\n[[File:Flame Robin girraween.ogg|thumbtime=9|thumb|Male and Female, Girraween National Park, southern Queensland]]\nSeveral courtship behaviours have been recorded. Males have been recorded feeding females.<ref name=Higgins674>Higgins ''et al.'', p. 674.</ref><!-- cites previous two sentences --> A male flame robin either lands next to and moves a female off her perch, or flies in front of her. Courting males also run to and fro in front of a female, in a crouch with wings and head lowered and hiding their breast feathers. In both displays, the male proceeds to chase the female. Pairs are generally [[Monogamous pairing in animals|monogamous]], and remain together unless one bird perishes, although \"divorces\" have been recorded.<ref name=\"robinson90ibis\">{{cite journal|last=Robinson|first=Doug|year=1990|title=The social organization of the Scarlet Robin ''Petroica multicolor'' and Flame Robin ''P. phoenicea'' in southeastern Australia: a comparison between sedentary and migratory flycatchers|journal=Ibis|volume=132|issue=1|pages=78\u201394|doi=10.1111/j.1474-919X.1990.tb01018.x}}</ref><!-- cites previous four sentences -->\n\nThe breeding season is August to January with one or two broods raised.<ref name=Ber03/> The male proposes suitable nest sites to the female by hopping around the area. Unlike other robins, the female sometimes initiates the site selection. A pair spends anywhere from one to five days looking before finding a suitable site. The female constructs the nest alone.<ref name=\"robinson90\"/> Eucalypts are generally chosen, but birds have been recorded nesting in ''[[Pinus radiata]]'' on [[Mount Wellington (Tasmania)|Mount Wellington]] in Tasmania. The flame robin is more versatile in its selection of nesting sites than other robins, and has even been recorded nesting in sheds.<ref name=\"chisholm60\">{{cite journal|last=Chisholm|first=Alec H.|year=1960|title=Remarks on robins|journal=Emu|volume=60|issue=4|pages=221\u201335|doi=10.1071/MU960221}}</ref><!-- cites previous two sentences -->\n\nThe nest is a neat deep cup made of soft dry grass, moss and bark. [[Spider web]]s, feathers and fur are used for binding/filling, generally in a tree fork or crevice, or cliff or riverbank ledge, typically within a few metres of the ground. The clutch generally numbers three or four dull white eggs, which are laid on consecutive days.<ref name=Higgins677>Higgins ''et al.'', p. 677.</ref> They are tinted bluish, greyish or brownish and splotched with dark grey-brown, and measure 18&nbsp;mm x 14&nbsp;mm.<ref name=Ber03>{{cite book  | last = Beruldsen  | first = Gordon  | title = Australian Birds: Their Nests and Eggs  | publisher = self  | year = 2003  | location = Kenmore Hills, Queensland  | page = 341 | isbn = 0-646-42798-9}}</ref> A field study in open eucalypt forest at Nimmitabel found that flame robins and scarlet robins chose different sites to breed, the former in tree hollows and bark crevices, most commonly of ''Eucalyptus viminalis'' around {{convert|4|m|ft|abbr=on}} off the ground, and the latter more commonly in forks or on branches of ''E.&nbsp;pauciflora''  around {{convert|7|m|ft|abbr=on}} above the ground. Flame robins, which were migratory at the site, were more successful in raising young, but the success rate of scarlet robins in the area appeared to be poor compared with other sites.<ref name=\"robinson90\"/>\n\n[[Avian incubation|Incubation]] has been recorded as averaging around 17 days.<ref name=\"robinson90\"/> Like all passerines, the chicks are [[altricial]]; they are born blind and naked, and start to develop [[down feather|down]] on their heads on day two. Their eyes open around day six, and they begin developing their primary flight feathers around day nine or ten.<ref name=Higgins678/> For the first three days after hatching, the mother feeds the nestlings alone, with food brought to her by the father. The father feeds them directly from the fourth day onwards, with the mother brooding them afterwards until day seven.<ref>{{cite journal|doi=10.1071/MU966347|author=Cooper, R. P.|year=1967|title=Unusual nesting sites of the Flame Robin|journal=Emu|volume=66|issue=4|pages=347\u201351}}</ref> Flies, butterflies, moths, caterpillars and beetles predominate in the food fed to the young birds. Flame robins fed a higher proportion of flying insects to their young at Nimmitabel than did scarlet robins, which may have been due to their later start to breeding.<ref name=\"robinson90\"/> Both parents participate in removing [[Fecal sac|faecal sacs]] from the nest.<ref name=cooper70>{{cite journal|title=The Flame robin on Wilson's Promontory| author=Cooper, R. P.|journal=Australian Bird Watcher |volume=3 |pages=227&ndash;35|year=1970}}</ref> Parents have been observed feeding young up to five weeks after leaving the nest.<ref name=Higgins678/>\n\nThe [[fan-tailed cuckoo]] (''Cacomantis flabelliformis'') and [[pallid cuckoo]] (''C.&nbsp;pallidus'') have been recorded as [[brood parasite]]s of the flame robin;<ref name=Higgins678/> female cuckoos lay their eggs in robin nests, which are then raised by the robins as their own. One fan-tailed cuckoo was recorded ejecting baby robins before being raised by its foster parents. Other nest predators recorded include the [[grey shrikethrush]] (''Colluricincla harmonica''), [[pied currawong]] (''Strepera graculina''), and [[eastern brown snake]] (''Pseudonaja textilis'').<ref name=\"robinson90\"/><!-- cites both previous -->\n\n===Feeding===\nLike all [[Australasian robins]], the flame robin is a perch and pounce hunter, mainly eating [[insect]]s, and often returning to a favourite low perch several times to stand erect and motionless, scanning the leaf-litter for more prey. They are typically seen in pairs (during the spring and summer breeding season) or in loose companies in more open country in winter, when they more commonly feed on the ground.<ref name=Higgins671>Higgins ''et al.'', p. 671.</ref><!-- cites para --> A field study in the Southern Tablelands of New South Wales found no significant difference in foraging behaviour between male and female flame robins.<ref>{{cite journal|doi = 10.1071/MU9904|title = The Foraging Ecology of Birds of Eucalypt Forest and Woodland. I. Differences Between Males and Females|author1=Recher, Harry F. |author2=Holmes, Richard T. |journal = Emu|volume = 100|issue = 3|pages = 205\u201315|year = 2000}}</ref> Birds have been recorded foraging for insects in furrows in freshly ploughed fields.<ref name=North03/> In [[Deniliquin]], a flame robin was observed holding one foot forward and pattering the ground repeatedly to disturb ground-dwelling insects, and then watching and snapping up any which emerged; this behaviour is otherwise seen in [[wader]]s.<ref>{{cite journal|doi=10.1071/MU954278b|title=Flame Robin's 'Foot Pattering' Feeding Habit|author=Hobbs, John N. |journal=Emu|volume=54|issue=4|pages=278\u201379|year=1954}}</ref>\n\nCompared with the scarlet robin, the flame robin eats a higher proportion of flying insects. Biologist Doug Robinson has proposed that scarcity of flying insects in winter is a reason why the flame robin migrates.<ref name=RobCorella>{{cite journal|author=Robinson, Doug|year=1992|title=Why do Flame Robins ''Petroica phoenicea'' migrate? A comparison between the social and feeding ecologies of the Flame Robin and Scarlet Robin ''P. multicolor''. |journal=Corella|volume=16|pages=1\u201314}}</ref> They have been seen in  [[Mixed-species feeding flock|mixed-species flocks]] with other small insectivorous passerines, such as scarlet robins, [[hooded robin]]s (''Melanodryas cucullata''), [[white-fronted chat]]s (''Epthianura albifrons''), and [[Australasian pipit]]s (''Anthus novaeseelandiae'').<ref name=Higgins666/>\n\nAmong the types of insects consumed are many families of [[beetle]]s, [[wasp]]s and ants, [[diptera|flies]] (families [[Tabanidae]] and [[Asilidae]]), [[hemiptera|bugs]], and caterpillars. Other invertebrates eaten include [[spider]]s, [[millipede]]s and [[Oligochaeta|earthworms]].<ref name=Higgins672/> The flame robin consumes small prey items whole, and bashes larger victims against a hard surface repeatedly to break up before eating. The latter group constitute only 0.5% of prey over time\u2014seasonally varying from a peak of 1.8% in autumn to a low of 0.2% of prey caught in winter.<ref name=RobCorella/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n===Cited texts===\n*{{cite book |title=The Robins and Flycatchers of Australia |last=Boles |first=Walter E.|year=1988 |publisher=Angus & Robertson |location=Sydney |isbn=0-207-15400-7}}\n* {{cite book |title=[[Handbook of Australian, New Zealand and Antarctic Birds]]. Volume 6: Pardalotes to Shrike-thrushes|editor=Higgins, Peter J.|editor2=Peter, Jeffrey M |year=2002 |publisher=Oxford University Press |location=Melbourne |isbn=0-19-553762-9}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons|Petroica phoenicea}}\n{{Wikispecies|Petroica phoenicea}}\n* [http://ibc.lynxeds.com/species/flame-robin-petroica-phoenicea Flame robin videos, photos & sounds] on the Internet Bird Collection\n\n{{Petroicidae}}\n{{portalbar|Birds}}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q931191}}\n{{featured article}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:robin, flame}}\n[[Category:Petroica|flame robin]]\n[[Category:Birds of New South Wales]]\n[[Category:Birds of South Australia]]\n[[Category:Birds of Tasmania]]\n[[Category:Birds of Victoria (Australia)]]\n[[Category:Birds described in 1830|flame robin]]\n[[Category:Articles containing video clips]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|A small passerine bird native to southeastern Australia}}\n{{speciesbox\n | name                = Flame robin\n | status              = NT\n | status_system       = IUCN3.1\n | status_ref          = <ref name=IUCN>{{cite iucn|url=https://www.iucnredlist.org/details/22704819/0 |title=''Petroica phoenicea'' |author=BirdLife International |author-link=BirdLife International |year=2012 |access-date=26 November 2013|ref=harv}}</ref>\n | image               = Flame Robin, Eaglehawk Neck..jpg\n | genus               = Petroica\n | species             = phoenicea\n | authority           = [[John Gould|Gould]], 1837\n | range_map           = Flamerobin dist gnangarra.png\n}}\n\nThe '''flame robin''' (''Petroica phoenicea'') is a small [[passerine]] bird native to [[Australia]]. It is a moderately common resident of the coolest parts of south-eastern Australia, including [[Tasmania]]. Like the other two red-breasted ''Petroica'' robins&mdash;the [[scarlet robin]] and the [[red-capped robin]]&mdash;it is often simply called the ''robin redbreast''. Like many brightly coloured robins of the [[Petroicidae]], it is [[Sexual dimorphism|sexually dimorphic]]. Measuring {{convert|12|\u2013|14|cm|in|abbr=on}} long, the flame robin has dark brown eyes and a small thin black bill. The male has a brilliant orange-red chest and throat, and a white patch on the forehead above the bill. Its upper parts are iron-grey with white bars, and its tail black with white tips. The female is a nondescript grey-brown. Its song has been described as the most musical of its genus.\n\nThe position of the flame robin and its Australian relatives on the passerine family tree is unclear; the Petroicidae are not closely related to either the [[European robin|European]] or [[American robin]]s, but appear to be an early offshoot of the [[Passerida]] group of [[songbird]]s. The flame robin is predominantly [[insectivore|insectivorous]], pouncing on prey from a perch in a tree, or foraging on the ground. A [[territory (animal)|territorial]] bird, the flame robin employs song and plumage displays to mark out and defend its territory. Classified by [[BirdLife International]] as ''[[Near Threatened]]'', the species has suffered a marked decline in the past 25 years.\n\n==Taxonomy==\nThe flame robin was first [[Species description|described]] by the French [[natural history|naturalist]]s, [[Jean Ren\u00e9 Constant Quoy]] and [[Joseph Paul Gaimard]], in 1830 as ''Muscicapa chrysoptera''.<ref>Quoy, Jean Ren\u00e9 Constant; Gaimard, Joseph Paul in Dumont-d'Urville, J. (1830). ''Voyage de d\u00e9couvertes de l'Astrolabe ex\u00e9cut\u00e9 par ordre du Roi, pendant les anne\u00e9s 1826\u20131827\u20131828\u20131829, sous le commandement de M.J. Dumont-d'Urville''. Zoologie. Paris: J. Tastu Vol. '''1'''</ref> The [[specific name (zoology)|specific epithet]], ''chrysoptera'', is derived from the [[Ancient Greek]] words ''chrysos'' 'golden', and ''pteron'' 'feather'.<ref name=Liddell1980>{{cite book | author = Liddell, Henry George | author-link = Henry Liddell | author2 = Scott, Robert | author2-link = Robert Scott (philologist) | year = 1980 | title = [[A Greek\u2013English Lexicon]] (Abridged Edition) | publisher = [[Oxford University Press]] | location = Oxford, United Kingdom | isbn = 0-19-910207-4 | pages = [https://archive.org/details/lexicon00lidd/page/615 615, 791] }}</ref>\n\n[[John Gould]] placed the flame robin in its current genus as ''Petroica phoenicea'' in his 1837 description, and it was this latter binomial name that has been used since that time. Given this, Quoy and Gaimard's name was declared a ''[[nomen oblitum]]''.<ref>{{cite web|title=Species ''Petroica (Littlera) phoenicea'' Gould, 1837|url=http://www.environment.gov.au/biodiversity/abrs/online-resources/fauna/afd/taxa/234a4598-0331-4881-aaa9-9f635d1890d9|accessdate=26 August 2010|author=((Department of the Environment, Water, Heritage and the Arts))|date=October 9, 2008|publisher=Australian Government|work=Australian Biological Resources Study: Australian Faunal Directory|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121012084338/http://www.environment.gov.au/biodiversity/abrs/online-resources/fauna/afd/taxa/234a4598-0331-4881-aaa9-9f635d1890d9|archivedate=12 October 2012}}</ref> The generic name is derived from the Ancient Greek words ''petros'' 'rock' and ''oikos'' 'home', from the birds' habit of sitting on rocks.<ref>Boles, p. 66.</ref> The [[specific name (zoology)|specific epithet]] is also derived from Ancient Greek, from the adjective ''phoinikes'' 'red'. It is one of five red- or pink-breasted species [[common name|colloquially]] known as \"red robins\", as distinct from the \"yellow robins\" of the genus ''[[Eopsaltria]]''. Although named after the [[European robin]], the flame robin is not closely related to either it or the [[American robin]].<ref name=\"Boles, p. xv\"/> The Australian robins were placed in the [[Old World flycatcher]] family [[Muscicapidae]],<ref name=\"Boles, p. xv\">Boles, p. xv.</ref> and the whistler family [[Pachycephalidae]],<ref name=Boles35>Boles, p. 35.</ref> before being [[Biological classification|classified]] in their own family [[Petroicidae]].<ref name=Boles35/><ref>Gill, F. and D. Donsker, eds. (2020). IOC World Bird List (v 10.1). Doi 10.14344/IOC.ML.10.1.  http://www.worldbirdnames.org/</ref> [[Charles Sibley|Sibley]] and [[Jon Edward Ahlquist|Ahlquist]]'s [[DNA-DNA hybridisation]] studies placed the robins in a [[Corvida]] [[parvorder]] comprising many tropical and Australian passerines, including [[Pardalotidae|pardalotes]], [[Maluridae|fairy-wrens]] and [[Meliphagidae|honeyeaters]], as well as crows.<ref name=\"SibAhl\">{{cite book|author1=Sibley, Charles G. |author2=Ahlquist, Jon E. |title=Phylogeny and Classification of Birds: A Study in Molecular Evolution |publisher=Yale University Press|location=New Haven, Connecticut|year=1990|pages=603, 610\u201327|isbn=0-300-04085-7}}</ref> However, subsequent [[molecular phylogenetics|molecular]] research (and current consensus) places the robins as a very early offshoot of the [[Passerida]], or \"advanced\" songbirds, within the [[songbird]] lineage.<ref>{{cite journal |author1=Barker, F. Keith |author2=Cibois, Alice |author3=Schikler, Peter A. |author4=Feinstein, Julie |author5=Cracraft, Joel |year=2004 |title=Phylogeny and diversification of the largest avian radiation. |journal=[[Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences]] |volume=101 |issue=30 |pages=11040\u201345 |doi=10.1073/pnas.0401892101 |url=http://www.pnas.org/cgi/reprint/0401892101v1.pdf |format=pdf |accessdate=14 August 2008 |pmid=15263073 |pmc=503738 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080309053127/http://www.pnas.org/cgi/reprint/0401892101v1.pdf |archive-date=2008-03-09 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nNo [[subspecies]] are recognised,<ref name=Higgins666>Higgins ''et al.'', p. 666.</ref> and the degree of geographic variation is unclear. Adult male birds which breed on the mainland have been reported as having lighter upperparts and underparts than their Tasmanian relatives, and females are said to be browner, but these differences may also result from worn plumage. Furthermore, migration across the [[Bass Strait]] by some birds obfuscates the issue. Mainland and Tasmanian birds are the same size.<ref name=Higgins681>Higgins ''et al.'', p. 681.</ref> Ornithologists, [[Richard Schodde]] and Ian Mason, argued that the poor quality of museum collections and partially migratory habits meant that discrete subspecies could not be distinguished on the basis of the observed variation within the species.<ref name=schodde99>{{cite book|author1=Schodde, Richard |author-link=Richard Schodde |author2=Mason, Ian J.|year=1999|title=The Directory of Australian Birds: Passerines. A taxonomic and zoogeographic atlas of the biodiversity of birds of Australia and its territories|pages=273\u201375|publisher=CSIRO Publishing|location=Melbourne|isbn=0-643-06456-7}}</ref>\n\n''Flame-breasted robin'' was the [[common name]] formerly used for the species, and it was gradually abbreviated to ''flame robin''.<ref name=Boles88>Boles, p. 68.</ref> Other names recorded include ''bank robin'', ''redhead'', and (inaccurately) ''robin redbreast''.<ref name=Higgins666/>  \"Flame Robin\" is the preferred vernacular name of the [[International Ornithological Congress]].<ref>Frank Gill and Minturn Wright, ''Birds of the World: Recommended English Names'', Princeton University Press, 2006.</ref>\n\n==Description==\n[[File:Flame robin.jpg|thumb|right|The flame robin, ''Petroica phoenicea'', 1931 by [[E. E. Gostelow]].]]\nThe largest of the red robins, the flame robin is {{convert|12|\u2013|14|cm|in|abbr=on}} long. It has a more slender build than other members of the genus ''Petroica'', with relatively long wings and neck and small head.<ref name=Higgins666/> The male is easily distinguished by the bright orange-red [[Feather|plumage]] of the throat, breast, and abdomen. The crown, [[nape]], ear [[covert feather|coverts]], hindneck, and sides of neck are dark grey, and [[Bird anatomy#Head|lores]] and chin are a grey-black. The grey feathers of the sides of the [[crown (anatomy)|crown]] may be suffused with dull orange.<ref name=Higgins678>Higgins ''et al.'', p. 678.</ref> The rest of the upperparts, comprising the wings, back and tail, are dark grey. There is a small, white frontal spot above the bill, and the wing bar and outer tail shafts are white. The feathers of the posterior belly, flanks, and vent are white with grey-black bases. The female is plainly coloured\u2014pale brown overall, and a lighter [[buff (colour)|buff]] underneath. The posterior belly, flanks, and vent are off-white. As in the male, feathers on the side of the crown may be suffused with a dull orange, and this may also occur with breast feathers. There are small, off-white marks on the wings and above the bill.<ref name=Higgins679>Higgins ''et al.'', p. 679.</ref> The bill, legs, feet, and claws are black, and the eyes dark brown.<ref name=Higgins680>Higgins ''et al.'', p. 680.</ref> A flame robin with an all lemon-yellow breast and otherwise female plumage was observed in a small flock of flame robins near [[Swansea, Tasmania|Swansea]], in eastern Tasmania, in September 1950.<ref>{{cite journal|title=Xanthochroism in scarlet robin, ''Petroica multicolor'', and flame robin, ''P. phoenicea''|author=Wall, L. E.|journal=Emu| volume=66|issue=3|page=297|year=1967|doi=10.1071/mu966295d}}</ref>\n\nNestlings have dark grey or brown [[down feather|down]],<ref name=Higgins679/> cream to grey bills, cream [[gape]]s and orange throats.<ref name=Higgins680/> The plumage of juvenile birds in their first moult resembles that of the adult female, but the head and upperparts are streaked and slightly darker.<ref name=Higgins679/> Soon after [[fledge|fledging]], juveniles moult into their first immature plumage, and more closely resemble the adult female. The breasts of male juveniles may have some orange feathers. Birds in their second year moult into a second immature phase, some males of which may resemble adult males, while others retain a more immature brown plumage.<ref name=Higgins680/> Determining the age and sex of birds in brown plumage can be very difficult.<ref name=\"Higgins681\"/> Information on exact timing of moulting is lacking, but the replacement of [[primary feather]]s takes place over the summer months between December and February.<ref name=Higgins680/>\n\nThe colour alone is not a reliable guide to determine the species, as some [[scarlet robin]]s (''P.&nbsp;boodang'') take on an orange hue, but while male scarlet and [[red-capped robin]]s (''P.&nbsp;goodenovii'') have red breasts and black throats, the flame robin's breast plumage extends right up to the base of the bill. It is also a little slimmer and has a smaller head than the scarlet robin, and is clearly larger than the red-capped robin.<ref name = \"Simpsday\">{{cite book |author1=Simpson, Ken |author2=Day, Nicolas |author3=Trusler, Peter | title = Field Guide to the Birds of Australia | publisher = Viking O'Neil | year = 1993 | location = Ringwood, Victoria | page = 174 | isbn = 0-670-90478-3}}</ref> Females of the respective species are harder to tell apart. Those of red-capped, [[rose robin|rose]], and [[pink robin]]s are all smaller, with wing lengths less than {{convert|7|cm|in|abbr=on}}, smaller than the smallest flame robin. The female scarlet robin has a more pronounced red flush to the breast and the spot on the forehead above the bill is more prominent and white rather than off-white.<ref name=Higgins681/>\n\nThe flame robin's [[Bird vocalization|calls]] are grouped into louder and quieter calls; the former can be heard from {{convert|150|m|ft|abbr=on}} away, while the latter, which are often briefer, from {{convert|30|m|ft|abbr=on}}. Loud songs make up almost 90% of calls in spring, summer, and autumn, but less than 50% of calls from May to July. Males sing rarely during this time, although they do so to defend their territories.<ref name=Higgins675>Higgins ''et al.'', p. 675.</ref> Their song is more varied and complex than that of the scarlet robin,<ref name=\"North03\">{{cite book|last = North|first = Alfred J.|title = Nests and eggs of birds found breeding in Australia and Tasmania|url = https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/31727#198|accessdate = 19 August 2010|edition = 2nd|year = 1903|publisher = Australian Museum/F.W. White|location = Sydney|pages = 165\u201367|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20120923190135/http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/31727#198|archive-date = 2012-09-23|url-status = live}}</ref> and has been described as the most musical of the red robins. A series of descending notes in groups of three, the musical song has been likened to the phrases, \"''you-may-come, if-you-will, to-the-sea''\"<ref>Slater, Peter (1974) ''A Field Guide to Australian Birds: Passerines''. Adelaide: Rigby. ISBN 085179813-6</ref> or \"''you-are-not a-pretty-little-bird like-me''\". Both males and females sing this song, often perched from a vantage point, such as a stump or fence.<ref name=North03/> This loud song is used to attract the attention of a potential mate, and to announce the bringing of food to its mate or young. The softer call has been described as a ''tlip'', ''terp'' or ''pip'', and is used as a contact call in the vicinity of the nest.<ref name=Higgins676>Higgins ''et al.'', p. 676.</ref><!-- cites both previous sentences --> The female makes a hissing sound, if approached while on the nest,<ref name=North03/> and the male has been recorded making a wheezing call when displaying around the nest.<ref name=\"robinson90\">{{cite journal|doi=10.1071/MU9900040|last=Robinson|first=Doug|year=1990|title=The Nesting Ecology of Sympatric Scarlet Robin Petroica multicolor and Flame Robin ''Petroica phoenicea'' Populations in Open Eucalypt Forest|journal=Emu|volume=90|issue=1|pages=40\u201352}}</ref>\n\n==Distribution and habitat==\nThe flame robin is found in temperate regions of southeastern Australia and all over Tasmania, although it is less common in the southwest and west. In [[Victoria (Australia)|Victoria]], it is more common in uplands than lower altitudes.<ref name=Higgins667>Higgins ''et al.'', p. 667.</ref> It ranges from the [[Adelaide Plains|Adelaide]] and Murray Plains around the mouth of the [[Murray River]] in southeastern South Australia, across Victoria, and into the [[South West Slopes]] and southern regions of New South Wales. Further north, it is found along the [[Great Dividing Range]] and its western slopes, with a few records from southeast Queensland.<ref name=Higgins668>Higgins ''et al.'', p. 668.</ref> Within its range, it is generally migratory, moving from alpine and subalpine regions to lowlands in winter, although the breeding and non-breeding ranges overlap. There is some evidence that male birds migrate several days before the females. It is unclear what proportion of Tasmanian birds cross [[Bass Strait]] to winter in Victoria.<ref name=Higgins669>Higgins ''et al.'', p. 669.</ref> Birds which remain in Tasmania move away from breeding areas, and are found in paddocks in loose flocks of up to fourteen birds. They have left these areas by August, and immature birds appear to disperse earlier.<ref>{{cite journal|\ndoi=10.1071/MU969235d|\ntitle=Composition of Flame Robin Flocks Wintering in Tasmania |author=Thomas, D. G.|journal=Emu| volume=69|issue= 4| pages=240\u201341| year=1969}}</ref> A [[field study]] in the outer Melbourne suburb of [[Langwarrin, Victoria|Langwarrin]] showed that climate did not influence peak abundance of Flame Robins there.<ref>{{cite journal|\ndoi = 10.1071/MU09023|\ntitle = Altered timing of avian movements in a peri-urban environment and its relationship to climate |author = Chambers, Lynda E.|journal = Emu| volume = 110|issue = 1| pages = 48\u201353| year = 2010}}</ref> The international organization [[BirdLife International]] has regraded it from ''[[Least Concern]]'' to ''[[Near Threatened]]'' in 2004 due to its population decline over the previous 25 years.<ref name=IUCN/> The Australian Government had classified it as ''Least Concern'', but noted evidence of decline at the edges of its non-breeding range;<ref name=\"Garnett00\">{{cite web|publisher = Department of the Environment, Water, Heritage and the Arts, Australian Government|url = http://www.environment.gov.au/biodiversity/threatened/publications/action/birds2000/pubs/flame-robin.pdf|title = Taxon summary: Flame Robin|work = Environment Australia|year = 2000|author = Garnett, Stephen T.|accessdate = 9 August 2010|url-status = dead|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20110328003052/http://environment.gov.au/biodiversity/threatened/publications/action/birds2000/pubs/flame-robin.pdf|archivedate = 28 March 2011}}</ref> it has become rare in South Australia<ref>{{cite journal|author1=Paton, D. C. |author2=Carpenter, G. |author3=Sinclair, R. G. |year=1994|title=A second bird atlas of the Adelaide region. Part 1: changes in the distribution of birds: 1974&ndash;75 vs 1984&ndash;85|journal= South Australian Ornithologist|volume= 31|pages=151\u201393}}</ref> and Victoria.<ref name=Garnett00/> Flame robins are not rare in Victoria. They are frequently encountered at high elevations on the Great Dividing Range, especially in sparser snow gum woodland and similar habitat, and during the summer breeding season are one of the most reliably observed species around the summit of Mount Macedon, NW of Melbourne.\n\nIn spring and summer, the flame robin is more often found in wet eucalypt forest in hilly or mountainous areas, particularly the tops and slopes, to an elevation of {{convert|1800|m|ft|abbr=on}}. It generally prefers areas with more clearings and less [[understory]]. In particular it prefers tall forests dominated by such trees as snow gum (''[[Eucalyptus pauciflora]]''), mountain ash ( ''[[Eucalyptus regnans|E.&nbsp;regnans]]''), alpine ash (''[[Eucalyptus delegatensis|E.&nbsp;delegatensis]]''), manna gum (''[[Eucalyptus viminalis|E.&nbsp;viminalis]]''), messmate stringybark (''[[Eucalyptus obliqua|E.&nbsp;obliqua]]''), black gum (''[[Eucalyptus aggregata|E.&nbsp;aggregata]]''), white mountain gum (''[[Eucalyptus dalrympleana|E.&nbsp;dalrympleana]]''), brown barrel (''[[Eucalyptus fastigata|E.&nbsp;fastigata]]''), narrow-leaved peppermint (''[[Eucalyptus radiata|E.&nbsp;radiata]]''), and black peppermint (''[[Eucalyptus amygdalina|E.&nbsp;amygdalina]]''). It is occasionally encountered in [[temperate rainforest]]. In the autumn and winter, birds move to more open areas such as grasslands and open woodlands, such as those containing river red gum (''[[Eucalyptus camaldulensis|E.&nbsp;camaldulensis]]''), Blakely's red gum (''[[Eucalyptus blakelyi|E.&nbsp;blakelyi]]''), yellow box (''[[Eucalyptus melliodora|E.&nbsp;melliodora]]''), grey box (''[[Eucalyptus microcarpa|E.&nbsp;microcarpa]]''), and mugga ironbark  (''[[Eucalyptus sideroxylon|E.&nbsp;sideroxylon]]''), at lower altitude.<ref name=Higgins667/><!-- cites para -->\n\nFlame robins often become more abundant in areas recently burnt by [[bushfire]]s, but move away once the undergrowth regrows.<ref name=Higgins667/> They may also move into logged or cleared areas in forests.<ref name=Higgins668/> However, a field study in the Boola Boola State Forest in central [[Gippsland]] revealed they are not found in areas where the regrowth after logging is dense.<ref name=\"Loyn80\">{{cite journal|last=Loyn|first=Richard H.|year=1980|title=Bird populations in a mixed Eucalypt forest used for production of wood in Gippsland, Victoria|journal=Emu|volume=80|issue=3|pages=146\u201356|doi=10.1071/mu9800145}}</ref>\n\n==Behaviour==\n[[File:Petroica phoenicea 2 - Goat's Beach.jpg|thumb]]\nThe flame robin mostly breeds in and around the [[Great Dividing Range]], the Tasmanian highlands and islands in Bass Strait.<ref name=Ber03/> With the coming of cooler autumn weather, most birds disperse to lower and warmer areas, some travelling as far as eastern [[South Australia]], southern Queensland, or (in the case of some Tasmanian birds) across Bass Strait to Victoria. Birds breeding in the warmer climates north of the [[Blue Mountains (New South Wales)|Blue Mountains]] in [[New South Wales]] tend to retain their highland territories all year round. Outside the breeding season, birds may congregate in loose flocks, but they are most usually encountered throughout the year singly or in pairs, the latter more commonly in breeding season.<ref name=Higgins672>Higgins ''et al.'', p. 672.</ref>\n\nWhen perched or between bouts of foraging on the ground, the flame robin holds itself in a relatively upright pose, with its body angled at 45\u00b0 or less from the vertical, and its wings held low below its tail. It impresses as nervous and twitchy, flicking its wings alternately when still. The flame robin's flight is fast, with a markedly undulating character.<ref name=Higgins667/><!-- cites previous three sentences-->\n\nThe flame robin is [[territory (animal)|territorial]], defending its territory against other members of its species and also scarlet robins where they co-occur. In [[Nimmitabel, New South Wales|Nimmitabel]] in southern New South Wales, migratory flame robins invaded and eked out their territories from amid existing scarlet robin territories. Once settled, however, no species dominated over the other and stable boundaries emerged.<ref name=\"robinson89\">{{cite journal|doi = 10.1071/MU9890093|last = Robinson|first = Doug|year = 1989|title = Interspecific Aggression and Territorial Behavior Between Scarlet Robin ''Petroica multicolor'' and Flame Robin ''P. phoenicea''|journal = Emu|volume = 89|issue = 2|pages = 93\u2013101}}</ref> The flame robin deploys a number of [[Agonistic behaviour|agonistic]] displays, including a breast-puffing display where it puffs its breast feathers and a white spot display where it puffs its feathers to accentuate its frontal white crown, white wing markings or white outer tail feathers. They may also fly at intruders or sing to defend their territory.<ref name=\"robinson89\"/>\n\n===Courtship and breeding===\n[[File:Flame Robin girraween.ogg|thumbtime=9|thumb|Male and Female, Girraween National Park, southern Queensland]]\nSeveral courtship behaviours have been recorded. Males have been recorded feeding females.<ref name=Higgins674>Higgins ''et al.'', p. 674.</ref><!-- cites previous two sentences --> A male flame robin either lands next to and moves a female off her perch, or flies in front of her. Courting males also run to and fro in front of a female, in a crouch with wings and head lowered and hiding their breast feathers. In both displays, the male proceeds to chase the female. Pairs are generally [[Monogamous pairing in animals|monogamous]], and remain together unless one bird perishes, although \"divorces\" have been recorded.<ref name=\"robinson90ibis\">{{cite journal|last=Robinson|first=Doug|year=1990|title=The social organization of the Scarlet Robin ''Petroica multicolor'' and Flame Robin ''P. phoenicea'' in southeastern Australia: a comparison between sedentary and migratory flycatchers|journal=Ibis|volume=132|issue=1|pages=78\u201394|doi=10.1111/j.1474-919X.1990.tb01018.x}}</ref><!-- cites previous four sentences -->\n\nThe breeding season is August to January with one or two broods raised.<ref name=Ber03/> The male proposes suitable nest sites to the female by hopping around the area. Unlike other robins, the female sometimes initiates the site selection. A pair spends anywhere from one to five days looking before finding a suitable site. The female constructs the nest alone.<ref name=\"robinson90\"/> Eucalypts are generally chosen, but birds have been recorded nesting in ''[[Pinus radiata]]'' on [[Mount Wellington (Tasmania)|Mount Wellington]] in Tasmania. The flame robin is more versatile in its selection of nesting sites than other robins, and has even been recorded nesting in sheds.<ref name=\"chisholm60\">{{cite journal|last=Chisholm|first=Alec H.|year=1960|title=Remarks on robins|journal=Emu|volume=60|issue=4|pages=221\u201335|doi=10.1071/MU960221}}</ref><!-- cites previous two sentences -->\n\nThe nest is a neat deep cup made of soft dry grass, moss and bark. [[Spider web]]s, feathers and fur are used for binding/filling, generally in a tree fork or crevice, or cliff or riverbank ledge, typically within a few metres of the ground. The clutch generally numbers three or four dull white eggs, which are laid on consecutive days.<ref name=Higgins677>Higgins ''et al.'', p. 677.</ref> They are tinted bluish, greyish or brownish and splotched with dark grey-brown, and measure 18&nbsp;mm x 14&nbsp;mm.<ref name=Ber03>{{cite book  | last = Beruldsen  | first = Gordon  | title = Australian Birds: Their Nests and Eggs  | publisher = self  | year = 2003  | location = Kenmore Hills, Queensland  | page = 341 | isbn = 0-646-42798-9}}</ref> A field study in open eucalypt forest at Nimmitabel found that flame robins and scarlet robins chose different sites to breed, the former in tree hollows and bark crevices, most commonly of ''Eucalyptus viminalis'' around {{convert|4|m|ft|abbr=on}} off the ground, and the latter more commonly in forks or on branches of ''E.&nbsp;pauciflora''  around {{convert|7|m|ft|abbr=on}} above the ground. Flame robins, which were migratory at the site, were more successful in raising young, but the success rate of scarlet robins in the area appeared to be poor compared with other sites.<ref name=\"robinson90\"/>\n\n[[Avian incubation|Incubation]] has been recorded as averaging around 17 days.<ref name=\"robinson90\"/> Like all passerines, the chicks are [[altricial]]; they are born blind and naked, and start to develop [[down feather|down]] on their heads on day two. Their eyes open around day six, and they begin developing their primary flight feathers around day nine or ten.<ref name=Higgins678/> For the first three days after hatching, the mother feeds the nestlings alone, with food brought to her by the father. The father feeds them directly from the fourth day onwards, with the mother brooding them afterwards until day seven.<ref>{{cite journal|doi=10.1071/MU966347|author=Cooper, R. P.|year=1967|title=Unusual nesting sites of the Flame Robin|journal=Emu|volume=66|issue=4|pages=347\u201351}}</ref> Flies, butterflies, moths, caterpillars and beetles predominate in the food fed to the young birds. Flame robins fed a higher proportion of flying insects to their young at Nimmitabel than did scarlet robins, which may have been due to their later start to breeding.<ref name=\"robinson90\"/> Both parents participate in removing [[Fecal sac|faecal sacs]] from the nest.<ref name=cooper70>{{cite journal|title=The Flame robin on Wilson's Promontory| author=Cooper, R. P.|journal=Australian Bird Watcher |volume=3 |pages=227&ndash;35|year=1970}}</ref> Parents have been observed feeding young up to five weeks after leaving the nest.<ref name=Higgins678/>\n\nThe [[fan-tailed cuckoo]] (''Cacomantis flabelliformis'') and [[pallid cuckoo]] (''C.&nbsp;pallidus'') have been recorded as [[brood parasite]]s of the flame robin;<ref name=Higgins678/> female cuckoos lay their eggs in robin nests, which are then raised by the robins as their own. One fan-tailed cuckoo was recorded ejecting baby robins before being raised by its foster parents. Other nest predators recorded include the [[grey shrikethrush]] (''Colluricincla harmonica''), [[pied currawong]] (''Strepera graculina''), and [[eastern brown snake]] (''Pseudonaja textilis'').<ref name=\"robinson90\"/><!-- cites both previous -->\n\n===Feeding===\nLike all [[Australasian robins]], the flame robin is a perch and pounce hunter, mainly eating [[insect]]s, and often returning to a favourite low perch several times to stand erect and motionless, scanning the leaf-litter for more prey. They are typically seen in pairs (during the spring and summer breeding season) or in loose companies in more open country in winter, when they more commonly feed on the ground.<ref name=Higgins671>Higgins ''et al.'', p. 671.</ref><!-- cites para --> A field study in the Southern Tablelands of New South Wales found no significant difference in foraging behaviour between male and female flame robins.<ref>{{cite journal|doi = 10.1071/MU9904|title = The Foraging Ecology of Birds of Eucalypt Forest and Woodland. I. Differences Between Males and Females|author1=Recher, Harry F. |author2=Holmes, Richard T. |journal = Emu|volume = 100|issue = 3|pages = 205\u201315|year = 2000}}</ref> Birds have been recorded foraging for insects in furrows in freshly ploughed fields.<ref name=North03/> In [[Deniliquin]], a flame robin was observed holding one foot forward and pattering the ground repeatedly to disturb ground-dwelling insects, and then watching and snapping up any which emerged; this behaviour is otherwise seen in [[wader]]s.<ref>{{cite journal|doi=10.1071/MU954278b|title=Flame Robin's 'Foot Pattering' Feeding Habit|author=Hobbs, John N. |journal=Emu|volume=54|issue=4|pages=278\u201379|year=1954}}</ref>\n\nCompared with the scarlet robin, the flame robin eats a higher proportion of flying insects. Biologist Doug Robinson has proposed that scarcity of flying insects in winter is a reason why the flame robin migrates.<ref name=RobCorella>{{cite journal|author=Robinson, Doug|year=1992|title=Why do Flame Robins ''Petroica phoenicea'' migrate? A comparison between the social and feeding ecologies of the Flame Robin and Scarlet Robin ''P. multicolor''. |journal=Corella|volume=16|pages=1\u201314}}</ref> They have been seen in  [[Mixed-species feeding flock|mixed-species flocks]] with other small insectivorous passerines, such as scarlet robins, [[hooded robin]]s (''Melanodryas cucullata''), [[white-fronted chat]]s (''Epthianura albifrons''), and [[Australasian pipit]]s (''Anthus novaeseelandiae'').<ref name=Higgins666/>\n\nAmong the types of insects consumed are many families of [[beetle]]s, [[wasp]]s and ants, [[diptera|flies]] (families [[Tabanidae]] and [[Asilidae]]), [[hemiptera|bugs]], and caterpillars. Other invertebrates eaten include [[spider]]s, [[millipede]]s and [[Oligochaeta|earthworms]].<ref name=Higgins672/> The flame robin consumes small prey items whole, and bashes larger victims against a hard surface repeatedly to break up before eating. The latter group constitute only 0.5% of prey over time\u2014seasonally varying from a peak of 1.8% in autumn to a low of 0.2% of prey caught in winter.<ref name=RobCorella/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n===Cited texts===\n*{{cite book |title=The Robins and Flycatchers of Australia |last=Boles |first=Walter E.|year=1988 |publisher=Angus & Robertson |location=Sydney |isbn=0-207-15400-7}}\n* {{cite book |title=[[Handbook of Australian, New Zealand and Antarctic Birds]]. Volume 6: Pardalotes to Shrike-thrushes|editor=Higgins, Peter J.|editor2=Peter, Jeffrey M |year=2002 |publisher=Oxford University Press |location=Melbourne |isbn=0-19-553762-9}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons|Petroica phoenicea}}\n{{Wikispecies|Petroica phoenicea}}\n* [http://ibc.lynxeds.com/species/flame-robin-petroica-phoenicea Flame robin videos, photos & sounds] on the Internet Bird Collection\n\n{{Petroicidae}}\n{{portalbar|Birds}}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q931191}}\n{{featured article}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:robin, flame}}\n[[Category:Petroica|flame robin]]\n[[Category:Birds of New South Wales]]\n[[Category:Birds of South Australia]]\n[[Category:Birds of Tasmania]]\n[[Category:Birds of Victoria (Australia)]]\n[[Category:Birds described in 1830|flame robin]]\n[[Category:Articles containing video clips]]\n", "name_user": "Rogermccart", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eDistribution and habitat:ce", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flame_robin"}
{"title_page": "Godzilla vs. Kong", "text_new": "{{About|the upcoming 2020 film|the 1962 film|King Kong vs. Godzilla}}\n{{short description|2020 film directed by Adam Wingard}}\n{{Use American English|date=September 2019}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Godzilla vs. Kong\n| image          = File:Godzilla vs. Kong - licensing promotional poster.jpg\n| caption        = Official promotional poster\n| director       = [[Adam Wingard]]\n| producer       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Mary Parent]]\n* Alex Garcia\n* Eric McLeod\n* Brian Rogers\n}}\n| screenplay     = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Terry Rossio]] <!-- DO NOT ADD MICHAEL DOUGHERTY AND ZACH SHIELDS! Their contributions were only minor, not enough to merit them screenwriting credit. As of this moment, Warner Bros has named Rossio as the sole screenwriter. DO NOT ADD any additional writing credits until the WGA reveals the final writing credit list. -->\n}}\n| story          =\n| based on       = {{based on|[[Godzilla]]|[[Toho]]}}<br>{{based on|[[King Kong]]|[[Edgar Wallace]] and [[Merian C. Cooper]]}}\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Alexander Skarsg\u00e5rd]]\n* [[Millie Bobby Brown]]\n* [[Rebecca Hall]]\n* [[Brian Tyree Henry]]\n* [[Shun Oguri]]\n* [[Eiza Gonz\u00e1lez]]\n* [[Jessica Henwick]]\n* [[Julian Dennison]]\n* [[Kyle Chandler]]\n* [[Zhang Ziyi]]\n* [[Demi\u00e1n Bichir]]\n}}\n| music          = \n| cinematography = [[Ben Seresin]]\n| editing        = Josh Schaeffer\n| studio         = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Legendary Entertainment|Legendary Pictures]]\n}}\n| distributor    = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Warner Bros. Pictures]] (Worldwide)\n* Toho (Japan)\n}}\n| released       = {{Film date|2020|11|20|United States}}\n| country        = United States\n| language       = English\n| budget         =\n| gross          =\n}}\n\n'''''Godzilla vs. Kong''''' is an upcoming American [[monster film]] directed by [[Adam Wingard]]. A sequel to ''[[Godzilla: King of the Monsters (2019 film)|Godzilla: King of the Monsters]]'' (2019) and ''[[Kong: Skull Island]]'' (2017), it is the fourth film in [[Legendary Entertainment|Legendary]]'s [[MonsterVerse]]. The film is also the 36th film in the [[Godzilla (franchise)|''Godzilla'' franchise]], the 12th film in the [[King Kong (franchise)|''King Kong'' franchise]], and the fourth ''Godzilla'' film to be completely produced by a Hollywood studio.{{efn|The American releases of ''[[Godzilla (1954 film)|Godzilla]]'' (''[[Godzilla, King of the Monsters!]]''), ''[[King Kong vs. Godzilla#English version|King Kong vs. Godzilla]]'', and ''[[The Return of Godzilla]]'' (''[[Godzilla 1985]]'') featured additional footage with American actors filmed by small Hollywood production companies that merged the American footage with the original Japanese footage in order to appeal to American audiences.{{sfn|Kalat|2010|p=25}} ''[[Invasion of Astro-Monster]]'' was the first ''Godzilla'' film to be co-produced between a Japanese studio (Toho) and an American studio ([[UPA (animation studio)|UPA]]). The first ''Godzilla'' film to be completely produced by a Hollywood studio was ''[[Godzilla (1998 film)|Godzilla]]'' (1998).}} The film stars [[Alexander Skarsg\u00e5rd]], [[Millie Bobby Brown]], [[Rebecca Hall]], [[Brian Tyree Henry]], [[Shun Oguri]], [[Eiza Gonz\u00e1lez]], [[Jessica Henwick]], [[Julian Dennison]], [[Kyle Chandler]], [[Zhang Ziyi]], and [[Demi\u00e1n Bichir]].\n\nThe project was announced in October 2015 when Legendary announced plans for a shared cinematic universe between [[Godzilla]] and [[King Kong]]. The film's writers room was assembled in March 2017, and Wingard was announced as the director in May 2017. [[Principal photography]] began in November 2018 in [[Hawaii]], [[Australia]], and [[Hong Kong]] and [[Wrap (filmmaking)|wrapped]] in April 2019. ''Godzilla vs. Kong'' is scheduled to be released on November 20, 2020, in 2D, [[3D film|3D]], and [[IMAX]].\n\n==Premise==\n{{quote|In a time when monsters walk the Earth, humanity's fight for its future sets Godzilla and Kong on a collision course that will see the two most powerful forces of nature on the planet collide in a spectacular battle for the ages. As Monarch embarks on a perilous mission into uncharted terrain and unearths clues to the Titans' origins, a human conspiracy threatens to wipe the creatures, both good and bad, from the face of the earth forever.|source=Legendary and Warner Bros.<ref name=\"Press Release\"/>}}\n\n== Cast ==\n*[[Alexander Skarsg\u00e5rd]]:<br>A [[geologist]] who works closely with Kong. Skarsg\u00e5rd described his character as a [[reluctant hero]] who is \"not an alpha, bad-ass\" and \"thrown into this very dangerous situation and is definitely not equipped for it\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://etcanada.com/news/383733/alexander-skarsgard-spills-details-about-his-role-in-godzilla-vs-king-kong/|title=Alexander Skarsgard Spills Details About His Role In \u2018Godzilla Vs. Kong\u2019|author=Brent Furdyk|work=Entertainment Tonight Canada|date=November 5, 2018|accessdate=October 14, 2019|url-status=live|archivedate=October 14, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191015021004/https://etcanada.com/news/383733/alexander-skarsgard-spills-details-about-his-role-in-godzilla-vs-king-kong/}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://collider.com/alexander-skarsgard-the-kill-team-the-stand-godzilla-vs-kong-interview/|title=Alexander Skarsgard on 'The Kill Team', 'The Stand', and His Unlikely Hero in 'Godzilla vs. Kong'|last=Radish|first=Christina|date=2019-10-30|website=Collider|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/10/18/movies/alexander-skarsgard-the-kill-team.html|title=There Are Worse Roles Than the Seducer. Ask Alexander Skarsgard.|last=Shattuck|first=Kathryn|date=2019-10-18|work=The New York Times|access-date=2019-11-09|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>\n*[[Millie Bobby Brown]] as Madison Russell\n*[[Rebecca Hall]]\n*[[Brian Tyree Henry]]\n*[[Shun Oguri]]\n*[[Eiza Gonz\u00e1lez]]:<br>Gonz\u00e1lez described her role as a \"very smart woman behind a company\". She also described the film as \"slightly comedic\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://collider.com/eiza-gonzalez-bloodshot-paradise-hills-interview/|title=Eiza Gonz\u00e1lez on 'Paradise Hills' and Playing the First Female Mexican Superhero in 'Bloodshot'|last=Radish|first=Christina|date=2019-10-31|website=Collider|language=en-US|url-status=live|access-date=2019-11-09}}</ref>\n*[[Jessica Henwick]]\n*[[Julian Dennison]]\n*[[Kyle Chandler]] as Dr. Mark Russell:<br>Madison's father and an expert [[Anthrozoology|anthrozoologist]].\n*[[Demi\u00e1n Bichir]]\n\nAdditionally, [[Zhang Ziyi]] reprises her role from ''Godzilla: King of the Monsters'', with Van Marten cast as her assistant. [[Lance Reddick]] has been cast in an undisclosed role.\n\n== Production ==\n'''Production credits'''<ref name=\"Press Release\"/>\n{{Div col}}\n* [[Adam Wingard]] \u2013 director\n* Kenji Okuhira \u2013 executive producer\n* [[Yoshimitsu Banno]] \u2013 executive producer (posthumous)\n* [[Jon Jashni]] \u2013 executive producer\n* [[Thomas Tull]] \u2013 executive producer\n* Jay Ashenfelter \u2013 co-producer\n* Jen Conroy \u2013 co-producer\n* Tamara Kent \u2013 co-producer\n* Owen Patterson \u2013 production designer\n* Tom Hammock \u2013 production designer\n* Ann Foley \u2013 costume designer\n* John \u201cDJ\u201d DesJardin \u2013 VFX supervisor\n{{Div col end}}\n\n===Development===\nIn September 2015, Legendary moved ''Kong: Skull Island'' from Universal to Warner Bros., which sparked media speculation that [[Godzilla]] and [[King Kong]] would appear in a film together.<ref name=\"KingKongOnMove\">{{cite web |url=http://deadline.com/2015/09/king-kong-godzilla-legendary-monster-movie-warner-bros-1201521004/ |title=King Kong On Move To Warner Bros, Presaging Godzilla Monster Matchup |last=Fleming Jr. |first=Mike |website=Deadline Hollywood |date=September 10, 2015 |accessdate=September 10, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150911232832/http://deadline.com/2015/09/king-kong-godzilla-legendary-monster-movie-warner-bros-1201521004/#|archive-date=September 11, 2015|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |work=The Hollywood Reporter |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/hollywood-gorilla-warfare-s-universal-823715 |title=Hollywood Gorilla Warfare: It\u2019s Universal vs. Legendary Over \u2018Kong: Skull Island\u2019 (and Who Says \"Thank You\") |first=Kim |last=Masters |date=September 16, 2015 |accessdate=September 17, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150917235805/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/hollywood-gorilla-warfare-s-universal-823715# |archive-date=September 17, 2015 |url-status=live}}</ref> In October 2015, Legendary confirmed that they would unite Godzilla and King Kong in ''Godzilla vs. Kong'', at the time targeted for a May 29, 2020, release. Legendary plans to create a shared cinematic franchise \"centered around Monarch\" that \"brings together Godzilla and Legendary\u2019s King Kong in an ecosystem of other [[kaiju|giant super-species]], both classic and new.\"<ref>{{cite press release |url=http://www.legendary.com/legendary-and-warner-bros-pictures-announce-cinematic-franchise-uniting-godzilla-king-kong-and-other-iconic-giant-monsters/ |title=Legendary and Warner Bros. Pictures Announce Cinematic Franchise Uniting Godzilla, King Kong and Other Iconic Giant Monsters |publisher=Legendary Pictures |date=October 14, 2015 |accessdate=October 14, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151105182819/http://www.legendary.com/legendary-and-warner-bros-pictures-announce-cinematic-franchise-uniting-godzilla-king-kong-and-other-iconic-giant-monsters/#|archive-date=November 5, 2015|url-status=live}}</ref> Producer Alex Garcia confirmed that the film will not be a [[remake]] of ''[[King Kong vs. Godzilla]]'', stating, \"the idea is not to remake that movie.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tohokingdom.com/interviews/kong_alex_garcia_02-2017.html |title=Interview: Alex Garcia \u2013 Roundtable (2015) |last=Mirjahangir |first=Chris |website=Toho Kingdom |date=December 2, 2015 |accessdate=July 14, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170619160700/http://www.tohokingdom.com/interviews/kong_alex_garcia_02-2017.html#|archive-date=June 19, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> In May 2017, [[Adam Wingard]] was announced as the director for ''Godzilla vs. Kong''.<ref name=\"Adam\">{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/godzilla-kong-finds-director-adam-wingard-1008773 |title='Godzilla vs. Kong' Finds Its Director With Adam Wingard (Exclusive) |last=Kit |first=Borys |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=May 30, 2017 |accessdate=May 30, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170531025423/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/godzilla-kong-finds-director-adam-wingard-1008773#|archive-date=May 31, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2017, Wingard spoke about the outline created by the writers room, stating, \"We're going in very great detail through all the characters, the arcs they have, how they relate to one another, and most importantly how they relate to the monsters, and how the monsters relate to them or reflect them.\" He also stated that he and his team are going \"beat by beat\" on the outline, stating, \"So once again, it's a discussion, and about feeling out how to make it as strong as possible, so that when Terry [Rossio] goes to write the screenplay, he has a definitive breakdown of what to include.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://birthmoviesdeath.com/2017/07/20/adam-wingard-talks-godzilla-vs.-kong-and-directorial-freedom |title=Adam Wingard Talks Godzilla vs. Kong And Directorial Freedom |last=Gingold |first=Michael |work=Birth.Movies.Death |date=July 20, 2017 |accessdate=July 20, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170723234247/http://birthmoviesdeath.com/2017/07/20/adam-wingard-talks-godzilla-vs.-kong-and-directorial-freedom#|archive-date=July 23, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> In August 2017, Wingard spoke about his approach for the monsters, stating:\n\n{{Quote|\"I really want you to take those characters seriously. I want you to be emotionally invested, not just in the human characters, but actually in the monsters. It\u2019s a massive monster brawl movie. There\u2019s lots of monsters going crazy on each other, but at the end of the day I want there to be an emotional drive to it. I want you to be emotionally invested in them. I think that\u2019s what\u2019s going to make it really cool.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://screencrush.com/adam-wingard-godzilla-vs-kong-emotional/ |title=Adam Wingard Wants 'Godzilla vs. Kong' to Make You Cry |last=Whitney |first=E. Oliver |work=Screen Crush |date=August 18, 2017 |accessdate=August 19, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170819034438/http://screencrush.com/adam-wingard-godzilla-vs-kong-emotional/#|archive-date=2017-08-19|url-status=live}}</ref>}} Wingard expressed his desire for the film to have a definite winner, stating:\n\n{{Quote|\u201cI do want there to be a winner. The original film was very fun, but you feel a little let down that the movie doesn\u2019t take a definitive stance. People are still debating now who won in that original movie, you know. So, I do want people to walk away from this film feeling like, Okay, there is a winner.\u201d<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indiewire.com/2017/08/godzilla-vs-kong-adam-wingard-winner-1201868084/ |title=\u2018Godzilla vs. Kong\u2019: Adam Wingard Says the Epic Battle Will Have a Definitive Winner |last=Nordine |first=Michael |work=IndieWire |date=August 20, 2017 |accessdate=January 8, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180109121908/http://www.indiewire.com/2017/08/godzilla-vs-kong-adam-wingard-winner-1201868084/#|archive-date=2018-01-09|url-status=live}}</ref>}}\n\nWingard also confirmed that the film will tie in with ''[[Godzilla: King of the Monsters (2019 film)|Godzilla: King of the Monsters]]'', be set in modern times, and feature a \"more rugged, a bit more aged Kong.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://screenrant.com/godzilla-vs-kong-setting-character-details/?view=lista |title=Godzilla vs. Kong Set in Modern Day, Ties to Godzilla 2 |last=Mithaiwala |first=Mansoor |work=Screen Rant |date=August 22, 2017 |accessdate=August 24, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171224101315/https://screenrant.com/godzilla-vs-kong-setting-character-details/?view=lista#|archive-date=December 24, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Writing===\nIn March 2017, Legendary assembled a writers room to develop the story for ''Godzilla vs. Kong'', with [[Terry Rossio]] (who co-wrote an early unproduced script for [[Godzilla (1998 film)|TriStar's ''Godzilla'']])<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.scifijapan.com/articles/2015/05/10/godzilla-unmade-the-history-of-jan-de-bonts-unproduced-tristar-film-part-1/ |title=Godzilla Unmade: The History of Jan De Bont\u2019s Unproduced TriStar Film \u2013 Part 1 of 4 |last=Aiken |first=Keith |website=Scifi Japan |date=May 10, 2015 |accessdate=May 23, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170915071019/http://www.scifijapan.com/articles/2015/05/10/godzilla-unmade-the-history-of-jan-de-bonts-unproduced-tristar-film-part-1/#|archive-date=September 15, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> leading a team consisting of Patrick McKay, J. D. Payne, Lindsey Beer, Cat Vasko, [[T.S. Nowlin]], Jack Paglen, and [[J. Michael Straczynski]].<ref name=\"writers room\">{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/kong-skull-island-sequel-plans-godzilla-kong-sets-writers-room-984992 |title='Godzilla vs. Kong' Film Sets Writers Room (Exclusive) |last=Kit |first=Borys |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=March 10, 2017 |accessdate=March 10, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170310230537/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/kong-skull-island-sequel-plans-godzilla-kong-sets-writers-room-984992#|archive-date=March 10, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> On his experience with the writers room, Rossio stated:\n\n{{Quote|\"''Godzilla vs. Kong'' was my first experience running a writer's room, and it was fantastic. It was a blast reading samples, meeting different writers, and crafting a story in a group setting. It felt similar to animation, where the film is happening up on the walls, and the end result is better than any one person could accomplish on their own.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/pirates-caribbean-screenwriter-how-a-budget-crisis-changed-villains-1001860 |title=Original 'Pirates of the Caribbean' Screenwriter on How a Budget Crisis Changed the Villains |last=Schoellkopf |first=Christina |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=May 26, 2017 |accessdate=May 27, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170527023430/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/pirates-caribbean-screenwriter-how-a-budget-crisis-changed-villains-1001860#|archive-date=May 27, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>}}\n\n[[Michael Dougherty]] and Zach Shields, the director and co-writers of ''Godzilla: King of the Monsters'', provided rewrites to ensure that certain themes from ''King of the Monsters'' were carried over and that some characters were properly developed.<ref>{{cite web |last=Tyler |first=Jacob |url=https://thegww.com/godzilla-vs-kong-got-rewrites-from-mike-dougherty-zach-shields-godzilla-king-of-the-monsters/ |title=''Godzilla vs. Kong'' Got Rewrites From Mike Dougherty & Zach Shields |date=March 5, 2019 |work=Omega Underground |accessdate=March 13, 2019|url-status=live |archivedate=March 13, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190314023922/https://thegww.com/godzilla-vs-kong-got-rewrites-from-mike-dougherty-zach-shields-godzilla-king-of-the-monsters/}}</ref> Dougherty revealed how he wrote for the title characters, and how the film would address their differing interactions with people. For Kong, Dougherty stated the film would feature \"those very unique, and even warm, bonding moments\" between Kong and humans since they've been a staple of the character since the [[King Kong (1933 film)|1933 film]]. For Godzilla, his connection to humans would be \"more implied\" as his softer side is rarely shown.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://screenrant.com/godzilla-king-kong-different-humanity-connections-explained/ |title=Godzilla 2 Director Explains Godzilla & Kong's Different Connections to Humanity |first=Daniel |last=Alvarez |work=Screen Rant |date=May 5, 2019 |accessdate=May 7, 2019|url-status=live |archivedate=May 7, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190507185131/https://screenrant.com/godzilla-king-kong-different-humanity-connections-explained/}}</ref>\n\n=== Pre-production ===\nIn June 2017, it was announced that [[Ziyi Zhang]] had joined Legendary's MonsterVerse, having a reportedly \"pivotal\" role in both ''Godzilla: King of the Monsters'' and ''Godzilla vs. Kong''.<ref name=\"ZiyiCast\">{{cite web |url=http://deadline.com/2017/06/zhang-ziyi-godzilla-movie-franchise-casting-1202110018/ |title=Zhang Ziyi Comes Aboard 'Godzilla' And Beyond |last=Hipes |first=Patrick |website=Deadline.com |date=June 8, 2017 |accessdate=June 8, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170611233620/http://deadline.com/2017/06/zhang-ziyi-godzilla-movie-franchise-casting-1202110018/#|archive-date=June 11, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> In June 2018, [[Julian Dennison]] was cast alongside Van Marten, while [[Millie Bobby Brown]] and [[Kyle Chandler]] would reprise their roles from ''Godzilla: King of the Monsters''.<ref>{{cite web |last=Perez |first=Lexy |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/deadpool-2-star-julian-dennison-joins-godzilla-kong-1116661 |title=''Deadpool 2'' Star Julian Dennison Joins ''Godzilla vs. Kong'' |date=June 2, 2018 |work=The Hollywood Reporter |accessdate=June 3, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180603033211/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/deadpool-2-star-julian-dennison-joins-godzilla-kong-1116661#|archive-date=June 3, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Legendary also sent an offer to [[Frances McDormand]] for a role.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://thathashtagshow.com/2018/06/exclusive-deadpool-2-julian-dennison-joins-godzilla-vs-kong/ |title=Exclusive: \u2018Deadpool 2\u2019s\u2019 Julian Dennison Joins \u2018Godzilla vs. Kong\u2019 |last=Murphy |first=Charles |work=That Hashtag Show |date=June 1, 2018 |accessdate=June 1, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612143532/http://thathashtagshow.com/2018/06/exclusive-deadpool-2-julian-dennison-joins-godzilla-vs-kong/|archive-date=June 12, 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref> In July 2018, it was revealed that [[Danai Gurira]] was in early talks to join the film.<ref name=\"Danai Guiridia\">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/07/danai-gurira-godzilla-vs-kong-star-trek-the-walking-dead-black-panther-1202425900/ |title=Danai Gurira In Early \u2018Godzilla Vs. Kong\u2019 Talks As \u2018Star Trek\u2019 Also Looms For \u2018Walking Dead\u2019 & \u2018Black Panther\u2019 Star |first=Mike |last=Fleming Jr. |work=Deadline |date=July 12, 2018 |accessdate=July 12, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180713054816/https://deadline.com/2018/07/danai-gurira-godzilla-vs-kong-star-trek-the-walking-dead-black-panther-1202425900/#|archive-date=July 13, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> In October 2018, [[Brian Tyree Henry]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/brian-tyree-henry-godzilla-vs-kong-millie-bobby-brown-1202976259/ |title=Brian Tyree Henry to Co-Star With Millie Bobby Brown in \u2018Godzilla vs. Kong\u2019 (Exclusive) |first=Justin |last=Kroll |work=Variety |date=October 10, 2018 |accessdate=October 10, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181011014559/https://variety.com/2018/film/news/brian-tyree-henry-godzilla-vs-kong-millie-bobby-brown-1202976259/#|archive-date=October 11, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Demi\u00e1n Bichir]],<ref>{{cite web |last=Kit |first=Borys |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/demi-n-bichir-joining-millie-bobby-brown-godzilla-kong-1153121 |title=Demi\u00e1n Bichir Joining Millie Bobby Brown in ''Godzilla vs. Kong'' |date=October 17, 2018 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |publisher=[[Valence Media]] |accessdate=October 17, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181017213127/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/demi-n-bichir-joining-millie-bobby-brown-godzilla-kong-1153121|archive-date=October 17, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Alexander Skarsg\u00e5rd]],<ref name=\"Skarsg\u00e5rdCast\">{{cite news |last1=Jr |first1=Mike Fleming |title=Alexander Skarsg\u00e5rd To Star In \u2018Godzilla Vs. Kong\u2019 |url=https://deadline.com/2018/10/alexander-skarsgard-to-star-in-godzilla-vs-kong-1202489612/ |accessdate=October 25, 2018 |work=Deadline |date=October 25, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181026064527/https://deadline.com/2018/10/alexander-skarsgard-to-star-in-godzilla-vs-kong-1202489612/# |archive-date=October 26, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref> [[Eiza Gonz\u00e1lez]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/10/eiza-gonzalez-godzilla-vs-king-kong-alexander-skarsgard-1202492406/ |title=Eiza Gonzalez Joins \u2018Godzilla Vs. King Kong |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |first=Mike |last=Fleming Jr |date=October 30, 2018 |accessdate=October 30, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181031052347/https://deadline.com/2018/10/eiza-gonzalez-godzilla-vs-king-kong-alexander-skarsgard-1202492406/#|archive-date=October 31, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> and [[Rebecca Hall]] were added to the cast.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/rebecca-hall-godzilla-vs-kong-1203014950/ |title=Rebecca Hall to Star Opposite Millie Bobby Brown in \u2018Godzilla vs. Kong\u2019 (EXCLUSIVE) |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |first=Justin |last=Kroll |date=October 30, 2018 |accessdate=October 30, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181031005404/https://variety.com/2018/film/news/rebecca-hall-godzilla-vs-kong-1203014950/#|archive-date=October 31, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> In November 2018, [[Jessica Henwick]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/jessica-henwick-godzilla-vs-kong-game-of-thrones-1203024081/ |title=\u2018Game of Thrones\u2019 Actress Jessica Henwick Joins \u2018Godzilla vs. Kong\u2019 (Exclusive) |first=Justin |last=Kroll |work=Variety |date=November 8, 2018 |accessdate=November 8, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181109070757/https://variety.com/2018/film/news/jessica-henwick-godzilla-vs-kong-game-of-thrones-1203024081/|archive-date=November 9, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Shun Oguri]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/11/shun-oguri-godzilla-vs-kong-japanese-star-crows-zero-alexander-skarsgard-1202499759/ |title=Japanese Star Shun Oguri Makes Hollywood Debut In \u2018Godzilla Vs. Kong\u2019 |first=Mike |last=Fleming Jr |work=Deadline |date=November 11, 2018 |accessdate=November 11, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181111213802/https://deadline.com/2018/11/shun-oguri-godzilla-vs-kong-japanese-star-crows-zero-alexander-skarsgard-1202499759/#|archive-date=November 11, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> and [[Lance Reddick]] were cast, with Oguri making his Hollywood debut.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/11/bosch-lance-reddick-godzilla-vs-kong-1202502022/ |title='Bosch' Actor Lance Reddick Cast in 'Godzilla vs Kong' |website=Deadline |first=Amanda |last=N'Duka |date=November 14, 2018 |accessdate=November 14, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181115030528/https://deadline.com/2018/11/bosch-lance-reddick-godzilla-vs-kong-1202502022/|archive-date=November 15, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n=== Filming ===\n[[Principal photography]] began on November 12, 2018 in [[Hawaii]] and [[Australia]] and was expected to end in February 2019 under the working title ''Apex''.<ref name=\"Press Release\">{{cite web |url=https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20181112005664/en/Warner-Bros.-Pictures%E2%80%99-Legendary-Entertainment%E2%80%99s-Monsterverse-Shifts |title=Warner Bros. Pictures\u2019 and Legendary Entertainment\u2019s Monsterverse Shifts into Overdrive as Cameras Roll on the Next Big-Screen Adventure \"Godzilla Vs. Kong\" |work=Business Wire |date= |accessdate=November 12, 2018 |archivedate=January 19, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190120054526/https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20181112005664/en/Warner-Bros.-Pictures%E2%80%99-Legendary-Entertainment%E2%80%99s-Monsterverse-Shifts|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Prasad |first=R.A |url=https://pursuenews.com/godzilla-vs-kong-working-title-revealed/ |title=Warner Bros. And Legendary Pictures' ''Godzilla Vs. Kong'' Working Title Revealed |date=May 3, 2018 |publisher=PureNews |accessdate=May 3, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180504092023/https://pursuenews.com/godzilla-vs-kong-working-title-revealed/#|archive-date=May 4, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Production was initially slated to begin on October 1, 2018.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Marc |first1=Christopher |title='Godzilla vs Kong' Heading Back To Australia and Hawaii - GWW |url=https://thegww.com/godzilla-vs-kong-heading-back-to-australia-and-hawaii/ |accessdate=July 18, 2018 |work=GWW |date=July 11, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181011053715/https://thegww.com/godzilla-vs-kong-heading-back-to-australia-and-hawaii/# |archive-date=October 11, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref> For the Hawaii shoot, the crew filmed on the [[USS Missouri (BB-63)|USS ''Missouri'']], at [[Manoa Falls]], and in [[Downtown Honolulu]]. The crew established a camp in the [[Hawaii Route 72|Kalanianaole Highway]], which had been closed until November 21. Local crews and extras were used for the film.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.staradvertiser.com/2018/11/16/hawaii-news/godzilla-vs-kong-filming-in-full-swing-with-upcoming-closures-on-oahu/ |title=\u2018Godzilla vs. Kong\u2019 filming in full swing with upcoming closures on Oahu |first=Nina |last=Wu |work=Star Advertiser |date=November 17, 2018 |accessdate=November 17, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181117114833/http://www.staradvertiser.com/2018/11/16/hawaii-news/godzilla-vs-kong-filming-in-full-swing-with-upcoming-closures-on-oahu/|archive-date=November 17, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> In January 2019, filming resumed in [[Gold Coast, Queensland]] at [[Village Roadshow Studios]] for an additional 26 weeks.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.brisbanetimes.com.au/national/queensland/godzilla-vs-kong-begins-filming-on-the-gold-coast-20190118-p50s6d.html |title=Godzilla vs. Kong begins filming on the Gold Coast |first=Felicity |last=Caldwell |work=Brisbane Times |date=January 18, 2019 |accessdate=January 19, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190119224354/https://www.brisbanetimes.com.au/national/queensland/godzilla-vs-kong-begins-filming-on-the-gold-coast-20190118-p50s6d.html |archivedate=January 19, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Godzilla sighting down under! |url=https://moviehole.net/godzilla-sighting-down-under/ |website=Moviehole |publisher=Editorial Staff |accessdate=January 24, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190124034500/https://moviehole.net/godzilla-sighting-down-under/ |archive-date=January 24, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nFilming locations in Australia included [[Miami State High School]] and parts of [[Brisbane]] such as the [[Newstead, Queensland|Newstead suburb]], the [[Chinatown, Brisbane|Chinatown Mall in Fortitude Valley]], and the [[Wickham Terrace Car Park]]. In April 2019, Wingard confirmed via [[Instagram]] that filming in Australia had wrapped.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cinemablend.com/news/2470013/Godzilla-Vs-Kong-Has-Wrapped-In-Australia-According-To-The-Director |title=Godzilla Vs. Kong Has Wrapped In Australia |first=Dirk |last=Libbey |work=Cinema Blend |date=April 9, 2019 |accessdate=April 9, 2019|url-status=live |archivedate=April 9, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190410020411/https://www.cinemablend.com/news/2470013/Godzilla-Vs-Kong-Has-Wrapped-In-Australia-According-To-The-Director}}</ref> That same month, Wingard revealed [[Hong Kong]] as one of the final shooting locations and that principal photography had wrapped.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://ew.com/movies/2019/04/20/godzilla-vs-kong/ |title=Godzilla vs. Kong wraps shooting |first=Clark |last=Collis |work=Entertainment Weekly |date=April 20, 2019 |accessdate=April 20, 2019|url-status=live |archivedate=April 20, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190420223019/https://ew.com/movies/2019/04/20/godzilla-vs-kong/}}</ref>\nafter the dissapointing box office performance of Godzilla king of the monsters,warner bros president Toby Emmerich hinted that they would delay godzilla vs kong in order to do it the way fans and the general public expect using reshoots.\n\n== Release ==\n===Marketing===\nIn May 2019, the first promotional one-sheet poster was revealed at the Licensing Expo.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://collider.com/godzilla-vs-kong-dune-promo-posters/ |title=New Promo Posters for \u2018Godzilla vs Kong\u2019 and \u2018Dune\u2019 Tease the Titanic 2020 Titles |first=Dave |last=Trumbore |work=Collider |date=May 30, 2019 |accessdate=May 31, 2019|url-status=live |archivedate=May 31, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190531091732/http://collider.com/godzilla-vs-kong-dune-promo-posters/}}</ref> In June 2019, Warner Bros screened an early look to European exhibitors at CineEurope.<ref name=\"CineEurope\">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/06/warner-bros-godzilla-vs-kong-it2-joker-wonder-woman-lionsgate-rian-johnson-knives-out-studiocanal-cineeurope-1202633778/ |title=Warner Bros Teases Horror, DC, \u2018Godzilla Vs Kong\u2019; Studiocanal Goes \u2018Radioactive\u2019 \u2013 CineEurope |first=Nancy |last=Tartaglione |work=Deadline Hollywood |date=June 17, 2019 |accessdate=June 17, 2019|url-status=live |archivedate=June 17, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190618043628/https://deadline.com/2019/06/warner-bros-godzilla-vs-kong-it2-joker-wonder-woman-lionsgate-rian-johnson-knives-out-studiocanal-cineeurope-1202633778/}}</ref> In August 2019, it was announced that Disruptor Beam will develop a mobile game to tie-in for the film's release.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://cosmicbook.news/godzilla-vs-kong-poster-game |title=Godzilla vs. Kong Poster teases one will fall;Game in Development |first=Matt |last=McGloin |work=Cosmic Book News |date=August 10, 2019 |accessdate=August 11, 2019|url-status=live |archivedate=August 11, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190811215337/https://cosmicbook.news/godzilla-vs-kong-poster-game}}</ref> In December 2019, a brief clip was revealed during a Warner Bros. reel at [[Comic Con Experience]], and later leaked online.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cinemablend.com/news/2486314/whoa-kong-punches-godzilla-in-super-brief-but-badass-godzilla-vs-kong-footage|title=Whoa, Kong Punches Godzilla In Super-Brief But Badass Godzilla Vs. Kong Footage|author=Gina Carbone|work=CinemaBlend|date=December 8, 2019|accessdate=December 8, 2019|url-status=live|archivedate=December 8, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191209011305/https://www.cinemablend.com/news/2486314/whoa-kong-punches-godzilla-in-super-brief-but-badass-godzilla-vs-kong-footage}}</ref> In January 2020, images from the Hong Kong Toys & Games Fair displaying figures (including a [[Mechagodzilla]] figure) related to the film were leaked online, sparking speculation whether the film would include Mechagodzilla.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cinemablend.com/news/2487983/godzilla-vs-kong-might-be-bringing-in-an-iconic-kaiju|title=Godzilla Vs. Kong Might Be Bringing In An Iconic Kaiju|author=Adam Holmes|work=Cinema Blend|date=January 7, 2020|accessdate=January 7, 2020|url-status=live|archivedate=January 7, 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200108042635/https://www.cinemablend.com/news/2487983/godzilla-vs-kong-might-be-bringing-in-an-iconic-kaiju}}</ref> In February 2020, Toho and Legendary announced the ''Godzilla vs. Kong'' Publishing Program and licensees. Through the publishing program, Legendary plans to release two graphic novels, an art book, novelizations, and children\u2019s books. Amongst the licensees named were [[Playmates Toys]], Bioworld, Rubies, Funko, 60Out, and the Virtual Reality Company.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.scifijapan.com/articles/2020/02/20/toho-and-legendary-announce-licensees-for-godzilla-vs-kong/|title=Toho and Legendary Announce Licensees for Godzilla vs. Kong|author1=Chris Mowry|author2=Jacara Jenkins|work=SciFi Japan|date=February 20, 2020|accessdate=February 20, 2020|url-status=live|archivedate=February 20, 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200221062043/http://www.scifijapan.com/articles/2020/02/20/toho-and-legendary-announce-licensees-for-godzilla-vs-kong/}}</ref> In April 2019, images of toy figures were leaked online, revealing different forms for Godzilla and Kong, and a new monster.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cinemablend.com/news/2494095/godzilla-vs-kong-merchandise-seemingly-reveals-another-monster-heading-to-the-big-screen|title=Godzilla Vs Kong Merchandise Seemingly Reveals Another Monster Heading To The Big Screen|author=Erik Swann|work=Cinema Blend|date=April 8, 2020|accessdate=April 9, 2020|url-status=live|archivedate=April 9, 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200409221801/https://www.cinemablend.com/news/2494095/godzilla-vs-kong-merchandise-seemingly-reveals-another-monster-heading-to-the-big-screen}}</ref>\n\n===Theatrical===\n''Godzilla vs. Kong'' is scheduled to be released in the United States on November 20, 2020, in 2D, [[3D film|3D]], and [[IMAX]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/godzilla-kong-release-date-pushed-8-months-november-2020-1253500|title='Godzilla vs. Kong' Release Date Pushed 8 Months to November 2020|author=Aaron Couch|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=November 25, 2019|accessdate=November 25, 2019|url-status=live|archivedate=November 25, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191126074636/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/godzilla-kong-release-date-pushed-8-months-november-2020-1253500}}</ref> It will be distributed by [[Warner Bros.|Warner Bros. Pictures]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/02/space-jam-2-release-date-godzilla-vs-kong-annabelle-sequel-warner-bros-1202562428/ |title=Warner Bros Dates \u2018Space Jam 2\u2019, Shifts \u2018Annabelle\u2019 Sequel & \u2018Godzilla Vs. Kong\u2019 |first=Erik |last=Pedersen |work=Deadline |date=February 21, 2019 |accessdate=February 21, 2019|url-status=live |archivedate=February 21, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190222025700/https://deadline.com/2019/02/space-jam-2-release-date-godzilla-vs-kong-annabelle-sequel-warner-bros-1202562428/}}</ref> except in Japan where it will be distributed by [[Toho]].<ref name=\"Press Release\"/> The film was previously scheduled to be released on May 29, May 22, and March 13, 2020.<ref name=\"May10\">{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/warner-bros-moves-dates-godzilla-892634 |title=Warner Bros. Moves Dates For 'Godzilla 2,' 'Godzilla vs Kong' |last=Rahman |first=Abid |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=May 10, 2016 |accessdate=May 10, 2016|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6pLyTqstH?url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/warner-bros-moves-dates-godzilla-892634#|archive-date=March 30, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/06/warner-studio-toby-emmerich-peter-roth-dc-netflix-godzilla-vs-kong-kevin-tsujihara-1202629538/ |title=Warner Bros. Bosses Toby Emmerich & Peter Roth On Studio Post Kevin Tsujihara In Streaming Era, Disney/Fox & Potential \u2018Godzilla vs. Kong\u2019 Move \u2013 Produced By |first=Anthony |last=D'Alessandro |work=Deadline Hollywood |date=June 8, 2019 |accessdate=June 9, 2019|url-status=live |archivedate=June 9, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190609070404/https://deadline.com/2019/06/warner-studio-toby-emmerich-peter-roth-dc-netflix-godzilla-vs-kong-kevin-tsujihara-1202629538/}}</ref><ref name=\"new date\">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/02/space-jam-2-release-date-godzilla-vs-kong-annabelle-sequel-warner-bros-1202562428/ |title=Warner Bros Dates \u2018Space Jam 2\u2019, Shifts \u2018Annabelle\u2019 Sequel & \u2018Godzilla Vs. Kong\u2019 |last=Pedersen |first=Erik |work=Deadline |date=February 21, 2019 |accessdate=February 21, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190222025700/https://deadline.com/2019/02/space-jam-2-release-date-godzilla-vs-kong-annabelle-sequel-warner-bros-1202562428/|archive-date=February 22, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Prior to the film's pushed date, Warner Bros. Studio chairman [[Toby Emmerich]] revealed in June 2019 that the film could potentially be pushed back, stating, \"It might come out later in the year, so we can deliver an A+ movie.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/06/warner-studio-toby-emmerich-peter-roth-dc-netflix-godzilla-vs-kong-kevin-tsujihara-1202629538/ |title=Warner Bros. Bosses Toby Emmerich & Peter Roth On Studio Post Kevin Tsujihara In Streaming Era, Disney/Fox & Potential \u2018Godzilla vs. Kong\u2019 Move \u2013 Produced By |first=Anthony |last=D'Alessandro |work=Deadline Hollywood |date=June 8, 2019 |accessdate=June 9, 2019|url-status=live |archivedate=June 9, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190609070404/https://deadline.com/2019/06/warner-studio-toby-emmerich-peter-roth-dc-netflix-godzilla-vs-kong-kevin-tsujihara-1202629538/}}</ref> In February 2020, Warner Bros. hosted an unannounced test screening, which received a positive response.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cinemablend.com/news/2491108/check-out-godzilla-vs-kongs-directors-cryptic-post-following-reported-test-screening|title=Check Out Godzilla Vs. Kong's Director\u2019s Cryptic Post Following Reported Test Screening|author=Adam Holmes|work=Cinema Blend|date=February 28, 2020|accessdate=March 11, 2020|url-status=live|archivedate=March 11, 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312012236/https://www.cinemablend.com/news/2491108/check-out-godzilla-vs-kongs-directors-cryptic-post-following-reported-test-screening}}</ref>\n\n== Notes ==\n{{Notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n=== Citations ===\n{{Reflist|refs=}}\n\n=== Bibliography ===\n* {{cite book |last=Kalat |first=David |year=2010 |title=A Critical History and Filmography of Toho's Godzilla Series - Second Edition |publisher=McFarland |isbn=9780786447497 |ref=harv}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|5034838|Godzilla vs. Kong}}\n{{MonsterVerse}}\n{{Godzilla}}\n{{KingKong}}\n{{Adam Wingard}}\n\n[[Category:Upcoming films]]\n[[Category:2020 films]]\n[[Category:2020 3D films]]\n[[Category:2020s monster movies]]\n[[Category:2020s sequel films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American 3D films]]\n[[Category:Crossover films]]\n[[Category:Films set in the Atlantic Ocean]]\n[[Category:Films set in Berlin]]\n[[Category:Films set in Brisbane]]\n[[Category:Films set in Hawaii]]\n[[Category:Films set in Hong Kong]]\n[[Category:Films set in Honolulu]]\n[[Category:Films set in London]]\n[[Category:Films set in Moscow]]\n[[Category:Films set in the Pacific Ocean]]\n[[Category:Films set in Paris]]\n[[Category:Films set in Rome]]\n[[Category:Films set in Seoul]]\n[[Category:Films set in Shanghai]]\n[[Category:Films set in Sydney]]\n[[Category:Films set in Taiwan]]\n[[Category:Films set in Tokyo]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Brisbane]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Hawaii]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Hong Kong]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Honolulu]]\n[[Category:Godzilla films]]\n[[Category:Kaiju films]]\n[[Category:King Kong films]]\n[[Category:Legendary Pictures films]]\n[[Category:MonsterVerse]]\n[[Category:Films with screenplays by Terry Rossio]]\n[[Category:Toho films]]\n[[Category:Upcoming sequel films]]\n[[Category:Warner Bros. films]]\n", "text_old": "{{About|the upcoming 2020 film|the 1962 film|King Kong vs. Godzilla}}\n{{short description|2020 film directed by Adam Wingard}}\n{{Use American English|date=September 2019}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Godzilla vs. Kong\n| image          = File:Godzilla vs. Kong - licensing promotional poster.jpg\n| caption        = Official promotional poster\n| director       = [[Adam Wingard]]\n| producer       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Mary Parent]]\n* Alex Garcia\n* Eric McLeod\n* Brian Rogers\n}}\n| screenplay     = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Terry Rossio]] <!-- DO NOT ADD MICHAEL DOUGHERTY AND ZACH SHIELDS! Their contributions were only minor, not enough to merit them screenwriting credit. As of this moment, Warner Bros has named Rossio as the sole screenwriter. DO NOT ADD any additional writing credits until the WGA reveals the final writing credit list. -->\n}}\n| story          =\n| based on       = {{based on|[[Godzilla]]|[[Toho]]}}<br>{{based on|[[King Kong]]|[[Edgar Wallace]] and [[Merian C. Cooper]]}}\n| starring       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Alexander Skarsg\u00e5rd]]\n* [[Millie Bobby Brown]]\n* [[Rebecca Hall]]\n* [[Brian Tyree Henry]]\n* [[Shun Oguri]]\n* [[Eiza Gonz\u00e1lez]]\n* [[Jessica Henwick]]\n* [[Julian Dennison]]\n* [[Kyle Chandler]]\n* [[Zhang Ziyi]]\n* [[Demi\u00e1n Bichir]]\n}}\n| music          = \n| cinematography = [[Ben Seresin]]\n| editing        = Josh Schaeffer\n| studio         = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Legendary Entertainment|Legendary Pictures]]\n}}\n| distributor    = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Warner Bros. Pictures]] (Worldwide)\n* Toho (Japan)\n}}\n| released       = {{Film date|2020|11|20|United States}}\n| country        = United States\n| language       = English\n| budget         =\n| gross          =\n}}\n\n'''''Godzilla vs. Kong''''' is an upcoming American [[monster film]] directed by [[Adam Wingard]]. A sequel to ''[[Godzilla: King of the Monsters (2019 film)|Godzilla: King of the Monsters]]'' (2019) and ''[[Kong: Skull Island]]'' (2017), it is the fourth film in [[Legendary Entertainment|Legendary]]'s [[MonsterVerse]]. The film is also the 36th film in the [[Godzilla (franchise)|''Godzilla'' franchise]], the 12th film in the [[King Kong (franchise)|''King Kong'' franchise]], and the fourth ''Godzilla'' film to be completely produced by a Hollywood studio.{{efn|The American releases of ''[[Godzilla (1954 film)|Godzilla]]'' (''[[Godzilla, King of the Monsters!]]''), ''[[King Kong vs. Godzilla#English version|King Kong vs. Godzilla]]'', and ''[[The Return of Godzilla]]'' (''[[Godzilla 1985]]'') featured additional footage with American actors filmed by small Hollywood production companies that merged the American footage with the original Japanese footage in order to appeal to American audiences.{{sfn|Kalat|2010|p=25}} ''[[Invasion of Astro-Monster]]'' was the first ''Godzilla'' film to be co-produced between a Japanese studio (Toho) and an American studio ([[UPA (animation studio)|UPA]]). The first ''Godzilla'' film to be completely produced by a Hollywood studio was ''[[Godzilla (1998 film)|Godzilla]]'' (1998).}} The film stars [[Alexander Skarsg\u00e5rd]], [[Millie Bobby Brown]], [[Rebecca Hall]], [[Brian Tyree Henry]], [[Shun Oguri]], [[Eiza Gonz\u00e1lez]], [[Jessica Henwick]], [[Julian Dennison]], [[Kyle Chandler]], [[Zhang Ziyi]], and [[Demi\u00e1n Bichir]].\n\nThe project was announced in October 2015 when Legendary announced plans for a shared cinematic universe between [[Godzilla]] and [[King Kong]]. The film's writers room was assembled in March 2017, and Wingard was announced as the director in May 2017. [[Principal photography]] began in November 2018 in [[Hawaii]], [[Australia]], and [[Hong Kong]] and [[Wrap (filmmaking)|wrapped]] in April 2019. ''Godzilla vs. Kong'' is scheduled to be released on November 20, 2020, in 2D, [[3D film|3D]], and [[IMAX]].\n\n==Premise==\n{{quote|In a time when monsters walk the Earth, humanity's fight for its future sets Godzilla and Kong on a collision course that will see the two most powerful forces of nature on the planet collide in a spectacular battle for the ages. As Monarch embarks on a perilous mission into uncharted terrain and unearths clues to the Titans' origins, a human conspiracy threatens to wipe the creatures, both good and bad, from the face of the earth forever.|source=Legendary and Warner Bros.<ref name=\"Press Release\"/>}}\n\n== Cast ==\n*[[Alexander Skarsg\u00e5rd]]:<br>A [[geologist]] who works closely with Kong. Skarsg\u00e5rd described his character as a [[reluctant hero]] who is \"not an alpha, bad-ass\" and \"thrown into this very dangerous situation and is definitely not equipped for it\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://etcanada.com/news/383733/alexander-skarsgard-spills-details-about-his-role-in-godzilla-vs-king-kong/|title=Alexander Skarsgard Spills Details About His Role In \u2018Godzilla Vs. Kong\u2019|author=Brent Furdyk|work=Entertainment Tonight Canada|date=November 5, 2018|accessdate=October 14, 2019|url-status=live|archivedate=October 14, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191015021004/https://etcanada.com/news/383733/alexander-skarsgard-spills-details-about-his-role-in-godzilla-vs-king-kong/}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://collider.com/alexander-skarsgard-the-kill-team-the-stand-godzilla-vs-kong-interview/|title=Alexander Skarsgard on 'The Kill Team', 'The Stand', and His Unlikely Hero in 'Godzilla vs. Kong'|last=Radish|first=Christina|date=2019-10-30|website=Collider|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/10/18/movies/alexander-skarsgard-the-kill-team.html|title=There Are Worse Roles Than the Seducer. Ask Alexander Skarsgard.|last=Shattuck|first=Kathryn|date=2019-10-18|work=The New York Times|access-date=2019-11-09|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref>\n*[[Millie Bobby Brown]] as Madison Russell\n*[[Rebecca Hall]]\n*[[Brian Tyree Henry]]\n*[[Shun Oguri]]\n*[[Eiza Gonz\u00e1lez]]:<br>Gonz\u00e1lez described her role as a \"very smart woman behind a company\". She also described the film as \"slightly comedic\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://collider.com/eiza-gonzalez-bloodshot-paradise-hills-interview/|title=Eiza Gonz\u00e1lez on 'Paradise Hills' and Playing the First Female Mexican Superhero in 'Bloodshot'|last=Radish|first=Christina|date=2019-10-31|website=Collider|language=en-US|url-status=live|access-date=2019-11-09}}</ref>\n*[[Jessica Henwick]]\n*[[Julian Dennison]]\n*[[Kyle Chandler]] as Dr. Mark Russell:<br>Madison's father and an expert [[Anthrozoology|anthrozoologist]].\n*[[Demi\u00e1n Bichir]]\n\nAdditionally, [[Zhang Ziyi]] reprises her role from ''Godzilla: King of the Monsters'', with Van Marten cast as her assistant. [[Lance Reddick]] has been cast in an undisclosed role.\n\n== Production ==\n'''Production credits'''<ref name=\"Press Release\"/>\n{{Div col}}\n* [[Adam Wingard]] \u2013 director\n* Kenji Okuhira \u2013 executive producer\n* [[Yoshimitsu Banno]] \u2013 executive producer (posthumous)\n* [[Jon Jashni]] \u2013 executive producer\n* [[Thomas Tull]] \u2013 executive producer\n* Jay Ashenfelter \u2013 co-producer\n* Jen Conroy \u2013 co-producer\n* Tamara Kent \u2013 co-producer\n* Owen Patterson \u2013 production designer\n* Tom Hammock \u2013 production designer\n* Ann Foley \u2013 costume designer\n* John \u201cDJ\u201d DesJardin \u2013 VFX supervisor\n{{Div col end}}\n\n===Development===\nIn September 2015, Legendary moved ''Kong: Skull Island'' from Universal to Warner Bros., which sparked media speculation that [[Godzilla]] and [[King Kong]] would appear in a film together.<ref name=\"KingKongOnMove\">{{cite web |url=http://deadline.com/2015/09/king-kong-godzilla-legendary-monster-movie-warner-bros-1201521004/ |title=King Kong On Move To Warner Bros, Presaging Godzilla Monster Matchup |last=Fleming Jr. |first=Mike |website=Deadline Hollywood |date=September 10, 2015 |accessdate=September 10, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150911232832/http://deadline.com/2015/09/king-kong-godzilla-legendary-monster-movie-warner-bros-1201521004/#|archive-date=September 11, 2015|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |work=The Hollywood Reporter |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/hollywood-gorilla-warfare-s-universal-823715 |title=Hollywood Gorilla Warfare: It\u2019s Universal vs. Legendary Over \u2018Kong: Skull Island\u2019 (and Who Says \"Thank You\") |first=Kim |last=Masters |date=September 16, 2015 |accessdate=September 17, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150917235805/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/hollywood-gorilla-warfare-s-universal-823715# |archive-date=September 17, 2015 |url-status=live}}</ref> In October 2015, Legendary confirmed that they would unite Godzilla and King Kong in ''Godzilla vs. Kong'', at the time targeted for a May 29, 2020, release. Legendary plans to create a shared cinematic franchise \"centered around Monarch\" that \"brings together Godzilla and Legendary\u2019s King Kong in an ecosystem of other [[kaiju|giant super-species]], both classic and new.\"<ref>{{cite press release |url=http://www.legendary.com/legendary-and-warner-bros-pictures-announce-cinematic-franchise-uniting-godzilla-king-kong-and-other-iconic-giant-monsters/ |title=Legendary and Warner Bros. Pictures Announce Cinematic Franchise Uniting Godzilla, King Kong and Other Iconic Giant Monsters |publisher=Legendary Pictures |date=October 14, 2015 |accessdate=October 14, 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151105182819/http://www.legendary.com/legendary-and-warner-bros-pictures-announce-cinematic-franchise-uniting-godzilla-king-kong-and-other-iconic-giant-monsters/#|archive-date=November 5, 2015|url-status=live}}</ref> Producer Alex Garcia confirmed that the film will not be a [[remake]] of ''[[King Kong vs. Godzilla]]'', stating, \"the idea is not to remake that movie.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tohokingdom.com/interviews/kong_alex_garcia_02-2017.html |title=Interview: Alex Garcia \u2013 Roundtable (2015) |last=Mirjahangir |first=Chris |website=Toho Kingdom |date=December 2, 2015 |accessdate=July 14, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170619160700/http://www.tohokingdom.com/interviews/kong_alex_garcia_02-2017.html#|archive-date=June 19, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> In May 2017, [[Adam Wingard]] was announced as the director for ''Godzilla vs. Kong''.<ref name=\"Adam\">{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/godzilla-kong-finds-director-adam-wingard-1008773 |title='Godzilla vs. Kong' Finds Its Director With Adam Wingard (Exclusive) |last=Kit |first=Borys |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=May 30, 2017 |accessdate=May 30, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170531025423/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/godzilla-kong-finds-director-adam-wingard-1008773#|archive-date=May 31, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2017, Wingard spoke about the outline created by the writers room, stating, \"We're going in very great detail through all the characters, the arcs they have, how they relate to one another, and most importantly how they relate to the monsters, and how the monsters relate to them or reflect them.\" He also stated that he and his team are going \"beat by beat\" on the outline, stating, \"So once again, it's a discussion, and about feeling out how to make it as strong as possible, so that when Terry [Rossio] goes to write the screenplay, he has a definitive breakdown of what to include.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://birthmoviesdeath.com/2017/07/20/adam-wingard-talks-godzilla-vs.-kong-and-directorial-freedom |title=Adam Wingard Talks Godzilla vs. Kong And Directorial Freedom |last=Gingold |first=Michael |work=Birth.Movies.Death |date=July 20, 2017 |accessdate=July 20, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170723234247/http://birthmoviesdeath.com/2017/07/20/adam-wingard-talks-godzilla-vs.-kong-and-directorial-freedom#|archive-date=July 23, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> In August 2017, Wingard spoke about his approach for the monsters, stating:\n\n{{Quote|\"I really want you to take those characters seriously. I want you to be emotionally invested, not just in the human characters, but actually in the monsters. It\u2019s a massive monster brawl movie. There\u2019s lots of monsters going crazy on each other, but at the end of the day I want there to be an emotional drive to it. I want you to be emotionally invested in them. I think that\u2019s what\u2019s going to make it really cool.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://screencrush.com/adam-wingard-godzilla-vs-kong-emotional/ |title=Adam Wingard Wants 'Godzilla vs. Kong' to Make You Cry |last=Whitney |first=E. Oliver |work=Screen Crush |date=August 18, 2017 |accessdate=August 19, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170819034438/http://screencrush.com/adam-wingard-godzilla-vs-kong-emotional/#|archive-date=2017-08-19|url-status=live}}</ref>}} Wingard expressed his desire for the film to have a definite winner, stating:\n\n{{Quote|\u201cI do want there to be a winner. The original film was very fun, but you feel a little let down that the movie doesn\u2019t take a definitive stance. People are still debating now who won in that original movie, you know. So, I do want people to walk away from this film feeling like, Okay, there is a winner.\u201d<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indiewire.com/2017/08/godzilla-vs-kong-adam-wingard-winner-1201868084/ |title=\u2018Godzilla vs. Kong\u2019: Adam Wingard Says the Epic Battle Will Have a Definitive Winner |last=Nordine |first=Michael |work=IndieWire |date=August 20, 2017 |accessdate=January 8, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180109121908/http://www.indiewire.com/2017/08/godzilla-vs-kong-adam-wingard-winner-1201868084/#|archive-date=2018-01-09|url-status=live}}</ref>}}\n\nWingard also confirmed that the film will tie in with ''[[Godzilla: King of the Monsters (2019 film)|Godzilla: King of the Monsters]]'', be set in modern times, and feature a \"more rugged, a bit more aged Kong.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://screenrant.com/godzilla-vs-kong-setting-character-details/?view=lista |title=Godzilla vs. Kong Set in Modern Day, Ties to Godzilla 2 |last=Mithaiwala |first=Mansoor |work=Screen Rant |date=August 22, 2017 |accessdate=August 24, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171224101315/https://screenrant.com/godzilla-vs-kong-setting-character-details/?view=lista#|archive-date=December 24, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Writing===\nIn March 2017, Legendary assembled a writers room to develop the story for ''Godzilla vs. Kong'', with [[Terry Rossio]] (who co-wrote an early unproduced script for [[Godzilla (1998 film)|TriStar's ''Godzilla'']])<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.scifijapan.com/articles/2015/05/10/godzilla-unmade-the-history-of-jan-de-bonts-unproduced-tristar-film-part-1/ |title=Godzilla Unmade: The History of Jan De Bont\u2019s Unproduced TriStar Film \u2013 Part 1 of 4 |last=Aiken |first=Keith |website=Scifi Japan |date=May 10, 2015 |accessdate=May 23, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170915071019/http://www.scifijapan.com/articles/2015/05/10/godzilla-unmade-the-history-of-jan-de-bonts-unproduced-tristar-film-part-1/#|archive-date=September 15, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> leading a team consisting of Patrick McKay, J. D. Payne, Lindsey Beer, Cat Vasko, [[T.S. Nowlin]], Jack Paglen, and [[J. Michael Straczynski]].<ref name=\"writers room\">{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/kong-skull-island-sequel-plans-godzilla-kong-sets-writers-room-984992 |title='Godzilla vs. Kong' Film Sets Writers Room (Exclusive) |last=Kit |first=Borys |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=March 10, 2017 |accessdate=March 10, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170310230537/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/kong-skull-island-sequel-plans-godzilla-kong-sets-writers-room-984992#|archive-date=March 10, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> On his experience with the writers room, Rossio stated:\n\n{{Quote|\"''Godzilla vs. Kong'' was my first experience running a writer's room, and it was fantastic. It was a blast reading samples, meeting different writers, and crafting a story in a group setting. It felt similar to animation, where the film is happening up on the walls, and the end result is better than any one person could accomplish on their own.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/pirates-caribbean-screenwriter-how-a-budget-crisis-changed-villains-1001860 |title=Original 'Pirates of the Caribbean' Screenwriter on How a Budget Crisis Changed the Villains |last=Schoellkopf |first=Christina |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=May 26, 2017 |accessdate=May 27, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170527023430/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/pirates-caribbean-screenwriter-how-a-budget-crisis-changed-villains-1001860#|archive-date=May 27, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>}}\n\n[[Michael Dougherty]] and Zach Shields, the director and co-writers of ''Godzilla: King of the Monsters'', provided rewrites to ensure that certain themes from ''King of the Monsters'' were carried over and that some characters were properly developed.<ref>{{cite web |last=Tyler |first=Jacob |url=https://thegww.com/godzilla-vs-kong-got-rewrites-from-mike-dougherty-zach-shields-godzilla-king-of-the-monsters/ |title=''Godzilla vs. Kong'' Got Rewrites From Mike Dougherty & Zach Shields |date=March 5, 2019 |work=Omega Underground |accessdate=March 13, 2019|url-status=live |archivedate=March 13, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190314023922/https://thegww.com/godzilla-vs-kong-got-rewrites-from-mike-dougherty-zach-shields-godzilla-king-of-the-monsters/}}</ref> Dougherty revealed how he wrote for the title characters, and how the film would address their differing interactions with people. For Kong, Dougherty stated the film would feature \"those very unique, and even warm, bonding moments\" between Kong and humans since they've been a staple of the character since the [[King Kong (1933 film)|1933 film]]. For Godzilla, his connection to humans would be \"more implied\" as his softer side is rarely shown.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://screenrant.com/godzilla-king-kong-different-humanity-connections-explained/ |title=Godzilla 2 Director Explains Godzilla & Kong's Different Connections to Humanity |first=Daniel |last=Alvarez |work=Screen Rant |date=May 5, 2019 |accessdate=May 7, 2019|url-status=live |archivedate=May 7, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190507185131/https://screenrant.com/godzilla-king-kong-different-humanity-connections-explained/}}</ref>\n\n=== Pre-production ===\nIn June 2017, it was announced that [[Ziyi Zhang]] had joined Legendary's MonsterVerse, having a reportedly \"pivotal\" role in both ''Godzilla: King of the Monsters'' and ''Godzilla vs. Kong''.<ref name=\"ZiyiCast\">{{cite web |url=http://deadline.com/2017/06/zhang-ziyi-godzilla-movie-franchise-casting-1202110018/ |title=Zhang Ziyi Comes Aboard 'Godzilla' And Beyond |last=Hipes |first=Patrick |website=Deadline.com |date=June 8, 2017 |accessdate=June 8, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170611233620/http://deadline.com/2017/06/zhang-ziyi-godzilla-movie-franchise-casting-1202110018/#|archive-date=June 11, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> In June 2018, [[Julian Dennison]] was cast alongside Van Marten, while [[Millie Bobby Brown]] and [[Kyle Chandler]] would reprise their roles from ''Godzilla: King of the Monsters''.<ref>{{cite web |last=Perez |first=Lexy |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/deadpool-2-star-julian-dennison-joins-godzilla-kong-1116661 |title=''Deadpool 2'' Star Julian Dennison Joins ''Godzilla vs. Kong'' |date=June 2, 2018 |work=The Hollywood Reporter |accessdate=June 3, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180603033211/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/deadpool-2-star-julian-dennison-joins-godzilla-kong-1116661#|archive-date=June 3, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Legendary also sent an offer to [[Frances McDormand]] for a role.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://thathashtagshow.com/2018/06/exclusive-deadpool-2-julian-dennison-joins-godzilla-vs-kong/ |title=Exclusive: \u2018Deadpool 2\u2019s\u2019 Julian Dennison Joins \u2018Godzilla vs. Kong\u2019 |last=Murphy |first=Charles |work=That Hashtag Show |date=June 1, 2018 |accessdate=June 1, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612143532/http://thathashtagshow.com/2018/06/exclusive-deadpool-2-julian-dennison-joins-godzilla-vs-kong/|archive-date=June 12, 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref> In July 2018, it was revealed that [[Danai Gurira]] was in early talks to join the film.<ref name=\"Danai Guiridia\">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/07/danai-gurira-godzilla-vs-kong-star-trek-the-walking-dead-black-panther-1202425900/ |title=Danai Gurira In Early \u2018Godzilla Vs. Kong\u2019 Talks As \u2018Star Trek\u2019 Also Looms For \u2018Walking Dead\u2019 & \u2018Black Panther\u2019 Star |first=Mike |last=Fleming Jr. |work=Deadline |date=July 12, 2018 |accessdate=July 12, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180713054816/https://deadline.com/2018/07/danai-gurira-godzilla-vs-kong-star-trek-the-walking-dead-black-panther-1202425900/#|archive-date=July 13, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> In October 2018, [[Brian Tyree Henry]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/brian-tyree-henry-godzilla-vs-kong-millie-bobby-brown-1202976259/ |title=Brian Tyree Henry to Co-Star With Millie Bobby Brown in \u2018Godzilla vs. Kong\u2019 (Exclusive) |first=Justin |last=Kroll |work=Variety |date=October 10, 2018 |accessdate=October 10, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181011014559/https://variety.com/2018/film/news/brian-tyree-henry-godzilla-vs-kong-millie-bobby-brown-1202976259/#|archive-date=October 11, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Demi\u00e1n Bichir]],<ref>{{cite web |last=Kit |first=Borys |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/demi-n-bichir-joining-millie-bobby-brown-godzilla-kong-1153121 |title=Demi\u00e1n Bichir Joining Millie Bobby Brown in ''Godzilla vs. Kong'' |date=October 17, 2018 |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |publisher=[[Valence Media]] |accessdate=October 17, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181017213127/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/demi-n-bichir-joining-millie-bobby-brown-godzilla-kong-1153121|archive-date=October 17, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Alexander Skarsg\u00e5rd]],<ref name=\"Skarsg\u00e5rdCast\">{{cite news |last1=Jr |first1=Mike Fleming |title=Alexander Skarsg\u00e5rd To Star In \u2018Godzilla Vs. Kong\u2019 |url=https://deadline.com/2018/10/alexander-skarsgard-to-star-in-godzilla-vs-kong-1202489612/ |accessdate=October 25, 2018 |work=Deadline |date=October 25, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181026064527/https://deadline.com/2018/10/alexander-skarsgard-to-star-in-godzilla-vs-kong-1202489612/# |archive-date=October 26, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref> [[Eiza Gonz\u00e1lez]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/10/eiza-gonzalez-godzilla-vs-king-kong-alexander-skarsgard-1202492406/ |title=Eiza Gonzalez Joins \u2018Godzilla Vs. King Kong |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |first=Mike |last=Fleming Jr |date=October 30, 2018 |accessdate=October 30, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181031052347/https://deadline.com/2018/10/eiza-gonzalez-godzilla-vs-king-kong-alexander-skarsgard-1202492406/#|archive-date=October 31, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> and [[Rebecca Hall]] were added to the cast.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/rebecca-hall-godzilla-vs-kong-1203014950/ |title=Rebecca Hall to Star Opposite Millie Bobby Brown in \u2018Godzilla vs. Kong\u2019 (EXCLUSIVE) |website=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |first=Justin |last=Kroll |date=October 30, 2018 |accessdate=October 30, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181031005404/https://variety.com/2018/film/news/rebecca-hall-godzilla-vs-kong-1203014950/#|archive-date=October 31, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> In November 2018, [[Jessica Henwick]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/jessica-henwick-godzilla-vs-kong-game-of-thrones-1203024081/ |title=\u2018Game of Thrones\u2019 Actress Jessica Henwick Joins \u2018Godzilla vs. Kong\u2019 (Exclusive) |first=Justin |last=Kroll |work=Variety |date=November 8, 2018 |accessdate=November 8, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181109070757/https://variety.com/2018/film/news/jessica-henwick-godzilla-vs-kong-game-of-thrones-1203024081/|archive-date=November 9, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Shun Oguri]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/11/shun-oguri-godzilla-vs-kong-japanese-star-crows-zero-alexander-skarsgard-1202499759/ |title=Japanese Star Shun Oguri Makes Hollywood Debut In \u2018Godzilla Vs. Kong\u2019 |first=Mike |last=Fleming Jr |work=Deadline |date=November 11, 2018 |accessdate=November 11, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181111213802/https://deadline.com/2018/11/shun-oguri-godzilla-vs-kong-japanese-star-crows-zero-alexander-skarsgard-1202499759/#|archive-date=November 11, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> and [[Lance Reddick]] were cast, with Oguri making his Hollywood debut.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2018/11/bosch-lance-reddick-godzilla-vs-kong-1202502022/ |title='Bosch' Actor Lance Reddick Cast in 'Godzilla vs Kong' |website=Deadline |first=Amanda |last=N'Duka |date=November 14, 2018 |accessdate=November 14, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181115030528/https://deadline.com/2018/11/bosch-lance-reddick-godzilla-vs-kong-1202502022/|archive-date=November 15, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n=== Filming ===\n[[Principal photography]] began on November 12, 2018 in [[Hawaii]] and [[Australia]] and was expected to end in February 2019 under the working title ''Apex''.<ref name=\"Press Release\">{{cite web |url=https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20181112005664/en/Warner-Bros.-Pictures%E2%80%99-Legendary-Entertainment%E2%80%99s-Monsterverse-Shifts |title=Warner Bros. Pictures\u2019 and Legendary Entertainment\u2019s Monsterverse Shifts into Overdrive as Cameras Roll on the Next Big-Screen Adventure \"Godzilla Vs. Kong\" |work=Business Wire |date= |accessdate=November 12, 2018 |archivedate=January 19, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190120054526/https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20181112005664/en/Warner-Bros.-Pictures%E2%80%99-Legendary-Entertainment%E2%80%99s-Monsterverse-Shifts|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Prasad |first=R.A |url=https://pursuenews.com/godzilla-vs-kong-working-title-revealed/ |title=Warner Bros. And Legendary Pictures' ''Godzilla Vs. Kong'' Working Title Revealed |date=May 3, 2018 |publisher=PureNews |accessdate=May 3, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180504092023/https://pursuenews.com/godzilla-vs-kong-working-title-revealed/#|archive-date=May 4, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Production was initially slated to begin on October 1, 2018.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Marc |first1=Christopher |title='Godzilla vs Kong' Heading Back To Australia and Hawaii - GWW |url=https://thegww.com/godzilla-vs-kong-heading-back-to-australia-and-hawaii/ |accessdate=July 18, 2018 |work=GWW |date=July 11, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181011053715/https://thegww.com/godzilla-vs-kong-heading-back-to-australia-and-hawaii/# |archive-date=October 11, 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref> For the Hawaii shoot, the crew filmed on the [[USS Missouri (BB-63)|USS ''Missouri'']], at [[Manoa Falls]], and in [[Downtown Honolulu]]. The crew established a camp in the [[Hawaii Route 72|Kalanianaole Highway]], which had been closed until November 21. Local crews and extras were used for the film.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.staradvertiser.com/2018/11/16/hawaii-news/godzilla-vs-kong-filming-in-full-swing-with-upcoming-closures-on-oahu/ |title=\u2018Godzilla vs. Kong\u2019 filming in full swing with upcoming closures on Oahu |first=Nina |last=Wu |work=Star Advertiser |date=November 17, 2018 |accessdate=November 17, 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181117114833/http://www.staradvertiser.com/2018/11/16/hawaii-news/godzilla-vs-kong-filming-in-full-swing-with-upcoming-closures-on-oahu/|archive-date=November 17, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> In January 2019, filming resumed in [[Gold Coast, Queensland]] at [[Village Roadshow Studios]] for an additional 26 weeks.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.brisbanetimes.com.au/national/queensland/godzilla-vs-kong-begins-filming-on-the-gold-coast-20190118-p50s6d.html |title=Godzilla vs. Kong begins filming on the Gold Coast |first=Felicity |last=Caldwell |work=Brisbane Times |date=January 18, 2019 |accessdate=January 19, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190119224354/https://www.brisbanetimes.com.au/national/queensland/godzilla-vs-kong-begins-filming-on-the-gold-coast-20190118-p50s6d.html |archivedate=January 19, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Godzilla sighting down under! |url=https://moviehole.net/godzilla-sighting-down-under/ |website=Moviehole |publisher=Editorial Staff |accessdate=January 24, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190124034500/https://moviehole.net/godzilla-sighting-down-under/ |archive-date=January 24, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nFilming locations in Australia included [[Miami State High School]] and parts of [[Brisbane]] such as the [[Newstead, Queensland|Newstead suburb]], the [[Chinatown, Brisbane|Chinatown Mall in Fortitude Valley]], and the [[Wickham Terrace Car Park]]. In April 2019, Wingard confirmed via [[Instagram]] that filming in Australia had wrapped.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.cinemablend.com/news/2470013/Godzilla-Vs-Kong-Has-Wrapped-In-Australia-According-To-The-Director |title=Godzilla Vs. Kong Has Wrapped In Australia |first=Dirk |last=Libbey |work=Cinema Blend |date=April 9, 2019 |accessdate=April 9, 2019|url-status=live |archivedate=April 9, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190410020411/https://www.cinemablend.com/news/2470013/Godzilla-Vs-Kong-Has-Wrapped-In-Australia-According-To-The-Director}}</ref> That same month, Wingard revealed [[Hong Kong]] as one of the final shooting locations and that principal photography had wrapped.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://ew.com/movies/2019/04/20/godzilla-vs-kong/ |title=Godzilla vs. Kong wraps shooting |first=Clark |last=Collis |work=Entertainment Weekly |date=April 20, 2019 |accessdate=April 20, 2019|url-status=live |archivedate=April 20, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190420223019/https://ew.com/movies/2019/04/20/godzilla-vs-kong/}}</ref>\n\n== Release ==\n===Marketing===\nIn May 2019, the first promotional one-sheet poster was revealed at the Licensing Expo.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://collider.com/godzilla-vs-kong-dune-promo-posters/ |title=New Promo Posters for \u2018Godzilla vs Kong\u2019 and \u2018Dune\u2019 Tease the Titanic 2020 Titles |first=Dave |last=Trumbore |work=Collider |date=May 30, 2019 |accessdate=May 31, 2019|url-status=live |archivedate=May 31, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190531091732/http://collider.com/godzilla-vs-kong-dune-promo-posters/}}</ref> In June 2019, Warner Bros screened an early look to European exhibitors at CineEurope.<ref name=\"CineEurope\">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/06/warner-bros-godzilla-vs-kong-it2-joker-wonder-woman-lionsgate-rian-johnson-knives-out-studiocanal-cineeurope-1202633778/ |title=Warner Bros Teases Horror, DC, \u2018Godzilla Vs Kong\u2019; Studiocanal Goes \u2018Radioactive\u2019 \u2013 CineEurope |first=Nancy |last=Tartaglione |work=Deadline Hollywood |date=June 17, 2019 |accessdate=June 17, 2019|url-status=live |archivedate=June 17, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190618043628/https://deadline.com/2019/06/warner-bros-godzilla-vs-kong-it2-joker-wonder-woman-lionsgate-rian-johnson-knives-out-studiocanal-cineeurope-1202633778/}}</ref> In August 2019, it was announced that Disruptor Beam will develop a mobile game to tie-in for the film's release.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://cosmicbook.news/godzilla-vs-kong-poster-game |title=Godzilla vs. Kong Poster teases one will fall;Game in Development |first=Matt |last=McGloin |work=Cosmic Book News |date=August 10, 2019 |accessdate=August 11, 2019|url-status=live |archivedate=August 11, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190811215337/https://cosmicbook.news/godzilla-vs-kong-poster-game}}</ref> In December 2019, a brief clip was revealed during a Warner Bros. reel at [[Comic Con Experience]], and later leaked online.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cinemablend.com/news/2486314/whoa-kong-punches-godzilla-in-super-brief-but-badass-godzilla-vs-kong-footage|title=Whoa, Kong Punches Godzilla In Super-Brief But Badass Godzilla Vs. Kong Footage|author=Gina Carbone|work=CinemaBlend|date=December 8, 2019|accessdate=December 8, 2019|url-status=live|archivedate=December 8, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191209011305/https://www.cinemablend.com/news/2486314/whoa-kong-punches-godzilla-in-super-brief-but-badass-godzilla-vs-kong-footage}}</ref> In January 2020, images from the Hong Kong Toys & Games Fair displaying figures (including a [[Mechagodzilla]] figure) related to the film were leaked online, sparking speculation whether the film would include Mechagodzilla.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cinemablend.com/news/2487983/godzilla-vs-kong-might-be-bringing-in-an-iconic-kaiju|title=Godzilla Vs. Kong Might Be Bringing In An Iconic Kaiju|author=Adam Holmes|work=Cinema Blend|date=January 7, 2020|accessdate=January 7, 2020|url-status=live|archivedate=January 7, 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200108042635/https://www.cinemablend.com/news/2487983/godzilla-vs-kong-might-be-bringing-in-an-iconic-kaiju}}</ref> In February 2020, Toho and Legendary announced the ''Godzilla vs. Kong'' Publishing Program and licensees. Through the publishing program, Legendary plans to release two graphic novels, an art book, novelizations, and children\u2019s books. Amongst the licensees named were [[Playmates Toys]], Bioworld, Rubies, Funko, 60Out, and the Virtual Reality Company.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.scifijapan.com/articles/2020/02/20/toho-and-legendary-announce-licensees-for-godzilla-vs-kong/|title=Toho and Legendary Announce Licensees for Godzilla vs. Kong|author1=Chris Mowry|author2=Jacara Jenkins|work=SciFi Japan|date=February 20, 2020|accessdate=February 20, 2020|url-status=live|archivedate=February 20, 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200221062043/http://www.scifijapan.com/articles/2020/02/20/toho-and-legendary-announce-licensees-for-godzilla-vs-kong/}}</ref> In April 2019, images of toy figures were leaked online, revealing different forms for Godzilla and Kong, and a new monster.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cinemablend.com/news/2494095/godzilla-vs-kong-merchandise-seemingly-reveals-another-monster-heading-to-the-big-screen|title=Godzilla Vs Kong Merchandise Seemingly Reveals Another Monster Heading To The Big Screen|author=Erik Swann|work=Cinema Blend|date=April 8, 2020|accessdate=April 9, 2020|url-status=live|archivedate=April 9, 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200409221801/https://www.cinemablend.com/news/2494095/godzilla-vs-kong-merchandise-seemingly-reveals-another-monster-heading-to-the-big-screen}}</ref>\n\n===Theatrical===\n''Godzilla vs. Kong'' is scheduled to be released in the United States on November 20, 2020, in 2D, [[3D film|3D]], and [[IMAX]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/godzilla-kong-release-date-pushed-8-months-november-2020-1253500|title='Godzilla vs. Kong' Release Date Pushed 8 Months to November 2020|author=Aaron Couch|work=The Hollywood Reporter|date=November 25, 2019|accessdate=November 25, 2019|url-status=live|archivedate=November 25, 2019|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191126074636/https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/godzilla-kong-release-date-pushed-8-months-november-2020-1253500}}</ref> It will be distributed by [[Warner Bros.|Warner Bros. Pictures]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/02/space-jam-2-release-date-godzilla-vs-kong-annabelle-sequel-warner-bros-1202562428/ |title=Warner Bros Dates \u2018Space Jam 2\u2019, Shifts \u2018Annabelle\u2019 Sequel & \u2018Godzilla Vs. Kong\u2019 |first=Erik |last=Pedersen |work=Deadline |date=February 21, 2019 |accessdate=February 21, 2019|url-status=live |archivedate=February 21, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190222025700/https://deadline.com/2019/02/space-jam-2-release-date-godzilla-vs-kong-annabelle-sequel-warner-bros-1202562428/}}</ref> except in Japan where it will be distributed by [[Toho]].<ref name=\"Press Release\"/> The film was previously scheduled to be released on May 29, May 22, and March 13, 2020.<ref name=\"May10\">{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/warner-bros-moves-dates-godzilla-892634 |title=Warner Bros. Moves Dates For 'Godzilla 2,' 'Godzilla vs Kong' |last=Rahman |first=Abid |work=The Hollywood Reporter |date=May 10, 2016 |accessdate=May 10, 2016|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6pLyTqstH?url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/warner-bros-moves-dates-godzilla-892634#|archive-date=March 30, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/06/warner-studio-toby-emmerich-peter-roth-dc-netflix-godzilla-vs-kong-kevin-tsujihara-1202629538/ |title=Warner Bros. Bosses Toby Emmerich & Peter Roth On Studio Post Kevin Tsujihara In Streaming Era, Disney/Fox & Potential \u2018Godzilla vs. Kong\u2019 Move \u2013 Produced By |first=Anthony |last=D'Alessandro |work=Deadline Hollywood |date=June 8, 2019 |accessdate=June 9, 2019|url-status=live |archivedate=June 9, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190609070404/https://deadline.com/2019/06/warner-studio-toby-emmerich-peter-roth-dc-netflix-godzilla-vs-kong-kevin-tsujihara-1202629538/}}</ref><ref name=\"new date\">{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/02/space-jam-2-release-date-godzilla-vs-kong-annabelle-sequel-warner-bros-1202562428/ |title=Warner Bros Dates \u2018Space Jam 2\u2019, Shifts \u2018Annabelle\u2019 Sequel & \u2018Godzilla Vs. Kong\u2019 |last=Pedersen |first=Erik |work=Deadline |date=February 21, 2019 |accessdate=February 21, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190222025700/https://deadline.com/2019/02/space-jam-2-release-date-godzilla-vs-kong-annabelle-sequel-warner-bros-1202562428/|archive-date=February 22, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Prior to the film's pushed date, Warner Bros. Studio chairman [[Toby Emmerich]] revealed in June 2019 that the film could potentially be pushed back, stating, \"It might come out later in the year, so we can deliver an A+ movie.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://deadline.com/2019/06/warner-studio-toby-emmerich-peter-roth-dc-netflix-godzilla-vs-kong-kevin-tsujihara-1202629538/ |title=Warner Bros. Bosses Toby Emmerich & Peter Roth On Studio Post Kevin Tsujihara In Streaming Era, Disney/Fox & Potential \u2018Godzilla vs. Kong\u2019 Move \u2013 Produced By |first=Anthony |last=D'Alessandro |work=Deadline Hollywood |date=June 8, 2019 |accessdate=June 9, 2019|url-status=live |archivedate=June 9, 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190609070404/https://deadline.com/2019/06/warner-studio-toby-emmerich-peter-roth-dc-netflix-godzilla-vs-kong-kevin-tsujihara-1202629538/}}</ref> In February 2020, Warner Bros. hosted an unannounced test screening, which received a positive response.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cinemablend.com/news/2491108/check-out-godzilla-vs-kongs-directors-cryptic-post-following-reported-test-screening|title=Check Out Godzilla Vs. Kong's Director\u2019s Cryptic Post Following Reported Test Screening|author=Adam Holmes|work=Cinema Blend|date=February 28, 2020|accessdate=March 11, 2020|url-status=live|archivedate=March 11, 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200312012236/https://www.cinemablend.com/news/2491108/check-out-godzilla-vs-kongs-directors-cryptic-post-following-reported-test-screening}}</ref>\n\n== Notes ==\n{{Notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n=== Citations ===\n{{Reflist|refs=}}\n\n=== Bibliography ===\n* {{cite book |last=Kalat |first=David |year=2010 |title=A Critical History and Filmography of Toho's Godzilla Series - Second Edition |publisher=McFarland |isbn=9780786447497 |ref=harv}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|5034838|Godzilla vs. Kong}}\n{{MonsterVerse}}\n{{Godzilla}}\n{{KingKong}}\n{{Adam Wingard}}\n\n[[Category:Upcoming films]]\n[[Category:2020 films]]\n[[Category:2020 3D films]]\n[[Category:2020s monster movies]]\n[[Category:2020s sequel films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American 3D films]]\n[[Category:Crossover films]]\n[[Category:Films set in the Atlantic Ocean]]\n[[Category:Films set in Berlin]]\n[[Category:Films set in Brisbane]]\n[[Category:Films set in Hawaii]]\n[[Category:Films set in Hong Kong]]\n[[Category:Films set in Honolulu]]\n[[Category:Films set in London]]\n[[Category:Films set in Moscow]]\n[[Category:Films set in the Pacific Ocean]]\n[[Category:Films set in Paris]]\n[[Category:Films set in Rome]]\n[[Category:Films set in Seoul]]\n[[Category:Films set in Shanghai]]\n[[Category:Films set in Sydney]]\n[[Category:Films set in Taiwan]]\n[[Category:Films set in Tokyo]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Brisbane]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Hawaii]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Hong Kong]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Honolulu]]\n[[Category:Godzilla films]]\n[[Category:Kaiju films]]\n[[Category:King Kong films]]\n[[Category:Legendary Pictures films]]\n[[Category:MonsterVerse]]\n[[Category:Films with screenplays by Terry Rossio]]\n[[Category:Toho films]]\n[[Category:Upcoming sequel films]]\n[[Category:Warner Bros. films]]\n", "name_user": "88.1.142.92", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eFilming)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Godzilla_vs._Kong"}
{"title_page": "Alan Dillon", "text_new": "{{short description|Irish Fine Gael politician|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name         = Alan Dillon\n| honorific-suffix = [[Teachta D\u00e1la|TD]]\n| image        = Alan Dillon 2020.jpg\n| caption      = Dillon in 2020\n| office       = [[Teachta D\u00e1la]]\n| term_start   = [[2020 Irish general election|February 2020]]\n| term_end     =  \n| constituency = [[Mayo (D\u00e1il constituency)|Mayo]]\n| birth_date   = {{birth date and age|1982|9|28|df=y}}\n| birth_place  = [[Castlebar]], [[County Mayo]], Ireland\n| death_date   =\n| death_place  =\n| nationality  = [[Irish people|Irish]]\n| party        = [[Fine Gael]]\n| spouse       = Ashling Dillon {{small|(m. 2014)}}\n| children     = 1\n| education    = [[Davitt College]]\n| alma_mater   = {{Ubl|[[NUI Galway]]|[[Maynooth University]]|[[Royal College of Surgeons in Ireland|RCSI]]}}\n|}}\n{{infobox GAA player\n|image          =\n|name           = Alan Dillon\n|height         = {{convert|1.81|m|ftin|0|abbr=on}}\n|sport          = Gaelic Football\n|code           = Football\n|county         = Mayo\n|province       = Connacht\n|club           = [[Ballintubber GAA|Ballintubber]]\n|clyears        = 1999\u2013\n|clposition     = Centre Forward\n|clapps(points) =\n|clcounty       = 5\n|clprovince     =\n|clallireland   =\n|counties       = [[Mayo GAA|Mayo]]\n|icyears        = 2003\u20132017\n|icposition     = Left Half Forward\n|icapps(points) = 134 (3\u2013225)\n|icprovince     = 8\n|icallireland   =\n|nfl            =\n|allstars       = 2\n|clupdate       = \n|icupdate       = 28 November 2017\n|}}\n'''Alan Dillon''' (born 28 September 1982) is an Irish [[Fine Gael]] politician who has been a [[Teachta D\u00e1la]] (TD) for the [[Mayo (D\u00e1il constituency)|Mayo]] constituency since the [[2020 Irish general election|2020 general election]].<ref name=oireachtas_db>{{cite web|url=https://www.oireachtas.ie/en/members/member/Alan-Dillon.D.2020-02-08/|title=Alan Dillon|work=Oireachtas Members Database|access-date=15 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nPrevious to entering politics, he was a two time [[GAA All Stars Awards|All Star]] winning [[Gaelic football]]er for [[Mayo GAA|Mayo]] and a captain of the Mayo senior Gaelic football team.<ref>{{cite web|title=Dillon to captain Mayo|url=http://www.hoganstand.com/ArticleForm.aspx?ID=146597|publisher=Hoganstand.com|accessdate=2011-05-27|date=2011-05-20}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Dillon to captain Mayo|url=http://www.hoganstand.com/ArticleForm.aspx?ID=146597|publisher=Hoganstand.com|accessdate=2011-05-27 |date=2011-05-20}}</ref>\n\n==Gaelic football career==\nHe played football with his local club [[Ballintubber GAA|Ballintubber]] in [[County Mayo]] and was a pivotal member of the [[Mayo GAA|Mayo]] senior football team from 2003 until his retirement in 2017, playing in 6 [[All-Ireland Senior Football Championship|All-Ireland finals]]. His fine-tuned skill, his sharp roving eye and his clever reading of the game all contribute to his exceptional footballing abilities. Dillon won his first All Star award in 2006<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rte.ie/sport/2006/1122/allstars.html|title=Champions Kerry top All Star list|date=22 November 2006|accessdate=27 May 2011|website=[[RT\u00c9]]}}</ref> and a second All Star award in 2012.\n\n===Retirement===\nOn 28 November 2017, Dillon announced his retirement from inter-county football.<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.the42.ie/alan-dillon-retires-inter-county-football-mayo-3720108-Nov2017/ |title=Eight-time Connacht champion Alan Dillon calls time on his Mayo career|date=27 November 2017|work=The 42|accessdate=28 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.irishtimes.com/sport/gaelic-games/ciar%C3%A1n-murphy-alan-dillon-leaves-knowing-he-gave-it-his-all-1.3309787|title=Ciar\u00e1n Murphy: Alan Dillon leaves knowing he gave it his all|first=Ciaran|last=Murphy|website=The Irish Times}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|url=https://www.rte.ie/sport/gaa/2017/1128/923311-alan-dillon-calls-it-a-day-with-mayo/|title=Alan Dillon calls it a day with Mayo|date=November 28, 2017|via=www.rte.ie}}</ref>\n\n==Politics==\nFollowing his retirement from inter-county football in 2017, there was much speculation that Dillon would replace former [[Taoiseach]] [[Enda Kenny]] as a [[Fine Gael]] candidate for Mayo.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejournal.ie/alan-dillon-fine-gael-3727918-Dec2017/|title=Mayo GAA star lined up for general election bid to replace Enda Kenny|first=Christina|last=Finn|website=TheJournal.ie}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mayonews.ie/news/31209-fine-gael-and-footballer-alan-dillon-in-talks-about-surprise-general-election-bid-2|title=Fine Gael and Alan Dillon in talks about surprise General Election bid|website=www.mayonews.ie}}</ref> In January 2018, Dillon announced his intention not to stand for [[2019 Irish local elections|local elections in Januray 2019]].\n\nHe has numerous links to Fine Gael, an aunt having been Enda Kenny's Castlebar secretary and her husband being Kenny's driver and a county councillor.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.irishexaminer.com/sport/gaa/alan-dillon-bring-our-people-home-467553.html|title=Alan Dillon: Bring our people home|date=February 24, 2018|website=www.irishexaminer.com}}</ref> In 2020, he successfully stood as a Fine Gael candidate for the [[2020 Irish general election]] in the [[Mayo (D\u00e1il constituency)|Mayo constituency]].\n\n==Personal life==\nHe is married to Ashling, and they have one son. Dillon has participated in a marketing campaign for [[Ireland West Airport Knock]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.donegaldemocrat.ie/lifestyle/home-and-garden/donegal-gaa-stars-join-forces-as-ambassadors-for-ireland-west-airport-knock-1-5086123|title=Donegal GAA stars join forces as Ambassadors for Ireland West Airport Knock|newspaper=Donegal Democrat|publisher=Johnston Press|date=13 May 2013|accessdate=13 May 2013}}</ref> Dillon attended [[Davitt College]] in Castlebar for his Secondary school education.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mayonews.ie/sports/31206-alan-dillon-the-man-who-made-it-look-easy|title=Alan Dillon, the man who made it look easy|website=www.mayonews.ie}}</ref> He studied at [[NUI Galway]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nuigalway.ie/about-us/news-and-events/news-archive/2013/september2013/nui-galway-students-and-alumni-head-for-croke-park-with-mayo-senior-football-finalists-.html|title=NUI Galway students and alumni head for Croke Park with Mayo senior football finalists|date=17 September 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161217102433/https://www.nuigalway.ie/about-us/news-and-events/news-archive/2013/september2013/nui-galway-students-and-alumni-head-for-croke-park-with-mayo-senior-football-finalists-.html|archivedate=17 December 2016}}</ref> and played for [[NUI Galway GAA|the university football team]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.ie/sport/gaelic-games/gaelic-football/gardiner-digs-deep-to-bury-it-sligo-26705879.html|title=Gardiner digs deep to bury IT Sligo|newspaper=Irish Independent|date=18 February 2011|accessdate=18 February 2011}}</ref> Dillon has a M.Sc. in Pharmaceutical Science from the Royal College of Surgeons Ireland, a Postgraduate Diploma in Education from [[NUI Galway]], and a B.Sc. in Applied Mathematics and Biology from [[Maynooth University]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://election2020.finegael.ie/candidates/alan-dillon |title=Alan Dillon |author=<!--Not stated--> |date= |website=finegael.ie |publisher= |access-date=10 February 2020 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Navboxes|title=Alan Dillon GAA career navigational boxes|list1=\n{{Mayo Football Team 2004}}\n{{Mayo Football Team 2006}}\n{{Mayo Football Team 2012}}\n{{Mayo Football Team 2013}}\n{{Mayo Football Team 2016}}\n{{Mayo Football Team 2017}}\n{{2006 All Stars}}\n{{2012 All Stars}}\n}}\n{{Fine Gael}}\n{{Current TDs}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dillon, Alan}}\n[[Category:1982 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Alumni of NUI Galway]]\n[[Category:Alumni of St Patrick's College, Maynooth]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the Royal College of Surgeons in Ireland]]\n[[Category:Ballintubber Gaelic footballers]]\n[[Category:Fine Gael TDs]]\n[[Category:Irish sportsperson-politicians]]\n[[Category:Mayo inter-county Gaelic footballers]]\n[[Category:Members of the 33rd D\u00e1il]]\n[[Category:NUI Galway Gaelic footballers]]\n[[Category:People from Castlebar]]\n[[Category:Politicians from County Mayo]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Irish Fine Gael politician|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name         = Alan Dillon\n| honorific-suffix = [[Teachta D\u00e1la|TD]]\n| image        = Alan Dillon 2020.jpg\n| caption      = Dillon in 2020\n| office       = [[Teachta D\u00e1la]]\n| term_start   = [[2020 Irish general election|February 2020]]\n| term_end     =  \n| constituency = [[Mayo (D\u00e1il constituency)|Mayo]]\n| birth_date   = {{birth date and age|1982|9|28|df=y}}\n| birth_place  = [[Castlebar]], [[County Mayo]], Ireland\n| death_date   =\n| death_place  =\n| nationality  = [[Irish people|Irish]]\n| party        = [[Fine Gael]]\n| spouse       = Ashling Dillon {{small|(m. 2014)}}\n| children     = 1\n| education    = [[Davitt College]]\n| alma_mater   = {{Ubl|[[NUI Galway]]|[[Maynooth University]]|[[Royal College of Surgeons in Ireland|RCSI]]}}\n|}}\n{{infobox GAA player\n|image          =\n|name           = Alan Dillon\n|height         = {{convert|1.81|m|ftin|0|abbr=on}}\n|sport          = Gaelic Football\n|code           = Football\n|county         = Mayo\n|province       = Connacht\n|club           = [[Ballintubber GAA|Ballintubber]]\n|clyears        = 1999\u2013\n|clposition     = Centre Forward\n|clapps(points) =\n|clcounty       = 5\n|clprovince     =\n|clallireland   =\n|counties       = [[Mayo GAA|Mayo]]\n|icyears        = 2003\u20132017\n|icposition     = Left Half Forward\n|icapps(points) = 134 (3\u2013225)\n|icprovince     = 8\n|icallireland   =\n|nfl            =\n|allstars       = 2\n|clupdate       = \n|icupdate       = 28 November 2017\n|}}\n'''Alan Dillon''' (born 28 September 1982) is an Irish [[Fine Gael]] politician who has been a [[Teachta D\u00e1la]] (TD) for the [[Mayo (D\u00e1il constituency)|Mayo]] constituency since the [[2020 Irish general election|2020 general election]].<ref name=oireachtas_db>{{cite web|url=https://www.oireachtas.ie/en/members/member/Alan-Dillon.D.2020-02-08/|title=Alan Dillon|work=Oireachtas Members Database|access-date=15 February 2020}}</ref>\n\nPrevious to entering politics, he was a two time [[GAA All Stars Awards|All Star]] winning [[Gaelic football]]er for [[Mayo GAA|Mayo]] and a captain of the Mayo senior Gaelic football team.<ref>{{cite web|title=Dillon to captain Mayo|url=http://www.hoganstand.com/ArticleForm.aspx?ID=146597|publisher=Hoganstand.com|accessdate=2011-05-27|date=2011-05-20}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Dillon to captain Mayo|url=http://www.hoganstand.com/ArticleForm.aspx?ID=146597|publisher=Hoganstand.com|accessdate=2011-05-27 |date=2011-05-20}}</ref>\n\n==Gaelic football career==\nHe played football with his local club [[Ballintubber GAA|Ballintubber]] in [[County Mayo]] and was a pivotal member of the [[Mayo GAA|Mayo]] senior football team from 2003 until his retirement in 2017, playing in 6 [[All-Ireland Senior Football Championship|All-Ireland finals]]. His fine-tuned skill, his sharp roving eye and his clever reading of the game all contribute to his exceptional footballing abilities. Dillon won his first All Star award in 2006<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rte.ie/sport/2006/1122/allstars.html|title=Champions Kerry top All Star list|date=22 November 2006|accessdate=27 May 2011|website=[[RT\u00c9]]}}</ref> and a second All Star award in 2012.\n\n===Retirement===\nOn 28 November 2017, Dillon announced his retirement from inter-county football.<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.the42.ie/alan-dillon-retires-inter-county-football-mayo-3720108-Nov2017/ |title=Eight-time Connacht champion Alan Dillon calls time on his Mayo career|date=27 November 2017|work=The 42|accessdate=28 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.irishtimes.com/sport/gaelic-games/ciar%C3%A1n-murphy-alan-dillon-leaves-knowing-he-gave-it-his-all-1.3309787|title=Ciar\u00e1n Murphy: Alan Dillon leaves knowing he gave it his all|first=Ciaran|last=Murphy|website=The Irish Times}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|url=https://www.rte.ie/sport/gaa/2017/1128/923311-alan-dillon-calls-it-a-day-with-mayo/|title=Alan Dillon calls it a day with Mayo|date=November 28, 2017|via=www.rte.ie}}</ref>\n\n==Politics==\nFollowing his retirement from inter-county football in 2017, there was much speculation that Dillon would replace former [[Taoiseach]] [[Enda Kenny]] as a [[Fine Gael]] candidate for Mayo.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thejournal.ie/alan-dillon-fine-gael-3727918-Dec2017/|title=Mayo GAA star lined up for general election bid to replace Enda Kenny|first=Christina|last=Finn|website=TheJournal.ie}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mayonews.ie/news/31209-fine-gael-and-footballer-alan-dillon-in-talks-about-surprise-general-election-bid-2|title=Fine Gael and Alan Dillon in talks about surprise General Election bid|website=www.mayonews.ie}}</ref> In January 2018, Dillon announced his intention to stand for [[2019 Irish local elections|local elections in 2019]], but later decided not to run. \n\nHe has numerous links to Fine Gael, an aunt having been Enda Kenny's Castlebar secretary and her husband being Kenny's driver and a county councillor.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.irishexaminer.com/sport/gaa/alan-dillon-bring-our-people-home-467553.html|title=Alan Dillon: Bring our people home|date=February 24, 2018|website=www.irishexaminer.com}}</ref> In 2020, he successfully stood as a Fine Gael candidate for the [[2020 Irish general election]] in the [[Mayo (D\u00e1il constituency)|Mayo constituency]].\n\n==Personal life==\nHe is married to Ashling, and they have one son. Dillon has participated in a marketing campaign for [[Ireland West Airport Knock]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.donegaldemocrat.ie/lifestyle/home-and-garden/donegal-gaa-stars-join-forces-as-ambassadors-for-ireland-west-airport-knock-1-5086123|title=Donegal GAA stars join forces as Ambassadors for Ireland West Airport Knock|newspaper=Donegal Democrat|publisher=Johnston Press|date=13 May 2013|accessdate=13 May 2013}}</ref> Dillon attended [[Davitt College]] in Castlebar for his Secondary school education.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mayonews.ie/sports/31206-alan-dillon-the-man-who-made-it-look-easy|title=Alan Dillon, the man who made it look easy|website=www.mayonews.ie}}</ref> He studied at [[NUI Galway]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nuigalway.ie/about-us/news-and-events/news-archive/2013/september2013/nui-galway-students-and-alumni-head-for-croke-park-with-mayo-senior-football-finalists-.html|title=NUI Galway students and alumni head for Croke Park with Mayo senior football finalists|date=17 September 2013|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161217102433/https://www.nuigalway.ie/about-us/news-and-events/news-archive/2013/september2013/nui-galway-students-and-alumni-head-for-croke-park-with-mayo-senior-football-finalists-.html|archivedate=17 December 2016}}</ref> and played for [[NUI Galway GAA|the university football team]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.ie/sport/gaelic-games/gaelic-football/gardiner-digs-deep-to-bury-it-sligo-26705879.html|title=Gardiner digs deep to bury IT Sligo|newspaper=Irish Independent|date=18 February 2011|accessdate=18 February 2011}}</ref> Dillon has a M.Sc. in Pharmaceutical Science from the Royal College of Surgeons Ireland, a Postgraduate Diploma in Education from [[NUI Galway]], and a B.Sc. in Applied Mathematics and Biology from [[Maynooth University]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://election2020.finegael.ie/candidates/alan-dillon |title=Alan Dillon |author=<!--Not stated--> |date= |website=finegael.ie |publisher= |access-date=10 February 2020 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Navboxes|title=Alan Dillon GAA career navigational boxes|list1=\n{{Mayo Football Team 2004}}\n{{Mayo Football Team 2006}}\n{{Mayo Football Team 2012}}\n{{Mayo Football Team 2013}}\n{{Mayo Football Team 2016}}\n{{Mayo Football Team 2017}}\n{{2006 All Stars}}\n{{2012 All Stars}}\n}}\n{{Fine Gael}}\n{{Current TDs}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dillon, Alan}}\n[[Category:1982 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Alumni of NUI Galway]]\n[[Category:Alumni of St Patrick's College, Maynooth]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the Royal College of Surgeons in Ireland]]\n[[Category:Ballintubber Gaelic footballers]]\n[[Category:Fine Gael TDs]]\n[[Category:Irish sportsperson-politicians]]\n[[Category:Mayo inter-county Gaelic footballers]]\n[[Category:Members of the 33rd D\u00e1il]]\n[[Category:NUI Galway Gaelic footballers]]\n[[Category:People from Castlebar]]\n[[Category:Politicians from County Mayo]]\n", "name_user": "2001:bb6:14df:1958:d05:7595:23d6:21c2", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200ePolitics)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alan_Dillon"}
{"title_page": "Angelo Peruzzi", "text_new": "{{short description|Italian footballer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2019}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name               = Angelo Peruzzi\n| image              = Angelo Peruzzi.JPG\n| image_size         = 250\n| caption            = Peruzzi in 2010\n| fullname           = Angelo Peruzzi\n| height             = {{height|m=1.81}}<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gazzetta.it/speciali/mondiali/2006/giocatori/69.shtml|title=Mondiali Calcio 2006|newspaper=[[La Gazzetta dello Sport]]|accessdate=15 January 2015}}</ref>\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1970|2|16}}\n| birth_place        = [[Blera]], [[Viterbo]], Italy\n| currentclub        = \n| position           = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]]\n| years1             = 1986\u20131989 |clubs1 = [[A.S. Roma|Roma]]                   |caps1 = 13  |goals1 = 0\n| years2             = 1989\u20131990 |clubs2 = [[Hellas Verona F.C.|Hellas Verona]] |caps2 = 29  |goals2 = 0\n| years3             = 1990\u20131991 |clubs3 = [[A.S. Roma|Roma]]                   |caps3 = 3   |goals3 = 0\n| years4             = 1991\u20131999 |clubs4 = [[Juventus F.C.|Juventus]]           |caps4 = 208 |goals4 = 0\n| years5             = 1999\u20132000 |clubs5 = [[Inter Milan|Internazionale]]       |caps5 = 33  |goals5 = 0\n| years6             = 2000\u20132007 |clubs6 = [[S.S. Lazio|Lazio]]                 |caps6 = 192 |goals6 = 0\n| totalcaps          = 478       |totalgoals = 0\n| nationalyears1 = 1989\u20131992 |nationalteam1 = [[Italy national under-21 football team|Italy U-21]] |nationalcaps1 = 10 |nationalgoals1 = 0\n| nationalyears2 = 1995\u20132006 |nationalteam2 = [[Italy national football team|Italy]]               |nationalcaps2 = 31 |nationalgoals2 = 0\n| medaltemplates = {{MedalCountry|{{ITA}}}}\n{{MedalSport |Association football}}\n{{MedalCompetition |[[FIFA World Cup]]}}\n{{Medal|Winner|[[2006 FIFA World Cup|Germany 2006]]|}}\n}}\n\n'''Angelo Peruzzi''' {{postnominals|post-noms=[[Order of Merit of the Italian Republic|Ufficiale OMRI]]}}<ref>[https://www.fifa.com/en/organisation/president/index/0,4095,129202,00.html?articleid=129202 FIFA.com] {{dead link|date=June 2016|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref><ref>[http://www.ascotsportal.com/news/newsdtl.aspx?PID=89262e2c-3beb-4080-bd5e-949f498ecbcc&CID=4ca0fc99-f8bf-4260-b379-ee5bca3085eb&NID=e47baa4d-fe98-4feb-a0ff-a007b8e62e87 AscotSportal.com] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070928185818/http://www.ascotsportal.com/news/newsdtl.aspx?PID=89262e2c-3beb-4080-bd5e-949f498ecbcc&CID=4ca0fc99-f8bf-4260-b379-ee5bca3085eb&NID=e47baa4d-fe98-4feb-a0ff-a007b8e62e87 |date=28 September 2007 }}</ref> ({{IPA-it|\u02c8and\u0292elo pe\u02c8ruttsi}}; born 16 February 1970) is an Italian [[Manager (association football)|football coach]] and former [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]], and a three-time winner of the [[Serie A Goalkeeper of the Year]] award. He is currently team manager for [[S.S. Lazio|Lazio]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sportmediaset.mediaset.it/calcio/lazio/lazio-peruzzi-si-presenta-qui-per-risolvere-situazioni-negative-_1110903-201602a.shtml|title=Lazio, Peruzzi si presenta: \"Qui per risolvere situazioni negative\" - Sportmediaset|website=Sportmediaset.it|access-date=31 July 2016}}</ref>\n\nPeruzzi is regarded by pundits as one of the greatest Italian goalkeepers of all time,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/iffhs-century.html#eukoy |title=IFFHS' Century Elections - Europe - Keeper of the Century |website=[[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation]] |accessdate=14 January 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160112150635/http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/iffhs-century.html |archivedate=12 January 2016}}</ref> and as one of the best goalkeepers of his generation.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.repubblica.it/sport/calcio/2012/01/25/news/buffon_miglio_portiere_25_anni-28741113/|title=Buffon miglior portiere degli ultimi 25 anni|newspaper=[[la Repubblica]]|date=25 January 2012|accessdate=7 July 2015|language=Italian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/iffhs-gkoy97.html|title=IFFHS' World's Best Goalkeeper of the Year 1997|website=[[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation]]|accessdate=14 January 2016}}</ref><ref name=corsport>{{cite news|author=Furio Zara|url=http://www.corrieredellosport.it/625/2011/02/16-156120/Peruzzi%2C+il+cinghialone+che+parava+tutto|title=Peruzzi, il cinghialone che parava tutto|newspaper=[[Corriere dello Sport]]|date=16 February 2011|accessdate=8 July 2015|language=italian|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150525162017/http://www.corrieredellosport.it/625/2011/02/16-156120/Peruzzi%2C+il+cinghialone+che+parava+tutto|archivedate=25 May 2015}}</ref> Throughout his career, he played for Italian clubs [[A.S. Roma|Roma]], [[Hellas Verona F.C.|Hellas Verona]], [[Juventus F.C.|Juventus]], [[Inter Milan|Internazionale]] and [[S.S. Lazio|Lazio]]. He had a highly successful spell with Juventus, where he won three [[Serie A]] titles, the [[Coppa Italia]], the [[UEFA Europa League|UEFA Cup]] and the [[UEFA Champions League]], among other titles; he won a second Coppa Italia with Lazio before retiring with the club in 2007. At international level, he played 31 times for the [[Italy national football team|Italy national team]] from his debut in 1995, and was a member of their squad which won the [[2006 FIFA World Cup]]. He also represented them at the [[Football at the 1992 Summer Olympics|1992 Olympics]], at [[UEFA Euro 1996]] (as a starting goalkeeper), and at [[UEFA Euro 2004|Euro 2004]].\n\n==Club career==\nPeruzzi began his [[Serie A]] career with [[A.S. Roma|Roma]] in 1987. He was loaned to [[Hellas Verona F.C.|Hellas Verona]] in 1989, but was one of the two Roma players (the other being [[Andrea Carnevale]]) to be suspended for a year in October 1990 after failing a doping test because of an appetite suppressant he was taking at the time, which contained the banned substance [[Phentermine]].<ref name=\"Peruzzi, il doping e quel gol fantasma\"/> His signing with [[Juventus F.C.|Juventus]] in 1991 successfully revived his career and he soon surpassed [[Stefano Tacconi]] as the club's starting goalkeeper, remaining with the team until 1999, and winning the [[Serie A Goalkeeper of the Year]] Award in 1997 and 1998, as well as the [[Guerin d'oro]] in 1997. Peruzzi won three Serie A titles, a [[Coppa Italia]], two [[Supercoppa Italiana]] titles, a [[UEFA Europa League|UEFA Cup]], a [[UEFA Super Cup]], an [[Intercontinental Cup (football)|Intercontinental Cup]] and was part of Juventus' 1996 [[UEFA Champions League]] title squad that defeated [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]] in the final on penalties, saving two in the [[1996 UEFA Champions League Final|final shoot-out]]. He also reached two more consecutive Champions League finals with the [[Turin]]-based club, as well as a semi-final finish during his final season with the club. Peruzzi also won a runners-up medal in the [[1995 UEFA Cup Final|1995 UEFA Cup final]] and in the [[1992 Coppa Italia Final|1992 Coppa Italia final]], and was voted to the [[European Sports Magazines#ESM Team of the Year|ESM Team of the Year]] during the [[European Sports Media#1996.E2.80.9397|1996\u201397]] and the [[European Sports Media#1997.E2.80.9398|1997\u201398]] seasons. Over this period, several pundits began to consider him one of the most reliable goalkeepers in the world, if not the best one, due to his consistency, with Maurizio Crosetti describing him as \"the best goalkeeper in the world\" in 1997.<ref name=\"Angelo Peruzzi - Gazzetta\">{{cite news|url=http://archiviostorico.gazzetta.it//1997/ottobre/18/Angelo_Peruzzi_gm_0_9710181225.shtml|title=Angelo Peruzzi|newspaper=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=Italian|author=Salvatore Lo Presti|date=18 October 1997|accessdate=28 October 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"VITA DA DIMENTICATI\">{{cite news|url=http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/1997/09/16/peruzzi-konsel-vita-da-dimenticati.html|title=Peruzzi e Konsel, vita da dimenticati|newspaper=la Repubblica|author=Maurizio Crosetti|language=Italian|date=16 September 1997|accessdate=28 October 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"Ottimo Peruzzi\">{{cite news|url=http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/1997/04/07/ottimo-peruzzi-baresi-reiziger-in-picchiata.html|title=Ottimo Peruzzi, Baresi e Reiziger in picchiata|newspaper=la Repubblica|language=Italian|author=Licia Granello|date=7 April 1997|accessdate=28 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the departure [[Gianluca Pagliuca]], Peruzzi's perceived career rival in his position, from [[Inter Milan|Internazionale]] to [[Bologna F.C. 1909|Bologna]] in 1999,<ref name=\"Peruzzi para le cattiverie\">{{cite web|url=http://archiviostorico.gazzetta.it/1999/luglio/10/Peruzzi_para_cattiverie_ga_0_9907103110.shtml|title=Peruzzi para le cattiverie|publisher=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=Italian|author1=Nicola Cecere|date=10 July 1999|accessdate=29 October 2017}}</ref> Peruzzi left Juventus for Inter in 1999 on a 28&nbsp;billion lire (\u20ac14.461&nbsp;million) transfer fee,<ref name=Inter2000bilancio>F.C. Internazionale Milano S.p.A. ''bilancio'' (financial report and accounts) on 30 June 2000, PDF purchased from Italian [[Camera di Commercio, Industria, Agricoltura e Artigianato|C.C.I.A.A.]](in Italian)</ref> and a reported 8&nbsp;billion lire pre-tax wage.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://archiviostorico.gazzetta.it//1999/giugno/28/Inter_scommessa_200_miliardi_ga_0_9906286686.shtml|title=Inter, scommessa da 200 miliardi|date=28 June 1999|access-date=2 July 2017|work=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=Italian|quote=...Inseguendo Peruzzi, la societa' deve adesso affrontare un sacrificio di trentasei miliardi: ventotto del cartellino e otto di ingaggio lordo...}}</ref> Peruzzi spent one unsuccessful season with the club \u2013 despite his excellent performances<ref>{{cite news|url=http://archiviostorico.gazzetta.it/2000/maggio/03/Nessuno_insidia_sua_maesta_Peruzzi_ga_0_00050314121.shtml|title=Nessuno insidia sua maest\u00e0 Peruzzi|newspaper=La Gazzetta dello Sport|date=3 May 2000|language=Italian}}</ref> \u2013, under his former Juventus manager [[Marcello Lippi]], finishing the [[1999\u20132000 Serie A|league season]] in fourth place, and reaching the [[2000 Coppa Italia Final|Coppa Italia final]].\n\nThe following season, he transferred to [[S.S. Lazio|Lazio]] for 40&nbsp;billion lire (\u20ac20.658&nbsp;million; in cash plus [[Marco Ballotta]] deal),<ref name=Inter2000bilancio/><ref>{{cite news|url=http://archiviostorico.gazzetta.it//2000/giugno/09/Peruzzi_alla_Lazio_adesso_fatta_ga_0_0006099872.shtml|title=Peruzzi alla Lazio, adesso \u00e8 fatta|date=9 June 2000|access-date=2 July 2017|work=La Gazzetta dello Sport|publisher=RCS MediaGroup|language=Italian}}</ref> and made over 200 appearances in Serie A and European competitions with the club, winning the [[2000 Supercoppa Italiana|Supercoppa Italiana in 2000]] and the Coppa Italia in [[2004 Coppa Italia Final|2004]]. He kept playing at a very high level, being generally considered the best Italian goalkeeper behind [[Gianluigi Buffon]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Le \u00abuscite\u00bb di Peruzzi e i dubbi della societ\u00e0|author=Luca Valdiserri|newspaper=Corriere della Sera|p=47|date=15 August 2003|language=Italian}}</ref>\n\nAlthough his contract with the ''Biancocelesti'' ran until 2008, Peruzzi retired at the end of the [[2006\u201307 S.S. Lazio season|2006\u201307 season]]: after the 0\u20130 draw with Roma 29 April 2007, Peruzzi stated that he had played his last match due to the frustration of nagging injuries. However, he was put on in the final few minutes in Lazio's final home match of the season, a goalless draw against [[Parma Calcio 1913|Parma]] on 20 May, as a goodbye to the fans. He was named the Serie A Goalkeeper of the Year for the third time in his career on 28 January 2008.\n\n==International career==\nPeruzzi was [[cap (football)|capped]] 31 times in 11 years with [[Italy national football team|Italy]], between 1995 and 2006. He was also a member of the national squad that competed at the [[1992 Summer Olympics]] in [[Barcelona]], making two appearances during the tournament. Peruzzi made his senior debut under manager [[Arrigo Sacchi]], in a 4\u20131 home win over [[Estonia national football team|Estonia]], in an [[UEFA Euro 1996 qualifying]] match, on 25 March 1995, and he was named Italy's starting goalkeeper at [[1996 UEFA European Football Championship|Euro 1996]], although Italy suffered a group-stage elimination. He was scheduled to be the starter at the [[1998 FIFA World Cup]] under [[Cesare Maldini]], but suffered a late injury<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www2.raisport.rai.it/news/eventi/francia98/199805/31/35713fbc05fc2/|title=Francia 1998: Peruzzi infortunato|website=Rai.it|language=Italian|date=31 May 1998|accessdate=15 July 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150706011322/http://www2.raisport.rai.it/news/eventi/francia98/199805/31/35713fbc05fc2/|archive-date=6 July 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> and was replaced in the starting line-up by Gianluca Pagliuca.<ref name=\"Peruzzi para le cattiverie\"/>\n\nAfter the 1998 World Cup, Maldini was replaced by Italy's former goalkeeper and record-setter [[Dino Zoff]], who confirmed Peruzzi as first-choice goalkeeper during his first year as Italy's coach. Nonetheless, after a match against [[Norway national football team|Norway]] in 1999, Zoff decided to give Gianluigi Buffon the starting spot, and Peruzzi, who was overtaken even by [[Francesco Toldo]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/1999/agosto/31/Zoff_convoca_Del_Piero_boccia_co_0_9908311530.shtml|title=Zoff convoca Del Piero e boccia ancora Peruzzi|publisher=[[Corriere della Sera]]|p=39|date=31 August 1999|accessdate=8 July 2015|language=Italian}}</ref> decided not to participate in the [[UEFA Euro 2000|Euro 2000]] as the third goalkeeper.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2000/04/29/lippi-non-convoca-panucci-con-inter.html|title=Lippi non convoca Panucci. Con l'Inter \u00e8 gi\u00e0 finita|newspaper=[[la Repubblica]]|language=Italian|date=29 April 2000|accessdate=1 August 2016|author=Gianni Piva}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/euro2000/teams/italy/776101.stm|title=Injured Buffon out of Euro 2000|publisher=BBC Sport|date=3 June 2000|accessdate=15 November 2017}}</ref>\n\nPeruzzi did not play for Italy again until making a substitute appearance in a friendly against [[Spain national football team|Spain]] on 28 April 2004,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.repubblica.it/2004/d/sezioni/sport/calcio/nazionale/italiaspagna/italiaspagna/italiaspagna.html|title=Baggio, lungo, emozionante addio ma Italia-Spagna \u00e8 poca cosa|trans-title=Baggio, a long, emotional farewell but Italy-Spain amounts to little|publisher=La Repubblica|language=Italian|date=28 April 2004|accessdate=19 January 2015}}</ref> and was subsequently called up by [[Giovanni Trapattoni]] as the team's third keeper behind Buffon and Toldo at [[UEFA Euro 2004|Euro 2004]]. In August 2005, he was the starter in two [[2006 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|World Cup qualifiers]] against [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]] and [[Belarus national football team|Belarus]], while Buffon was shelved with a shoulder injury; Peruzzi then served as second goalkeeper (behind Buffon) in the [[2006 FIFA World Cup|2006 World Cup]] under Marcello Lippi,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.repubblica.it/2006/05/sezioni/sport/calcio/nazionale/conferenza-stampa-lippi/conferenza-stampa-lippi/conferenza-stampa-lippi.html|title=Lippi ha fiducia, nonostante tutto Convocato Buffon: \"E' sereno\"|publisher=La Repubblica|language=Italian|date=15 May 2006|accessdate=20 January 2017}}</ref> as Italy won the tournament for the fourth time. Even though he did not take the field, teammate [[Daniele De Rossi]] highlighted Peruzzi's important role in the squad as a key dressing room personality, due to his leadership and experience.<ref name=\"indispensabile\"/> Peruzzi retired from international football after the tournament.<ref name=\"figc\">{{cite web|title=Nazionale in cifre: Peruzzi, Angelo|url=http://www.figc.it/nazionali/DettaglioConvocato?codiceConvocato=811&squadra=1|website=figc.it|publisher=FIGC|accessdate=23 April 2015|language=Italian|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150715155443/http://www.figc.it/nazionali/DettaglioConvocato?codiceConvocato=811&squadra=1|archive-date=15 July 2015|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n==Style of play==\nA powerful, athletic, complete, and consistent goalkeeper \u2013 although injury-prone<ref name=corsport/><ref name=\"cinquantamila\">{{cite web|url=http://www.cinquantamila.it/storyTellerThread.php?threadId=PERUZZI+Angelo|title=Biografia di Angelo Peruzzi|publisher=www.cinquantamila.it|language=Italian|author1=GIORGIO DELL\u2019ARTI|date=23 June 2014|accessdate=28 October 2017}}</ref> \u2013, Peruzzi was renowned for his physical strength, positioning, explosive reactions, speed, and agility, in spite of his sturdy physique; he particularly excelled at [[Goalkeeper (association football)#Sweeper-keeper|rushing off his line]] to parry the ball on the ground,<ref name=corsport/><ref name=\"cinquantamila\"/><ref>{{cite news|url=http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/1998/04/16/peruzzi-del-piero-principi-della-notte.html|title=Peruzzi e Del Piero, principi della notte|newspaper=[[la Repubblica]]|date=16 April 1998|accessdate=7 October 2015|author=Emanuele Gamba|language=italian}}</ref> as well as at anticipating his opponents outside the penalty area,<ref name=\"tuttojuve\">{{cite web|url=http://www.tuttojuve.com/gli-eroi-bianconeri/gli-eroi-in-bianconero-angelo-peruzzi-41618|title=Gli eroi in bianconero: Angelo PERUZZI|author=Stefano Bedeschi|website=tuttojuve.com|language=Italian|date=17 February 2014}}</ref> which made him particularly effective in teams which relied on a zonal marking defensive system with high defensive lines.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.archiviolastampa.it/component/option,com_lastampa/task,search/mod,libera/Itemid,3/action,viewer/page,30/articleid,0723_01_1994_0018_0030_10451948/|title=Peruzzi, sogno mondiale|publisher=La Stampa|page=30|language=Italian|author1=Piero Serantoni|date=19 January 1994|accessdate=28 October 2017}}</ref> Due to his modest height for a goalkeeper, he was less effective at coming out to collect crosses, and preferred to punch the ball out rather than trying to catch it,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ilportiere.com/interviste/interviste-portieri/angelo-peruzzi-la-nuova-sfida-di-angelo.html|title=Angelo Peruzzi: La nuova sfida di Angelo|website=ilportiere.com|language=Italian|date=31 July 2005|accessdate=21 October 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160326153504/http://www.ilportiere.com/interviste/interviste-portieri/angelo-peruzzi-la-nuova-sfida-di-angelo.html|archive-date=26 March 2016|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> although his handling was generally reliable.<ref name=\"tuttojuve\"/> While he was extremely gifted both technically and acrobatics-wise,<ref name=\"addio\"/><ref name=\"Sarti vota Marchegiani\">{{cite news|url=http://www.archiviolastampa.it/component/option,com_lastampa/task,search/mod,libera/action,viewer/Itemid,3/page,33/articleid,0696_01_1995_0056_0041_10284763/|title=Sarti vota Marchegiani|newspaper=[[La Stampa]]|date=26 February 1995|p=33|language=Italian}}</ref> he was an efficient goalkeeper, who performed spectacular dives only in case of strict necessity: he indeed believed that \"a great keeper must walk across the line: this way he disheartens the opposing strikers, because he seems to save shots effortlessly\".<ref name=\"sfida con Zenga\">{{cite news|url=http://www.archiviolastampa.it/component/option,com_lastampa/task,search/mod,libera/action,viewer/Itemid,3/page,33/articleid,0696_01_1995_0056_0041_10284761/|title=Peruzzi. La mia sfida con Zenga|newspaper=[[La Stampa]]|language=Italian|date=26 February 1995|author=Marco Ansaldo|p=33}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://archiviostorico.gazzetta.it//1997/marzo/25/scudetto_nelle_mani_ga_0_9703257501.shtml|title=lo scudetto nelle mani|publisher=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=Italian|author1=Paolo Forcolin|author2=Lodovico Maradei|date=25 March 1997|accessdate=28 October 2017}}</ref> Throughout his career, he also stood out for his concentration, and for his ability to produce decisive saves even after not having been called into action for long periods of time during a match;<ref name=\"VITA DA DIMENTICATI\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/1997/04/20/la-risposta-che-volevo.html|title='LA RISPOSTA CHE VOLEVO'|publisher=La Repubblica|language=Italian|author1=Maurizio Crosetti|date=20 April 1997|accessdate=28 October 2017}}</ref> he was also effective at stopping penalties,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://archiviostorico.gazzetta.it//1999/settembre/27/Vieri_ordina_applauso_Peruzzi_ga_0_9909276392.shtml|title=Vieri ordina l' applauso a Peruzzi|publisher=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=Italian|author1=Francesco Bramardo|author2=Luca Curino|author3=Andrea Elefante|author4=Luigi Garlando|date=27 September 1999|accessdate=28 October 2017}}</ref> while he was not particularly skilled with the ball at his feet, and usually preferred to clear the ball away whenever it was passed back to him.<ref name=\"Sarti vota Marchegiani\"/><ref name=\"sfida con Zenga\"/><ref>{{cite news|url=http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/1993/giugno/28/portieri_anche_piedi_hanno_ali_co_0_93062814308.shtml|title=Portieri, anche i piedi hanno le ali|newspaper=Corriere della Sera|language=italian|date=28 June 1993|accessdate=10 October 2015}}</ref>\n\nA precocious talent in his youth,<ref name=\"cinquantamila\"/> he was regarded as one of the best goalkeepers in the world in his prime during the 1990s,<ref name=\"Angelo Peruzzi - Gazzetta\"/><ref name=\"VITA DA DIMENTICATI\"/><ref name=\"Ottimo Peruzzi\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/1999/05/26/sorpresa-juve-via-peruzzi.html|title=Sorpresa Juve, via Peruzzi|publisher=La Repubblica|language=Italian|author1=EMANUELE GAMBA|date=26 May 1999|accessdate=28 October 2017}}</ref> but also stood out for his longevity in his later career, which enabled him to maintain a consistently high level of performances.<ref name=\"indispensabile\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/SoleOnLine4/Z_Altro/Feed_Esterni/goaldotcom/292135.shtml|title=Mancio e Totti invitano Peruzzi a ripensarci, De Rossi abbraccia l'uomo prima che il campione, Lotito spera che cambi idea, ma... \"Alla Lazio siamo tutti utili e nessuno indispensabile\"|publisher=Il Sole 24 Ore|language=Italian|accessdate=28 October 2017}}</ref> Although he was known for his personality, leadership from the back, strong mentality, and the confidence he inspired in his teammates throughout his career, he had quite a kind, calm and reserved character off the pitch,<ref name=\"Angelo Peruzzi - Gazzetta\"/><ref name=\"cinquantamila\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/1998/05/26/peruzzi-provoca-fatemi-un-offerta.html|title=Peruzzi provoca Fatemi un' offerta|publisher=La Repubblica|language=Italian|author1=LICIA GRANELLO|date=26 May 1998|accessdate=28 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.repubblica.it/2004/f/sezioni/sport/calcio/nazionale/peruz/peruz/peruz.html|title=Nazionale, rebus Peruzzi Forse il portiere torna a casa|publisher=La Repubblica|language=Italian|author1=ENRICO CURR\u00d2|date=2 June 2004|accessdate=28 October 2017}}</ref> which, although made him very popular with his teammates,<ref name=\"indispensabile\"/><ref name=\"addio\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/SoleOnLine4/Z_Altro/Feed_Esterni/goaldotcom/292806.shtml|title=A Buffon dispiace l'addio al calcio di Peruzzi: \"Un portiere straordinario, che avrebbe meritato un Mondiale da titolare\"|publisher=Il Sole 24 Ore|language=Italian|accessdate=28 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://archiviostorico.gazzetta.it//1999/ottobre/08/Centrocampo_Zoff_cambia_tutto_ga_0_9910082359.shtml|title=Centrocampo, Zoff cambia tutto|publisher=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=Italian|author1=Luca Calamai|author2=Nicola Cecere|author3=Alberto Cerruti|author4=Gaetano Imparato|date=8 October 1999|accessdate=28 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://archiviostorico.gazzetta.it//1999/dicembre/11/Vieri_spaventa_Inzaghi_Vinceremo__ga_0_9912115027.shtml|title=Vieri spaventa Inzaghi: \u00abVinceremo\u00bb|publisher=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=Italian|author1=Nicola Cecere|author2=Paolo Forcolin|author3=Carlo Laudisa|author4=Salvatore Lo Presti|date=11 December 1999|accessdate=28 October 2017}}</ref> led some pundits to accuse him of not being as effective at directing his back-line.<ref name=\"tuttojuve\"/><ref name=\"Pagelle\">{{cite news|url=http://www.archiviolastampa.it/component/option,com_lastampa/task,search/mod,libera/action,viewer/Itemid,3/page,31/articleid,0679_01_1995_0275_0029_9185951/|title=Le pagelle di Tacconi|trans-title=Tacconi's report cards|publisher=[[La Stampa]]|author1=Stefano Tacconi|language=Italian|page=29|date=10 October 1995|accessdate=21 March 2016}}</ref>\n\nBecause of his stocky physique, Peruzzi was given the nicknames \"Tyson\" in reference to the boxer [[Mike Tyson]]'s similarly powerful build,<ref name=\"Peruzzi, il doping e quel gol fantasma\">{{cite news|url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/16-07-2015/peruzzi-doping-quel-gol-fantasma-ora-posso-dire-verita-120587143219.shtml|title=Peruzzi, il doping e quel gol fantasma: \"Ora posso dire la verit\u00e0...\"|newspaper=[[La Gazzetta dello Sport]]|language=Italian|date=16 July 2015|accessdate=16 December 2015}}</ref> and \"The Boar\" (\"Cinghialone,\" in Italian).<ref name=corsport/>\n\n==Coaching career==\nAfter his retirement, Peruzzi worked in the Italy national team staff as one of Marcello Lippi's collaborators. He was then appointed [[Ciro Ferrara]]'s assistant on the [[Italy national under-21 football team|Italy under-21 team]]<ref name=\"ferrara_U21\">{{cite news |url=http://www.figc.it/it/204/26242/2010/10/News.shtml |title=Ferrara \u00e8 il nuovo tecnico, Peruzzi vice: luned\u00ec in Figc la presentazione |publisher=FIGC.it |language=Italian |date=22 October 2010 |accessdate=22 October 2010 }}</ref> and in 2012 followed him in joining [[U.C. Sampdoria|Sampdoria]] in Serie A.\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[Serie A]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[Coppa Italia]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[UEFA|Europe]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[A.S. Roma|Roma]]||[[1987\u201388 Serie A|1987\u201388]]||1||0||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||1||0\n|-\n|[[1988\u201389 Serie A|1988\u201389]]||12||0||7||0||1||0||20||0\n|-\n|[[Hellas Verona F.C.|Hellas Verona]]||[[1989\u201390 Serie A|1989\u201390]]||29||0||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||30||0\n|-\n|[[A.S. Roma|Roma]]||[[1990\u201391 Serie A|1990\u201391]]||3||0||0||0||2||0||5||0\n|-\n|rowspan=\"8\"|[[Juventus F.C.|Juventus]]||[[1991\u201392 Serie A|1991\u201392]]||6||0||6||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||12||0\n|-\n|[[1992\u201393 Serie A|1992\u201393]]||29||0||6||0||10||0||45||0\n|-\n|[[1993\u201394 Serie A|1993\u201394]]||32||0||1||0||6||0||39||0\n|-\n|[[1994\u201395 Serie A|1994\u201395]]||26||0||8||0||9||0||43||0\n|-\n|[[1995\u201396 Serie A|1995\u201396]]||30||0||0||0||10||0||40||0\n|-\n|[[1996\u201397 Serie A|1996\u201397]]||29||0||2||0||9||0||40||0\n|-\n|[[1997\u201398 Serie A|1997\u201398]]||31||0||1||0||11||0||43||0\n|-\n|[[1998\u201399 Serie A|1998\u201399]]||25||0||1||0||8||0||34||0\n|-\n|[[Inter Milan|Internazionale]]||[[1999\u20132000 Serie A|1999\u201300]]||33||0||4||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||38<sup>1</sup>||0\n|-\n|rowspan=\"7\"|[[S.S. Lazio|Lazio]]||[[2000\u201301 Serie A|2000\u201301]]||29||0||0||0||7||0||36||0\n|-\n|[[2001\u201302 Serie A|2001\u201302]]||27||0||2||0||8||0||37||0\n|-\n|[[2002\u201303 Serie A|2002\u201303]]||30||0||0||0||6||0||36||0\n|-\n|[[2003\u201304 Serie A|2003\u201304]]||27||0||0||0||7||0||34||0\n|-\n|[[2004\u201305 Serie A|2004\u201305]]||21||0||2||0||1||0||24||0\n|-\n|[[2005\u201306 Serie A|2005\u201306]]||30||0||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||30||0\n|-\n|[[2006\u201307 Serie A|2006\u201307]]||28||0||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||28||0\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Career total\n!478||0||41||0||95||0||615||0\n|}\n*<sup>1</sup> Including 1 match in season 1999-00 UEFA Champions League qualification.\n\n===International===\n:Source:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/peruzzi-intl.html |title=Angelo Peruzzi - International Appearances |publisher=Rsssf.com |date=}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|colspan=\"3\"|[[Italy national football team|Italy national team]]\n|-\n!Year!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|1995||5||0\n|-\n|1996||6||0\n|-\n|1997||9||0\n|-\n|1998||5||0\n|-\n|1999||1||0\n|-\n|2000||0||0\n|-\n|2001||0||0\n|-\n|2002||0||0\n|-\n|2003||0||0\n|-\n|2004||1||0\n|-\n|2005||4||0\n|-\n!Total||31||0\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n===Club===\n'''Juventus'''<ref name=eurosport.com>{{cite web|url=http://www.eurosport.com/football/angelo-peruzzi_prs5086/person.shtml|title=Angelo Peruzzi|publisher=Eurosport|accessdate=16 December 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Serie A]]: [[1994\u201395 Serie A|1994\u201395]], [[1996\u201397 Serie A|1996\u201397]], [[1997\u201398 Serie A|1997\u201398]]\n* [[Coppa Italia]]: [[1994\u201395 Coppa Italia|1994\u201395]]\n* [[Supercoppa Italiana]]: [[1995 Supercoppa Italiana|1995]], [[1997 Supercoppa Italiana|1997]]\n* [[UEFA Champions League]]: [[1995\u201396 UEFA Champions League|1995\u201396]]\n* [[UEFA Europa League|UEFA Cup]]: [[1992\u201393 UEFA Cup|1992\u201393]]\n* [[UEFA Super Cup]]: [[1996 UEFA Super Cup|1996]]\n* [[Intercontinental Cup (football)|Intercontinental Cup]]: [[1996 Intercontinental Cup|1996]]\n\n'''Lazio'''<ref name=SW>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/angelo-peruzzi/54/|title=A. Peruzzi|publisher=Soccerway|accessdate=16 December 2015}}</ref>\n*[[Coppa Italia]]: [[2003\u201304 Coppa Italia|2003\u201304]]\n*[[Supercoppa Italiana]]: [[2000 Supercoppa Italiana|2000]]\n\n===International===\n'''Italy'''<ref name=eurosport.com/>\n* [[FIFA World Cup]]: [[2006 FIFA World Cup|2006]]\n\n===Individual===\n<!--LEAGUE AND FEDERATION-SANCTIONED AWARDS ONLY. No fan or magazine-voted awards. Listed in chronological order from last time won.-->\n* [[Guerin d'Oro]]: 1997<ref name=\"Guerin d'Oro\">{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/italpoy.html |title=Italy - Footballer of the Year |publisher=RSSSF |accessdate=6 February 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150121013030/http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/italpoy.html |archivedate=21 January 2015}}</ref>\n* [[European Sports Magazines#ESM Team of the Year|ESM Team of the Year]]: [[European Sports Media#1996.E2.80.9397|1996\u201397]], [[European Sports Media#1997.E2.80.9398|1997\u201398]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/esm-xi.html |title=ESM XI |publisher=RSSSF |author1=Karel Stokkermans |date=14 March 2007 |accessdate=29 November 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160207144925/http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/esm-xi.html |archivedate=7 February 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Serie A Goalkeeper of the Year]]: 1997, 1998, 2007\n\n===Orders===\n:* [[File:Ufficiale OMRI BAR.svg|left|50px]] 4th Class / Officer: ''Ufficiale Ordine al Merito della Repubblica Italiana'': 2006<ref name=\"4th class\">[http://www.quirinale.it/elementi/DettaglioOnorificenze.aspx?decorato=198737 \"Ufficiale Ordine al Merito della Repubblica Italiana Sig. Angelo Peruzzi\"] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402233855/http://www.quirinale.it/elementi/DettaglioOnorificenze.aspx?decorato=198737 |date=2 April 2015 }} Retrieved 26 May 2012</ref>\n\n:* [[Image:Friedrich Order.png|left|50px]] [[Italian National Olympic Committee|CONI]]: ''Golden Collar of Sports Merit'': 2006<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.coni.it/it/news/primo-piano/49-primo-piano-2006/2935-coni-_consegna_dei_collari_d&rsquo%3Boro_e_dei_diplomi_d&rsquo%3Bonore-_premia_il_presidente_del_consiglio_romano_prodi-_diretta_tv_su_rai_2.html |title=Coni: Consegna dei Collari d\u2019Oro e dei Diplomi d\u2019Onore. Premia il Presidente del Consiglio Romano Prodi. Diretta Tv su Rai 2 |publisher=Coni.it |language=Italian |date=16 October 2006 |accessdate=23 December 2016}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{navboxes colour\n|title=Italy squads\n|bg= #0066bc\n|fg= #FFFFFF\n|list1=\n{{Italy Squad 1992 Summer Olympics}}\n{{Italy Squad 1996 UEFA Euro}}\n{{Italy Squad 2004 UEFA Euro}}\n{{Italy Squad 2006 World Cup}}\n}}\n{{Serie A Goalkeeper of the Year}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Peruzzi, Angelo}}\n[[Category:1970 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Viterbo]]\n[[Category:Association football goalkeepers]]\n[[Category:Italian footballers]]\n[[Category:Italy international footballers]]\n[[Category:People of Lazian descent]]\n[[Category:A.S. Roma players]]\n[[Category:Hellas Verona F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Juventus F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Inter Milan players]]\n[[Category:S.S. Lazio players]]\n[[Category:Serie A players]]\n[[Category:Olympic footballers of Italy]]\n[[Category:Footballers at the 1992 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:UEFA Euro 1996 players]]\n[[Category:UEFA Euro 2004 players]]\n[[Category:2006 FIFA World Cup players]]\n[[Category:FIFA World Cup-winning players]]\n[[Category:Doping cases in association football]]\n[[Category:Italian sportspeople in doping cases]]\n[[Category:UEFA Champions League winning players]]\n[[Category:UEFA Cup winning players]]\n[[Category:Officers of the Order of Merit of the Italian Republic]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Italian footballer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2019}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name               = Angelo Peruzzi\n| image              = Angelo Peruzzi.JPG\n| image_size         = 250\n| caption            = Peruzzi in 2010\n| fullname           = Angelo Peruzzi\n| height             = {{height|m=1.81}}<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gazzetta.it/speciali/mondiali/2006/giocatori/69.shtml|title=Mondiali Calcio 2006|newspaper=[[La Gazzetta dello Sport]]|accessdate=15 January 2015}}</ref>\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1970|2|16}}\n| birth_place        = [[Blera]], [[Viterbo]], Italy\n| currentclub        = \n| position           = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]]\n| years1             = 1986\u20131989 |clubs1 = [[A.S. Roma|Roma]]                   |caps1 = 13  |goals1 = 0\n| years2             = 1989\u20131990 |clubs2 = [[Hellas Verona F.C.|Hellas Verona]] |caps2 = 29  |goals2 = 0\n| years3             = 1990\u20131991 |clubs3 = [[A.S. Roma|Roma]]                   |caps3 = 3   |goals3 = 0\n| years4             = 1991\u20131999 |clubs4 = [[Juventus F.C.|Juventus]]           |caps4 = 208 |goals4 = 0\n| years5             = 1999\u20132000 |clubs5 = [[Inter Milan|Internazionale]]       |caps5 = 33  |goals5 = 0\n| years6             = 2000\u20132007 |clubs6 = [[S.S. Lazio|Lazio]]                 |caps6 = 192 |goals6 = 0\n| totalcaps          = 478       |totalgoals = 0\n| nationalyears1 = 1989\u20131992 |nationalteam1 = [[Italy national under-21 football team|Italy U-21]] |nationalcaps1 = 10 |nationalgoals1 = 0\n| nationalyears2 = 1995\u20132006 |nationalteam2 = [[Italy national football team|Italy]]               |nationalcaps2 = 31 |nationalgoals2 = 0\n| medaltemplates = {{MedalCountry|{{ITA}}}}\n{{MedalSport |Association football}}\n{{MedalCompetition |[[FIFA World Cup]]}}\n{{Medal|Winner|[[2006 FIFA World Cup|Germany 2006]]|}}\n}}\n\n'''Angelo Peruzzi''' {{postnominals|post-noms=[[Order of Merit of the Italian Republic|Ufficiale OMRI]]}}<ref>[https://www.fifa.com/en/organisation/president/index/0,4095,129202,00.html?articleid=129202 FIFA.com] {{dead link|date=June 2016|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref><ref>[http://www.ascotsportal.com/news/newsdtl.aspx?PID=89262e2c-3beb-4080-bd5e-949f498ecbcc&CID=4ca0fc99-f8bf-4260-b379-ee5bca3085eb&NID=e47baa4d-fe98-4feb-a0ff-a007b8e62e87 AscotSportal.com] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070928185818/http://www.ascotsportal.com/news/newsdtl.aspx?PID=89262e2c-3beb-4080-bd5e-949f498ecbcc&CID=4ca0fc99-f8bf-4260-b379-ee5bca3085eb&NID=e47baa4d-fe98-4feb-a0ff-a007b8e62e87 |date=28 September 2007 }}</ref> ({{IPA-it|\u02c8and\u0292elo pe\u02c8ruttsi}}; born 16 February 1970) is an Italian [[Manager (association football)|football coach]] and former [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]], and a three-time winner of the [[Serie A Goalkeeper of the Year]] award. He is currently team manager for [[S.S. Lazio|Lazio]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sportmediaset.mediaset.it/calcio/lazio/lazio-peruzzi-si-presenta-qui-per-risolvere-situazioni-negative-_1110903-201602a.shtml|title=Lazio, Peruzzi si presenta: \"Qui per risolvere situazioni negative\" - Sportmediaset|website=Sportmediaset.it|access-date=31 July 2016}}</ref>\n\nPeruzzi is regarded by pundits as one of the greatest Italian goalkeepers of all time,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/iffhs-century.html#eukoy |title=IFFHS' Century Elections - Europe - Keeper of the Century |website=[[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation]] |accessdate=14 January 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160112150635/http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/iffhs-century.html |archivedate=12 January 2016}}</ref> and as one of the best goalkeepers of his generation.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.repubblica.it/sport/calcio/2012/01/25/news/buffon_miglio_portiere_25_anni-28741113/|title=Buffon miglior portiere degli ultimi 25 anni|newspaper=[[la Repubblica]]|date=25 January 2012|accessdate=7 July 2015|language=Italian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/iffhs-gkoy97.html|title=IFFHS' World's Best Goalkeeper of the Year 1997|website=[[Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation]]|accessdate=14 January 2016}}</ref><ref name=corsport>{{cite news|author=Furio Zara|url=http://www.corrieredellosport.it/625/2011/02/16-156120/Peruzzi%2C+il+cinghialone+che+parava+tutto|title=Peruzzi, il cinghialone che parava tutto|newspaper=[[Corriere dello Sport]]|date=16 February 2011|accessdate=8 July 2015|language=italian|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150525162017/http://www.corrieredellosport.it/625/2011/02/16-156120/Peruzzi%2C+il+cinghialone+che+parava+tutto|archivedate=25 May 2015}}</ref> Throughout his career, he played for Italian clubs [[A.S. Roma|Roma]], [[Hellas Verona F.C.|Hellas Verona]], [[Juventus F.C.|Juventus]], [[Inter Milan|Internazionale]] and [[S.S. Lazio|Lazio]]. He had a highly successful spell with Juventus, where he won three [[Serie A]] titles, the [[Coppa Italia]], the [[UEFA Europa League|UEFA Cup]] and the [[UEFA Champions League]], among other titles; he won a second Coppa Italia with Lazio before retiring with the club in 2007. At international level, he played 31 times for the [[Italy national football team|Italy national team]] from his debut in 1995, and was a member of their squad which won the [[2006 FIFA World Cup]]. He also represented them at the [[Football at the 1992 Summer Olympics|1992 Olympics]], at [[UEFA Euro 1996]] (as a starting goalkeeper), and at [[UEFA Euro 2004|Euro 2004]].\n\n==Club career==\nPeruzzi began his [[Serie A]] career with [[A.S. Roma|Roma]] in 1987. He was loaned to [[Hellas Verona F.C.|Hellas Verona]] in 1989, but was one of the two Roma players (the other being [[Andrea Carnevale]]) to be suspended for a year in October 1990 after failing a doping test because of an appetite suppressant he was taking at the time, which contained the banned substance [[Phentermine]].<ref name=\"Peruzzi, il doping e quel gol fantasma\"/> His signing with [[Juventus F.C.|Juventus]] in 1991 successfully revived his career and he soon surpassed [[Stefano Tacconi]] as the club's starting goalkeeper, remaining with the team until 1999, and winning the [[Serie A Goalkeeper of the Year]] Award in 1997 and 1998, as well as the [[Guerin d'oro]] in 1997. Peruzzi won three Serie A titles, a [[Coppa Italia]], two [[Supercoppa Italiana]] titles, a [[UEFA Europa League|UEFA Cup]], a [[UEFA Super Cup]], an [[Intercontinental Cup (football)|Intercontinental Cup]] and was part of Juventus' 1996 [[UEFA Champions League]] title squad that defeated [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]] in the final on penalties, saving two in the [[1996 UEFA Champions League Final|final shoot-out]]. He also reached two more consecutive Champions League finals with the [[Turin]]-based club, as well as a semi-final finish during his final season with the club. Peruzzi also won a runners-up medal in the [[1995 UEFA Cup Final|1995 UEFA Cup final]] and in the [[1992 Coppa Italia Final|1992 Coppa Italia final]], and was voted to the [[European Sports Magazines#ESM Team of the Year|ESM Team of the Year]] during the [[European Sports Media#1996.E2.80.9397|1996\u201397]] and the [[European Sports Media#1997.E2.80.9398|1997\u201398]] seasons. Over this period, several pundits began to consider him one of the most reliable goalkeepers in the world, if not the best one, due to his consistency, with Maurizio Crosetti describing him as \"the best goalkeeper in the world\" in 1997.<ref name=\"Angelo Peruzzi - Gazzetta\">{{cite news|url=http://archiviostorico.gazzetta.it//1997/ottobre/18/Angelo_Peruzzi_gm_0_9710181225.shtml|title=Angelo Peruzzi|newspaper=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=Italian|author=Salvatore Lo Presti|date=18 October 1997|accessdate=28 October 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"VITA DA DIMENTICATI\">{{cite news|url=http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/1997/09/16/peruzzi-konsel-vita-da-dimenticati.html|title=Peruzzi e Konsel, vita da dimenticati|newspaper=la Repubblica|author=Maurizio Crosetti|language=Italian|date=16 September 1997|accessdate=28 October 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"Ottimo Peruzzi\">{{cite news|url=http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/1997/04/07/ottimo-peruzzi-baresi-reiziger-in-picchiata.html|title=Ottimo Peruzzi, Baresi e Reiziger in picchiata|newspaper=la Repubblica|language=Italian|author=Licia Granello|date=7 April 1997|accessdate=28 October 2017}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the departure [[Gianluca Pagliuca]], Peruzzi's perceived career rival in his position, from [[Inter Milan|Internazionale]] to [[Bologna F.C. 1909|Bologna]] in 1999,<ref name=\"Peruzzi para le cattiverie\">{{cite web|url=http://archiviostorico.gazzetta.it/1999/luglio/10/Peruzzi_para_cattiverie_ga_0_9907103110.shtml|title=Peruzzi para le cattiverie|publisher=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=Italian|author1=Nicola Cecere|date=10 July 1999|accessdate=29 October 2017}}</ref> Peruzzi left Juventus for Inter in 1999 on a 28&nbsp;billion lire (\u20ac14.461&nbsp;million) transfer fee,<ref name=Inter2000bilancio>F.C. Internazionale Milano S.p.A. ''bilancio'' (financial report and accounts) on 30 June 2000, PDF purchased from Italian [[Camera di Commercio, Industria, Agricoltura e Artigianato|C.C.I.A.A.]](in Italian)</ref> and a reported 8&nbsp;billion lire pre-tax wage.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://archiviostorico.gazzetta.it//1999/giugno/28/Inter_scommessa_200_miliardi_ga_0_9906286686.shtml|title=Inter, scommessa da 200 miliardi|date=28 June 1999|access-date=2 July 2017|work=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=Italian|quote=...Inseguendo Peruzzi, la societa' deve adesso affrontare un sacrificio di trentasei miliardi: ventotto del cartellino e otto di ingaggio lordo...}}</ref> Peruzzi spent one unsuccessful season with the club \u2013 despite his excellent performances<ref>{{cite news|url=http://archiviostorico.gazzetta.it/2000/maggio/03/Nessuno_insidia_sua_maesta_Peruzzi_ga_0_00050314121.shtml|title=Nessuno insidia sua maest\u00e0 Peruzzi|newspaper=La Gazzetta dello Sport|date=3 May 2000|language=Italian}}</ref> \u2013, under his former Juventus manager [[Marcello Lippi]], finishing the [[1999\u20132000 Serie A|league season]] in fourth place, and reaching the [[2000 Coppa Italia Final|Coppa Italia final]].\n\nThe following season, he transferred to [[S.S. Lazio|Lazio]] for 40&nbsp;billion lire (\u20ac20.658&nbsp;million; in cash plus [[Marco Ballotta]] deal),<ref name=Inter2000bilancio/><ref>{{cite news|url=http://archiviostorico.gazzetta.it//2000/giugno/09/Peruzzi_alla_Lazio_adesso_fatta_ga_0_0006099872.shtml|title=Peruzzi alla Lazio, adesso \u00e8 fatta|date=9 June 2000|access-date=2 July 2017|work=La Gazzetta dello Sport|publisher=RCS MediaGroup|language=Italian}}</ref> and made over 200 appearances in Serie A and European competitions with the club, winning the [[2000 Supercoppa Italiana|Supercoppa Italiana in 2000]] and the Coppa Italia in [[2004 Coppa Italia Final|2004]]. He kept playing at a very high level, being generally considered the best Italian goalkeeper behind [[Gianluigi Buffon]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Le \u00abuscite\u00bb di Peruzzi e i dubbi della societ\u00e0|author=Luca Valdiserri|newspaper=Corriere della Sera|p=47|date=15 August 2003|language=Italian}}</ref>\n\nAlthough his contract with the ''Biancocelesti'' ran until 2008, Peruzzi retired at the end of the [[2006\u201307 S.S. Lazio season|2006\u201307 season]]: after the 0\u20130 draw with Roma 29 April 2007, Peruzzi stated that he had played his last match due to the frustration of nagging injuries. However, he was put on in the final few minutes in Lazio's final home match of the season, a goalless draw against [[Parma Calcio 1913|Parma]] on 20 May, as a goodbye to the fans. He was named the Serie A Goalkeeper of the Year for the third time in his career on 28 January 2008.\n\n==International career==\nPeruzzi was [[cap (football)|capped]] 31 times in 11 years with [[Italy national football team|Italy]], between 1995 and 2006. He was also a member of the national squad that competed at the [[1992 Summer Olympics]] in [[Barcelona]], making two appearances during the tournament. Peruzzi made his senior debut under manager [[Arrigo Sacchi]], in a 4\u20131 home win over [[Estonia national football team|Estonia]], in an [[UEFA Euro 1996 qualifying]] match, on 25 March 1995, and he was named Italy's starting goalkeeper at [[1996 UEFA European Football Championship|Euro 1996]], although Italy suffered a group-stage elimination. He was scheduled to be the starter at the [[1998 FIFA World Cup]] under [[Cesare Maldini]], but suffered a late injury<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www2.raisport.rai.it/news/eventi/francia98/199805/31/35713fbc05fc2/|title=Francia 1998: Peruzzi infortunato|website=Rai.it|language=Italian|date=31 May 1998|accessdate=15 July 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150706011322/http://www2.raisport.rai.it/news/eventi/francia98/199805/31/35713fbc05fc2/|archive-date=6 July 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> and was replaced in the starting line-up by Gianluca Pagliuca.<ref name=\"Peruzzi para le cattiverie\"/>\n\nAfter the 1998 World Cup, Maldini was replaced by Italy's former goalkeeper and record-setter [[Dino Zoff]], who confirmed Peruzzi as first-choice goalkeeper during his first year as Italy's coach. Nonetheless, after a match against [[Norway national football team|Norway]] in 1999, Zoff decided to give Gianluigi Buffon the starting spot, and Peruzzi, who was overtaken even by [[Francesco Toldo]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/1999/agosto/31/Zoff_convoca_Del_Piero_boccia_co_0_9908311530.shtml|title=Zoff convoca Del Piero e boccia ancora Peruzzi|publisher=[[Corriere della Sera]]|p=39|date=31 August 1999|accessdate=8 July 2015|language=Italian}}</ref> decided not to participate in the [[UEFA Euro 2000|Euro 2000]] as the third goalkeeper.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/2000/04/29/lippi-non-convoca-panucci-con-inter.html|title=Lippi non convoca Panucci. Con l'Inter \u00e8 gi\u00e0 finita|newspaper=[[la Repubblica]]|language=Italian|date=29 April 2000|accessdate=1 August 2016|author=Gianni Piva}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/euro2000/teams/italy/776101.stm|title=Injured Buffon out of Euro 2000|publisher=BBC Sport|date=3 June 2000|accessdate=15 November 2017}}</ref>\n\nPeruzzi did not play for Italy again until making a substitute appearance in a friendly against [[Spain national football team|Spain]] on 28 April 2004,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.repubblica.it/2004/d/sezioni/sport/calcio/nazionale/italiaspagna/italiaspagna/italiaspagna.html|title=Baggio, lungo, emozionante addio ma Italia-Spagna \u00e8 poca cosa|trans-title=Baggio, a long, emotional farewell but Italy-Spain amounts to little|publisher=La Repubblica|language=Italian|date=28 April 2004|accessdate=19 January 2015}}</ref> and was subsequently called up by [[Giovanni Trapattoni]] as the team's third keeper behind Buffon and Toldo at [[UEFA Euro 2004|Euro 2004]]. In August 2005, he was the starter in two [[2006 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|World Cup qualifiers]] against [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]] and [[Belarus national football team|Belarus]], while Buffon was shelved with a shoulder injury; Peruzzi then served as second goalkeeper (behind Buffon) in the [[2006 FIFA World Cup|2006 World Cup]] under Marcello Lippi,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.repubblica.it/2006/05/sezioni/sport/calcio/nazionale/conferenza-stampa-lippi/conferenza-stampa-lippi/conferenza-stampa-lippi.html|title=Lippi ha fiducia, nonostante tutto Convocato Buffon: \"E' sereno\"|publisher=La Repubblica|language=Italian|date=15 May 2006|accessdate=20 January 2017}}</ref> as Italy won the tournament for the fourth time. Even though he did not take the field, teammate [[Daniele De Rossi]] highlighted Peruzzi's important role in the squad as a key dressing room personality, due to his leadership and experience.<ref name=\"indispensabile\"/> Peruzzi retired from international football after the tournament.<ref name=\"figc\">{{cite web|title=Nazionale in cifre: Peruzzi, Angelo|url=http://www.figc.it/nazionali/DettaglioConvocato?codiceConvocato=811&squadra=1|website=figc.it|publisher=FIGC|accessdate=23 April 2015|language=Italian|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150715155443/http://www.figc.it/nazionali/DettaglioConvocato?codiceConvocato=811&squadra=1|archive-date=15 July 2015|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n==Style of play==\nA powerful, athletic, complete, and consistent goalkeeper \u2013 although injury-prone<ref name=corsport/><ref name=\"cinquantamila\">{{cite web|url=http://www.cinquantamila.it/storyTellerThread.php?threadId=PERUZZI+Angelo|title=Biografia di Angelo Peruzzi|publisher=www.cinquantamila.it|language=Italian|author1=GIORGIO DELL\u2019ARTI|date=23 June 2014|accessdate=28 October 2017}}</ref> \u2013, Peruzzi was renowned for his physical strength, positioning, explosive reactions, speed, and agility, in spite of his sturdy physique; he particularly excelled at [[Goalkeeper (association football)#Sweeper-keeper|rushing off his line]] to parry the ball on the ground,<ref name=corsport/><ref name=\"cinquantamila\"/><ref>{{cite news|url=http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/1998/04/16/peruzzi-del-piero-principi-della-notte.html|title=Peruzzi e Del Piero, principi della notte|newspaper=[[la Repubblica]]|date=16 April 1998|accessdate=7 October 2015|author=Emanuele Gamba|language=italian}}</ref> as well as at anticipating his opponents outside the penalty area,<ref name=\"tuttojuve\">{{cite web|url=http://www.tuttojuve.com/gli-eroi-bianconeri/gli-eroi-in-bianconero-angelo-peruzzi-41618|title=Gli eroi in bianconero: Angelo PERUZZI|author=Stefano Bedeschi|website=tuttojuve.com|language=Italian|date=17 February 2014}}</ref> which made him particularly effective in teams which relied on a zonal marking defensive system with high defensive lines.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.archiviolastampa.it/component/option,com_lastampa/task,search/mod,libera/Itemid,3/action,viewer/page,30/articleid,0723_01_1994_0018_0030_10451948/|title=Peruzzi, sogno mondiale|publisher=La Stampa|page=30|language=Italian|author1=Piero Serantoni|date=19 January 1994|accessdate=28 October 2017}}</ref> Due to his modest height for a goalkeeper, he was less effective at coming out to collect crosses, and preferred to punch the ball out rather than trying to catch it,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ilportiere.com/interviste/interviste-portieri/angelo-peruzzi-la-nuova-sfida-di-angelo.html|title=Angelo Peruzzi: La nuova sfida di Angelo|website=ilportiere.com|language=Italian|date=31 July 2005|accessdate=21 October 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160326153504/http://www.ilportiere.com/interviste/interviste-portieri/angelo-peruzzi-la-nuova-sfida-di-angelo.html|archive-date=26 March 2016|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> although his handling was generally reliable.<ref name=\"tuttojuve\"/> While he was extremely gifted both technically and acrobatics-wise,<ref name=\"addio\"/><ref name=\"Sarti vota Marchegiani\">{{cite news|url=http://www.archiviolastampa.it/component/option,com_lastampa/task,search/mod,libera/action,viewer/Itemid,3/page,33/articleid,0696_01_1995_0056_0041_10284763/|title=Sarti vota Marchegiani|newspaper=[[La Stampa]]|date=26 February 1995|p=33|language=Italian}}</ref> he was an efficient goalkeeper, who performed spectacular dives only in case of strict necessity: he indeed believed that \"a great keeper must walk across the line: this way he disheartens the opposing strikers, because he seems to save shots effortlessly\".<ref name=\"sfida con Zenga\">{{cite news|url=http://www.archiviolastampa.it/component/option,com_lastampa/task,search/mod,libera/action,viewer/Itemid,3/page,33/articleid,0696_01_1995_0056_0041_10284761/|title=Peruzzi. La mia sfida con Zenga|newspaper=[[La Stampa]]|language=Italian|date=26 February 1995|author=Marco Ansaldo|p=33}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://archiviostorico.gazzetta.it//1997/marzo/25/scudetto_nelle_mani_ga_0_9703257501.shtml|title=lo scudetto nelle mani|publisher=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=Italian|author1=Paolo Forcolin|author2=Lodovico Maradei|date=25 March 1997|accessdate=28 October 2017}}</ref> Throughout his career, he also stood out for his concentration, and for his ability to produce decisive saves even after not having been called into action for long periods of time during a match;<ref name=\"VITA DA DIMENTICATI\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/1997/04/20/la-risposta-che-volevo.html|title='LA RISPOSTA CHE VOLEVO'|publisher=La Repubblica|language=Italian|author1=Maurizio Crosetti|date=20 April 1997|accessdate=28 October 2017}}</ref> he was also effective at stopping penalties,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://archiviostorico.gazzetta.it//1999/settembre/27/Vieri_ordina_applauso_Peruzzi_ga_0_9909276392.shtml|title=Vieri ordina l' applauso a Peruzzi|publisher=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=Italian|author1=Francesco Bramardo|author2=Luca Curino|author3=Andrea Elefante|author4=Luigi Garlando|date=27 September 1999|accessdate=28 October 2017}}</ref> while he was not particularly skilled with the ball at his feet, and usually preferred to clear the ball away whenever it was passed back to him.<ref name=\"Sarti vota Marchegiani\"/><ref name=\"sfida con Zenga\"/><ref>{{cite news|url=http://archiviostorico.corriere.it/1993/giugno/28/portieri_anche_piedi_hanno_ali_co_0_93062814308.shtml|title=Portieri, anche i piedi hanno le ali|newspaper=Corriere della Sera|language=italian|date=28 June 1993|accessdate=10 October 2015}}</ref>\n\nA precocious talent in his youth,<ref name=\"cinquantamila\"/> he was regarded as one of the best goalkeepers in the world in his prime during the 1990s,<ref name=\"Angelo Peruzzi - Gazzetta\"/><ref name=\"VITA DA DIMENTICATI\"/><ref name=\"Ottimo Peruzzi\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/1999/05/26/sorpresa-juve-via-peruzzi.html|title=Sorpresa Juve, via Peruzzi|publisher=La Repubblica|language=Italian|author1=EMANUELE GAMBA|date=26 May 1999|accessdate=28 October 2017}}</ref> but also stood out for his longevity in his later career, which enabled him to maintain a consistently high level of performances.<ref name=\"indispensabile\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/SoleOnLine4/Z_Altro/Feed_Esterni/goaldotcom/292135.shtml|title=Mancio e Totti invitano Peruzzi a ripensarci, De Rossi abbraccia l'uomo prima che il campione, Lotito spera che cambi idea, ma... \"Alla Lazio siamo tutti utili e nessuno indispensabile\"|publisher=Il Sole 24 Ore|language=Italian|accessdate=28 October 2017}}</ref> Although he was known for his personality, leadership from the back, strong mentality, and the confidence he inspired in his teammates throughout his career, he had quite a kind, calm and reserved character off the pitch,<ref name=\"Angelo Peruzzi - Gazzetta\"/><ref name=\"cinquantamila\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://ricerca.repubblica.it/repubblica/archivio/repubblica/1998/05/26/peruzzi-provoca-fatemi-un-offerta.html|title=Peruzzi provoca Fatemi un' offerta|publisher=La Repubblica|language=Italian|author1=LICIA GRANELLO|date=26 May 1998|accessdate=28 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.repubblica.it/2004/f/sezioni/sport/calcio/nazionale/peruz/peruz/peruz.html|title=Nazionale, rebus Peruzzi Forse il portiere torna a casa|publisher=La Repubblica|language=Italian|author1=ENRICO CURR\u00d2|date=2 June 2004|accessdate=28 October 2017}}</ref> which, although made him very popular with his teammates,<ref name=\"indispensabile\"/><ref name=\"addio\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/SoleOnLine4/Z_Altro/Feed_Esterni/goaldotcom/292806.shtml|title=A Buffon dispiace l'addio al calcio di Peruzzi: \"Un portiere straordinario, che avrebbe meritato un Mondiale da titolare\"|publisher=Il Sole 24 Ore|language=Italian|accessdate=28 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://archiviostorico.gazzetta.it//1999/ottobre/08/Centrocampo_Zoff_cambia_tutto_ga_0_9910082359.shtml|title=Centrocampo, Zoff cambia tutto|publisher=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=Italian|author1=Luca Calamai|author2=Nicola Cecere|author3=Alberto Cerruti|author4=Gaetano Imparato|date=8 October 1999|accessdate=28 October 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://archiviostorico.gazzetta.it//1999/dicembre/11/Vieri_spaventa_Inzaghi_Vinceremo__ga_0_9912115027.shtml|title=Vieri spaventa Inzaghi: \u00abVinceremo\u00bb|publisher=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=Italian|author1=Nicola Cecere|author2=Paolo Forcolin|author3=Carlo Laudisa|author4=Salvatore Lo Presti|date=11 December 1999|accessdate=28 October 2017}}</ref> led some pundits to accuse him of not being as effective at directing his back-line.<ref name=\"tuttojuve\"/><ref name=\"Pagelle\">{{cite news|url=http://www.archiviolastampa.it/component/option,com_lastampa/task,search/mod,libera/action,viewer/Itemid,3/page,31/articleid,0679_01_1995_0275_0029_9185951/|title=Le pagelle di Tacconi|trans-title=Tacconi's report cards|publisher=[[La Stampa]]|author1=Stefano Tacconi|language=Italian|page=29|date=10 October 1995|accessdate=21 March 2016}}</ref>\n\nBecause of his stocky physique, Peruzzi was given the nicknames \"Tyson\" in reference to the boxer [[Mike Tyson]]'s similarly powerful build,<ref name=\"Peruzzi, il doping e quel gol fantasma\">{{cite news|url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/16-07-2015/peruzzi-doping-quel-gol-fantasma-ora-posso-dire-verita-120587143219.shtml|title=Peruzzi, il doping e quel gol fantasma: \"Ora posso dire la verit\u00e0...\"|newspaper=[[La Gazzetta dello Sport]]|language=Italian|date=16 July 2015|accessdate=16 December 2015}}</ref> and \"The Boar\" (\"Cinghialone,\" in Italian).<ref name=corsport/>\n\n==Coaching career==\nAfter his retirement, Peruzzi worked in the Italy national team staff as one of Marcello Lippi's collaborators. He was then appointed [[Ciro Ferrara]]'s assistant on the [[Italy national under-21 football team|Italy under-21 team]]<ref name=\"ferrara_U21\">{{cite news |url=http://www.figc.it/it/204/26242/2010/10/News.shtml |title=Ferrara \u00e8 il nuovo tecnico, Peruzzi vice: luned\u00ec in Figc la presentazione |publisher=FIGC.it |language=Italian |date=22 October 2010 |accessdate=22 October 2010 }}</ref> and in 2012 followed him in joining [[U.C. Sampdoria|Sampdoria]] in Serie A.\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[Serie A]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[Coppa Italia]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[UEFA|Europe]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals||Apps||Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[A.S. Roma|Roma]]||[[1987\u201388 Serie A|1987\u201388]]||1||0||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||1||0\n|-\n|[[1988\u201389 Serie A|1988\u201389]]||12||0||7||0||1||0||20||0\n|-\n|[[Hellas Verona F.C.|Hellas Verona]]||[[1989\u201390 Serie A|1989\u201390]]||29||0||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||30||0\n|-\n|[[A.S. Roma|Roma]]||[[1990\u201391 Serie A|1990\u201391]]||3||0||0||0||2||0||5||0\n|-\n|rowspan=\"8\"|[[Juventus F.C.|Juventus]]||[[1991\u201392 Serie A|1991\u201392]]||6||0||6||0||colspan=\"2\"|-||12||0\n|-\n|[[1992\u201393 Serie A|1992\u201393]]||29||0||6||0||10||0||45||0\n|-\n|[[1993\u201394 Serie A|1993\u201394]]||32||0||1||0||6||0||39||0\n|-\n|[[1994\u201395 Serie A|1994\u201395]]||26||0||8||0||9||0||43||0\n|-\n|[[1995\u201396 Serie A|1995\u201396]]||30||0||0||0||10||0||40||0\n|-\n|[[1996\u201397 Serie A|1996\u